title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Grease a cookie sheet. Sprinkle salt on the potatoes.
Sift the flower with powdered milk.

title: icebox pie
directions: Cook pineapple, sugar and jello until it boils.
Set aside to cool.
Boil milk and add to jello mixture.
Blend and pour over vanilla wafers crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: shrimp st. augustine
directions: Lightly saute mushrooms, onion and peppers for 1 minute in 3 tablespoons butter.
Blend in flour; stir and cook 1 more minute. Remove from heat.
Blend all ingredients, saving enough cheese to sprinkle on top.
Place in a buttered casserole and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hot salad dressing
directions: Stir and cook until thickened. Add bacon and pour over lettuce.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken in a heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan.
Add 6 cups water and stir in salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat; simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour or until very tender. Remove chicken from broth and let cool.
Remove chicken from bones and dice.
Add milk and margarine to broth; bring to a simmer.

title: lemon butter frosting
directions: Mix ingredients together, adding enough lemon juice to make of spreading consistency.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into cakes.
Roll in corn meal and fry until golden brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all the ingredients and mix well.
Pour into buttered baking dish.

title: cold relish
directions: Grind or chop fine all vegetables. Add 1/2 cup salt. Let stand 3 hours; drain.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: With electric mixer, mix Jell-O and cottage cheese until well mixed.
Add the crushed pineapple and Cool Whip.
Can be eaten right away.
Use as salad or dessert.

title: old fashioned chocolate pudding
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, white sugar and 2 of the tablespoons
of
cocoa.
Stir
together
milk
and melted shortening.
Add
to
dry mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch
greased pan.
Mix together brown sugar and the remaining cocoa
tablespoons).
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Batter rises to top
with sauce beneath.
Serve warm with whipped cream, hard sauce or ice cream.
Good cold too.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Form patties 3 inches in diameter.
Fry in just enough olive oil to cover bottom of skillet.
If patties seem too dry, adjust mayonnaise.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix Kool Aid with water. Add pineapple juice and lemon juice. Add sugar according to taste.
Let set several hours before serving.
Just before serving add Ginger Ale.

title: pistachio jello salad
directions: Drain the juice from the pineapple.
(Reserve, as some can be added later, if needed.)
Combine remaining ingredients, mix well and chill.

title: chicken and asparagus casserole
directions: Remove all fat, skin and bones from chicken; cut in bite size pieces.
Place in bake dish.
Drain juice from asparagus; mix with cream of mushroom soup.
Put asparagus over chicken; pour soup mixture over asparagus.
Sprinkle stuffing mix on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until chicken is done.

title: quick buttermilk biscuits
directions: Add ingredients in order given.
Mix well and drop by tablespoons on lightly greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: fudge pie
directions: Beat eggs and melt butter.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix with a wire whip.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Great for doubling and making 2 pies.

title: no bake fruitcake
directions: Roll crackers and place in a large bowl.
Add fruit and nuts. Melt marshmallows in milk over low heat.
Add marshmallows to rest of ingredients and mix well.
Press into a deep dish.
Keeps well in a clean milk carton.

title: date squares
directions: Mix rolled oats, flour, sugar and soda with melted oleo.
Put 1/2 of mixture in a 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Cook.
Cut up dates.
Add sugar, flour, vanilla and hot water until thick. Spread on rolled out mixture; put the other 1/2 of rolled oat mixture on top.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: mom's apple pie
directions: On uncooked pie crust, cut up apples. Mix flour and sugar and place on apples.
Cut margarine in small pieces on top of flour-sugar mixture.
Cut top pie crust in strips and alternate on top of pie.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: In a large pot, bring all ingredients to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cut back and simmer for 45 minutes, or until cooked. Pour into pretty little jars.
Attach ribbon and give as gifts. Lasts weeks in refrigerator.

title: fruit drops
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: super cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and cinnamon. Blend in butter.
Press mixture into 8-inch round dish.
Beat cheese and sugar until smooth and well blended, 1 to 2 minutes at medium speed.
Blend in eggs, vanilla and salt.
Pour into crumb crust.
Bake 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Cook macaroni
separate.
Add the remaining ingredients after macaroni is cooked
and
drained.
Salad is better after it sits for 24 hours.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken and then chop into small pieces.
Mix with 1 can of soup and green chilies.
Spread small amount onto each tortilla, then sprinkle little cheese and onion on top of mixture; roll.
Stack in a 9 x 13-inch pan and add soup and sour cream mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Add remaining cheese on top the last few minutes of baking.

title: mixed vegetable mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cold water. Combine mayonnaise, vinegar and salt.
Gradually stir some of gelatin into mayonnaise blending well.
Stir mayonnaise mixture into remaining gelatin stirring well.
Chill until thick and syrupy.
Fold in cabbage, radishes, celery, green pepper, onion and cucumber.
Pour into lightly oiled 4-cup mold.
Chill until set.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dried beef cheese balls
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and shape into balls. Refrigerate for a short time, then roll in nuts.
Makes 2 good size balls.
May make into smaller balls or cheese logs.

title: the original home-baked girl scout cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray cookie sheet with Baker's Joy. Combine butter and sugar. Add beaten eggs, milk and vanilla; mix well. Add flour and baking powder; mix well. Roll thin. Make trefoil cutouts. Sprinkle sugar crystals on top and bake for 8 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Steam cabbage until tender; drain.
Put into casserole dish a layer of cabbage, a layer of cracker crumbs and a layer of cheese. Keep layering until all ingredients are used up.
Pour cream of mushroom soup over top.
Cover with grated cheese and cover with crushed cracker crumbs.
Bake until light brown or until cheese melts and dish is hot.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix together the sugar, flour and cornmeal.
Then add eggs, melted butter, milk and lemon juice.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: stir and drop sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in oil, vanilla and lemon extract.
Blend until mixture thickens.
Add sugar and stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Flatten with greased bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Do not mix in bowl.
Put it on the pan.
Put it in oven.
Hot 50° for 2 minutes.
Take it out, put them on a plate to cool.
Eat them!

title: ribbon salad or finger jello
directions: Heat milk to boiling point; take off stove and add dissolved Knox gelatine, sugar and vanilla.
Let cool for 10 minutes, then add sour cream.
Take 1 cup of mixture and 1 tablespoon for each layer.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Mix everything together; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Recipe can be cut in half.

title: cherry squares
directions: Canned fruit may be substituted for fresh cherries, apricots or prunes, depending on the season.

title: imperial stir-fry
directions: Steam asparagus until just done; do not overcook.
Refresh under cold water.
Cut into chunks.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Whip cut yams with evaporated milk and about 1/4 cup syrup for about 8 minutes (until it's creamy, no lumps).
Add brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake in 2-quart casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.
Then top with marshmallows and bake until brown (watch so not to overbake).

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onions in butter; cook broccoli and then drain.
Cook rice.
Add all ingredients with rice.
Use about a 9 x 11-inch pan or however much will go in a pan.
Bake in oven about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: crisp homemade granola
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Grease large jelly roll pan.
Spread oats, coconut and nuts on pan.
Toast in oven 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Melt butter.
Add sugar and honey to margarine. Heat until blended.
Stir in vanilla. Remove oat mixture from oven; sprinkle wheat germ over oats.
Stir with fork.
Increase oven temperature to 350°.
Drizzle sugar mixture over oats, stir until coated evenly.
Bake 5 minutes.
Stir with fork.
Press in pan with the bottom of a cup until firm and flat.
Bake 3 to 5 minutes longer.
Cool, break in pieces and store in airtight jar.

title: dessert
directions: Take a casserole dish and a cup.
Pour milk into cup.
Take chocolate wafers and dunk in milk for a second.
Then lay cookies in casserole dish until there is one layer of cookies.
Spread whipped cream over cookies.
Continue to layer in this order until dish is full with layers.
The last layer should have whipped cream on top.
Crumble cookie on top of whipped cream.
Put in refrigerator for about an hour or until cold.
Eat!

title: cheesy zucchini lasagne
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Reserve 1/2 cup of the Mozzarella cheese. Mix remaining Mozzarella cheese, the zucchini, Ricotta cheese and Parmesan cheese.

title: pig picken cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well with mixer and bake in 3 layer pans using temperature to bake on cake mix box.

title: spinach and ricotta stuffed meat loaf
directions: Combine egg, bread crumbs, 1/4 cup tomato sauce, onion, green pepper, garlic salt and pepper.
(Reserve rest of tomato sauce for Chunky Tomato Sauce.)
Add ground beef and mix well.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together well the butter, Crisco, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add sifted flour and baking powder alternately with milk.
Add vanilla, lemon and mace.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 1 1/2 hours (do not use Bundt pan).

title: strawberries and mandarins in plum wine
directions: Mix mandarins with strawberries, add the wine and mix.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Serve in fruit cups with topping if desired. Serves 4.

title: cowboy casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add milk, soup, macaroni, corn, salt and pepper.
Blend cheese through mixture.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cheesy vegetable chowder
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in corn and remove from heat.
Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook just until cheese melts, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir cheese mixture into vegetable mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thoroughly heated.
Serve immediately.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: pljeskavica
directions: Season lamb with salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Add onion, garlic and paprika.
Grind mixture again, then flatten into thin patties about 6-inches in diameter.
Again refrigerate overnight.
Grill patties and toast pitas until slightly crispy. Place meat in pita pockets, folding patties in center.
Serve with sour cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Blend ingredients thoroughly and store in refrigerator.
Pour about 1 cup of this sauce over an 8 oz. block of light cream cheese with sociable crackers or melba toast rounds.

title: baked scallops
directions: Wash and pat dry scallops; simmer in wine 5 minutes.
Drain and save liquid.
Add mushrooms and shallots; simmer 20 minutes. In shallow baking dish, place scallops; pour mushroom mixture over and top with bread crumbs.
When ready to serve, place pat of butter on top and broil until crisp.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins and water in saucepan over low heat until raisins are plump, 20 to 30 minutes.
Drain raisins and liquid into measuring cup.
Add enough water to make 1/2 cup.
Heat oven to 400°.
Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in raisin liquid.
Blend dry ingredients and stir in.
Add oats, raisins and nuts (optional).
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until lightly browned at 350°.

title: apricot bars
directions: Cut butter into dry ingredients.
Pat 2/3 of mixture into 11 x 7-inch pan.
Spread with jam.
Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 375°
for 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: spicy chicken stew
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add onion and garlic and saute, stirring, 2 minutes.
Dust chicken with flour and add to skillet. Brown on all sides, about 5 minutes.
Add cinnamon stick, curry powder, ginger and peppercorns and saute 1 minute.
Add chicken broth and stir up browned bits in skillet.
Add sweet potato and apple.
Stir well.
Cover and simmer until chicken and potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Add raisins and simmer, covered, 5 minutes longer.
Remove cinnamon stick.
Season to taste with salt.
Serve over the rice, mixed with almonds.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add 1/2 cup oil and 2 tablespoons milk.
Stir until well mixed.
Throw in pan and
pat around.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: layered dessert
directions: Blend puddings; add milk and beat until thick.
Spread over mixture; top with Cool Whip.
Grate Hershey bar on top. Refrigerate; cut in squares.

title: ham linguine florentine
directions: In a large saucepan, cook almonds about 1 to 2 minutes, or until golden.
Remove from pan; set aside.
Coarsely chop spinach and arrange on a serving platter.
In the same saucepan, cook mushrooms and onion in the beef broth for 2 minutes, or until tender.
Combine milk and cornstarch in a cup and stir.
Stir the milk mixture into the saucepan; add marjoram.
Cook until it thickens and is bubbly.
Cut ham slice into julienne strips.
Stir in ham, mustard and parsley.
Heat through.
Drain the linguine and stir it into the ham mixture.
Pour the ham and linguine mixture all over the spinach on the serving platter and sprinkle top with the toasted almonds.
Serve immediately.
Makes 3 servings.
(For larger serving, double all ingredients.)

title: stuffed celery
directions: Mix all ingredients and stuff celery.

title: heart healthy chicken cacciatore
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken and pasta in a stew pot or Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and add chicken and simmer 25 to 30 minutes or until tender.
Serve over cooked pasta.

title: ranch dip
directions: Mix ingredients. Add salt and pepper to taste. Serve cold. Serve with potato chips.

title: quiche
directions: Blend mayonnaise, flour, eggs and milk; then stir in meat, cheese and chopped green onions.
Pour in unbaked 9-inch shell. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lentil stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes or until lentils are tender.

title: foolproof dark chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chips with sweetened condensed milk and salt.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly into wax paper-lined 8 x 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm (about 2 hours).
Turn onto cutting board. Peel off wax paper and cut into squares.

title: raisin-oat cookies(low-fat; low cholesterol)
directions: Preheat oven to moderate 375°.
Lightly grease baking sheets. Stir together flour, bran, salt and baking soda in small bowl. Beat margarine in medium size bowl until creamy.
Gradually beat in brown and granulated sugars until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, yogurt, orange rind, juice and vanilla until blended.
Beat in flour mixture.
Stir in oats, raisins and sunflower seeds.
Drop batter by level teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto sheets.
Flatten with back of spoon.
Bake in preheated oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from sheets to racks to cool completely.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chocolate dip
directions: Combine cocoa and cornstarch in a small saucepan.
Add water, stirring until smooth.
Stir in corn syrup.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Cool mixture to room temperature.

title: grandma's old fashion bread pudding
directions: Cut toast into quarters and put in 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle raisins or dates over toast.
Mix eggs (slightly beaten), sugar, salt, milk, boiling water and vanilla.
Pour over toast. Let stand 10 minutes.
Sprinkle top with a mixture of 4 teaspoons sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into crock-pot that has been sprayed with Pam. Reserve small amount of cheese for top. Cover and cook for 3 hours on low.

title: banana muffins
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together. Cream the brown sugar and margarine together with the egg.
Mash the bananas with the water and add the vanilla.
Add the banana and egg mixtures to the dry ingredients.
Stir only enough to moisten.
Add nuts if you want.
Spoon batter into greased muffin cups or paper liners.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 12 large or 24 small muffins.

title: golden baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix bread crumbs with cheese, parsley, salt, pepper and mustard.
Saute garlic in butter.
Dip chicken pieces in garlic-butter mixture, then dredge in crumb mixture. Arrange in single layer in shallow baking dish.
Drizzle any remaining butter-garlic mixture over chicken.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes, until crisp and golden.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the first five ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Put crushed Ritz crackers on top.
Cut up margarine and put on top. Put in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle French fried onions on top.
Return to oven until hot.

title: great grilled burgers
directions: Mix together and form patties. Can be grilled or fried. I use a George Foreman grill. Brown patties and remove. Add thinly sliced velveeta to hot patties. Garnish as desired.

title: summer salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Adjust seasonings to taste.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Serve with tortilla chips or with Mexican dishes.
Yield:
2 1/2 cups.

title: caramel crunch sundaes
directions: Spread butter on baking sheet (15 1/2 x 11-inch), leaving a 1 1/2-inch border on all sides.
Sprinkle sugar on buttered area. Set oven control at broil.
Broil sugar 3 to 4 inches from heat for 1 to 2 minutes.
(Watch closely; mixture burns quickly.) Crunch will have a lacy appearance.
Cool a few minutes on baking sheet.
Remove with spatula and break into pieces.
Divide ice cream in 4 dessert dishes; sprinkle broken crunch over ice cream. Makes 4 servings.

title: lobster newburg
directions: In small bowl, add sherry to beaten egg yolks.
Melt butter in saucepan and add cream; allow to boil gently for 30 seconds.
Add lobster meat and again let reach a gentle boil.
Add egg yolk mixture and season with salt and cayenne pepper.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
A small amount of flour may be added, if more thickening is needed.
Serve on buttered toast for 4 people.

title: easy pineapple cake
directions: Mix pineapple, flour and sugar; put on top of cake.
Cook at 350°.

title: school girl pickle
directions: Dissolve salt completely in water and cover cucumbers.

title: six cup salad
directions: Drain juice and mix.
It is also good for a dessert.

title: monkey stew
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Add soups.
In a casserole, layer potatoes, celery and cabbage.
Pour hamburger mixture over.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Beat in sugar, salt, cornstarch and butter gradually.
Pour in milk and blend.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add 1 cup coconut and cool. Add flavoring and nutmeg and pour into shell.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) pans.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add shortening, 1/3 cup buttermilk and bananas.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla. Beat 2 more minutes.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together (add a little warm water if necessary.
Make into small balls.
Fry in oil until lightly brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill overnight! Delicious!! Makes 6 servings.

title: poached fish fillets with rich wine sauce
directions: In a shallow pan or skillet, bring to a boil enough wine and water to cover the fish, adding a pinch of salt, tarragon and the sliced onion.
Add the fillets and simmer gently (do not boil) until fish flakes easily.
This will take about 5 minutes.
Test for doneness with a fork or toothpick.

title: cranberry wine sorbet
directions: One recipe makes 1 pint; double to fit the Donvier ice cream maker.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix and boil 13 minutes
at
a hard rolling boil, stirring constantly while cooking.
Into
a	bowl
place chocolate chips and marshmallow cream.
Pour
boiling
mixture into bowl and mix thoroughly.
Continue
to
beat until mixture is ready to drop from spoon.
Drop out
into small amounts and allow to cool thoroughly.

title: seafood jambalaya
directions: Place all ingredients into rice cooker.
Mix well.
When cooker turns off, stir and turn on again until done.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar and flour; blend well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Roll in balls size of a cherry.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet and roll in powdered sugar while warm.
You may roll again after cooled, if you like.

title: king size gingersnaps
directions: Sift flour, salt, spices and baking soda.
Cream shortening until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar; blend in eggs and molasses.
Blend in flour mixture.
Shape dough into 1/2-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar; place 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 1 minute before removing from tin.

title: coney island hot dog sauce
directions: Cook beef and onion over medium heat until browned.
Drain off fat and blend in the salt, paprika, chili powder and ketchup. Cook on low for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add a little water to thin, if necessary.
Serve over hot dogs in buns.
This sauce freezes well.

title: pickle peach salad
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Heat juice from fruit (about 2 cups).
Use all the peach juice and what is needed of the pineapple juice.
Add gelatin and Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved. Cool and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a slightly oiled ring mold or pan, and put back in the refrigerator to congeal.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients; add ice just before serving.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients.
Pour over chops.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Place in lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Layer chicken.
Combine remaining ingredients except bread crumbs.
Spoon over chicken.
Top with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until crumbs are golden brown. Serves 4 to 6.

title: tomato ketchup
directions: Cook until real thick.
Stirring some while cooking.

title: ice cream
directions: Heat milk in a pan.
Add eggs, 2/3 cup sugar, salt and flour.
Add cocoa and extra sugar for chocolate.
Add the milk, vanilla and 1 1/4 cups sugar.
Add more milk to freezer line.
Yields 4 quarts.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix sugar, vanilla, salt and eggs.
Heat milk; bring almost to boil, then mix to other ingredients.
Put in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: zucchini squash cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Bake at 350°.

title: million dollar cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugar well.
Add egg and vanilla; beat. Mix flour, salt and soda together.
Add to shortening mixture. Add nuts; mix well.
Shape into small balls; roll in sugar.
Press flat with glass or press.
Bake for about 10 minutes in
350° to 375° oven.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream sugars and margarine together.
Add eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients, chip and nuts.
Bake at 350° on lightly greased cookie sheets for 10 to 12 minutes.
(Best if slightly undercooked.)
Yields 3 to 5 dozen, depending upon size.

title: green and red casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in bowl.
Spoon into lightly greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Toss bread crumbs with butter in bowl; sprinkle over casserole.

title: crabmeat entree
directions: Bake puff shells according to directions.
Combine remaining ingredients over low heat.
Blend well.
Fill shells with mixture on baking pan.
Broil until bubbly, approximately 2 to 3 minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water until done.
Saute diced onion in butter until golden brown.
When potatoes are cooked, drain off water and add milk, sauteed onions and butter they were sauteed in, cream corn, whole kernel corn, salt and pepper.
Cook until hot.
This keeps well and improves as it ripens.
Serve with oyster crackers.

title: spinach pie
directions: Thaw spinach.
Squeeze out excess liquid.
Saute chopped onion in a little oil.
Add remaining ingredients to spinach.
Mix thoroughly.
Melt 1 stick margarine and brush 9 x 13-inch pan with a little margarine.
Place 1 layer of phyllo and brush with margarine.
Use 8 more layers, brushing each with melted margarine.
Spread filling, then repeat with 9 more phyllo layers. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until brown.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook onion in hot fat.
Add hamburger meat and saute.
Layer meat and corn in baking dish.
Season with salt and pepper; cover with tomato soup.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Spread potatoes on top and bake until potatoes are brown.
Serves 6.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Layer first 4 items in 9 x 13-inch pan, ending with cheese on top.
Mix next 4 ingredients; pour over mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning mix 1/4 cup milk with mushroom soup and pour evenly over casserole.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: shrimp fettucini
directions: Mix in a large bowl the beaten eggs, butter, olive oil, garlic, seasonings, cheese and parsley. Set aside.
Saute shrimp in 2 tablespoons butter, olive oil and white wine.
Season to taste. Add juice of 1/3 lemon. Set aside.
Cook noodles according to package directions. Combine all ingredients while noodles are still hot enough to "cook" egg mixture. Serve immediately with freshly grated Parmesan cheese.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix ingredients in blender and serve.

title: mixed vegetable salad
directions: Mix together in a large bowl the corn (white Green Giant), green beans (drained and cut in small pieces), drained peas and finely diced pepper, celery and onions; set aside.

title: baked ziti d'abate
directions: While the ziti is cooking in boiling salted water, cut the sausage into bite-sized pieces and saute in a pan.
When the sausage is almost cooked, add the tomato sauce and heat.
Drain ziti and run under cold water when they are al dente.
In a large bowl, mix the ziti and tomato sauce, the sausage, eggs, olives and the Mozzarella.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pie filling evenly over bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan, then sprinkle cake mix and nuts on top of filling.
Cut 1 stick of margarine in pats and distribute over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spinach stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells; drain and set aside.
Spoon 1 cup spaghetti sauce into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine next 9 ingredients; mix well.
Stuff each shell with 1 1/2 tablespoons spinach mix and arrange in dish.
Spoon remaining sauce over shells.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: *Three tablespoons cocoa + 1 tablespoon oil can replace the squares of chocolate.

title: 7-up jello salad
directions: Mix jello, water and 7-Up; set until shaky.
Add other ingredients; mix.
Put in mold until firm.

title: oatmeal cake and topping
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; let stand 20 minutes.
Do not drain off.
Cream margarine and white and brown sugar with oats. Add 2 eggs and beat well.
Add the dry ingredients.
Bake in a greased and floured pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine in large bowl, the first three ingredients.
Combine in saucepan sugar and milk.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Stir in peanut butter.
Spread into buttered dish, 8 or 9-inch pan and cool.

title: picante chicken-pasta soup
directions: Cook chicken, onion and garlic in oil in large saucepan over medium heat, stirring frequently, until chicken loses its pink color and onion is tender, about 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except pasta; bring to a boil.
Stir in pasta. Reduce heat, cover and simmer until pasta is tender, about 12 minutes.
Serve with additional picante sauce.
Makes 6 servings, about 8 cups soup.

title: crisscross peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder; set aside.
Cream butter or shortening and sugars; add the eggs and vanilla.
Add the dry ingredients and the peanut butter.
Mix well and knead.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix
all ingredients together and pour into jello mold; chill. Serve with mayonnaise or sour cream.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash; add the chopped onion and boil in salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Mix soup and sour cream; stir in carrots and fold this into squash-onion mixture.
Combine stuffing and butter; layer 1/2 of this into bottom of baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture over the stuffing and sprinkle remaining stuffing mix on top of the vegetables.
Bake at 350° until the dish is hot and bubbling.

title: harvard beets
directions: Cook all ingredients and pour over red beets.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 350°.
In large bowl stir first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into crust.
Bake on cookie sheet 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Empty mix into a large bowl.
Blend in oil, apricot nectar and eggs.
Beat at high speed for 4 minutes.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Cool in pan.
Remove and dribble glaze over cake.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Chop cooked sausage and mushrooms, using food chopper; place in 2-quart batter bowl and add spinach and cheese. In 1-quart batter bowl, separate egg; add yolk to spinach mixture, reserving egg white. Press garlic over spinach mixture, using garlic press; mix well. Using dough and pizza roller, roll one pizza crust into a 12 x 9-inch rectangle on 18 x 12-inch grooved cutting board. Spoon half of spinach mixture over dough to within 1/2-inch of edges of dough, spreading evenly. Starting at longest side of rectangle, roll up dough, jellyroll fashion; press seam together to seal. Repeat with remaining pizza crust and filling. Place rolls, seam sides down, on 15-inch round baking stone. Join ends of rolls to form 1 large ring; pinch, using pastry brush. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: inside out chicken
directions: Combine stuffing and margarine in a large bowl.
In medium bowl mix soup and milk.
Dip chicken in soup-milk mixture and then in stuffing mixture.
Press stuffing on chicken to make it stick. Place in shallow baking pan in one layer.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: homemade bread
directions: Combine yeast, 1 cup bread flour, salt, sugar and water in a bowl of heavy-duty electric mixer. Beat 2 minutes with flat beater. Add whole-wheat flour. Beat hard 2 minutes longer. Change to dough hook. Gradually add remaining 1 to 1 1/4 cups bread flour and beat to form soft, but not sticky, dough. Cover dough with dish towel. Set aside at room temperature 4 hours, punching dough down about once per hour. When rising time is finished, punch down once more. Divide into 2 portions. Shape into 2 round loaves. Place on baking sheets dusted with cornmeal. Cover with dish towel and set aside to rise at room temperature 1 hour. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Spray loaves with water. Reduce heat to 350° and bake until light and crusty outside and browned on bottom, about 15 minutes longer. Cool breads on wire rack. Makes 2 loaves.

title: dutch lettuce
directions: Let lettuce leaves stand in cold water for 1 hour or more; drain well.
Alternate layers of lettuce, bacon, eggs, onions and mashed, boiled potatoes in dish.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add coconut and pecans.
Cook until golden brown.
Stir frequently; set aside.
Combine cream cheese and condensed milk; beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spread 1/4 of cream cheese mixture in each pie shell.
Drizzle 1/4 of caramel topping on that.
Sprinkle 1/4 of coconut mix evenly over each pie.
Repeat layers until all used.
Cover; freeze until firm (overnight).
Let frozen pie stand at room temperature for 5 minutes before slicing.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix and let jell.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook corn according to package; drain.
Add milk; mix together remaining ingredients.
Slowly add hot milk to mixture.
Add corn. Pour into casserole.
Bake 30 minutes or until set.

title: crusty cornbread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; mix well.
Place shortening in cast-iron skillet.
Heat at 425° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven; pour hot shortening into batter.
Mix well.
Quickly pour batter into hot skillet.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter, add onion and saute until tender.
Add flour. Gradually add milk and cook until thick (takes quite a while). Add broccoli and simmer until ready to serve.

title: chicken yassa(international:  west africa)
directions: Brown pieces of chicken.
Add lime juice, bouillon, soy sauce, potatoes, carrots, onion, bay leaf and garlic.
Add enough water to almost cover chicken.
Cover and stew just until done.
Serve over rice.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: chicken livers & gravy
directions: Cook the livers by boiling.
While the livers are cooking, melt the butter in a frying pan.
Stir in the flour and slowly add the milk and seasonings.
When the livers are cooked, cut pieces in half and add to the cream sauce.
Cook on low heat for 5 to 10 minutes until well blended.
Serve over English muffins or toast points.

title: barbecued beef and corn muffins
directions: Cook and stir onion in oil in large nonstick skillet over medium heat 3 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove and keep warm.
Add beef strips, half at a time, to skillet.
Cook and stir 2 to 3 minutes.
Add barbecue sauce and onion and until hot. Place over corn muffins.
Makes 4 servings.
Serve with cole slaw.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Serve with apple.

title: chocolate cake "1941"
directions: Mix dry ingredients, water and Miracle Whip.
Stir just enough to mix.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Let cool before removing from pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: confetti bites
directions: *Such as cauliflower, broccoli, carrots, celery, green onions, cucumber, tomatoes, mushrooms, green peppers or olives.

title: new orleans drop cookies
directions: Melt shortening.
Cool; add molasses and eggs and beat well. Sift flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and soda together.
Add alternately with milk to first mixture.
Add raisins and nuts. Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Peel potatoes; slice thin and boil on top of stove for approximately 4 to 5 minutes until slightly tender.
Place potatoes on the bottom of casserole dish.
Slice onion over potatoes.
Season hamburger as desired.
Spread hamburger evenly over potatoes and onions.
Pour can of cream of mushroom soup over hamburger.
Let cook for about 45 minutes until hamburger is done.

title: minute steaks parmesan
directions: Beat together egg, water and pepper.
Combine crumbs and 1/2 cheese.
Dip steaks in egg mixture, then in crumbs.
In skillet, brown steaks in hot oil.
Drain on paper toweling.
Arrange steaks in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Cover with spaghetti sauce and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake in 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: bonnie's peanut butter bars
directions: Combine 1/2 cup melted butter, graham cracker crumbs, powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Spread into ungreased 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Melt together chocolate chips and 1/3 cup butter.
Spread on top of graham cracker layer.
Refrigerate until firm.
Slice and eat.
Yields about 1 dozen.

title: mexican tea cakes
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and flour.
Add salt, vanilla and nuts.
Form into small balls.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 400° for 10 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar; repeat again when cold.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: shrimp slurp
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish in a 400° oven. Layer shrimp in bottom of dish.
Cover shrimp with Italian dressing.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons pepper covering the dressing. Squeeze each half lemon over dish; leave lemons in dish.
Bake for another 5 minutes, until shrimp are pink.
Great with French bread!
Serves 2.

title: grilled tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes in 1/4-inch slices.
Place slices on cookie sheet.
Slice Cheddar cheese into thin slices.
Place cheese onto tomato.
Broil tomatoes until cheese melts and serve.

title: zucchini banana nut bread
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Stir in beaten eggs, bananas (make sure bananas are very ripe), zucchini and vanilla.
In separate bowl, sift together the flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Blend dry ingredients mix into banana-zucchini mix.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Ovens may vary so check with toothpick before removing from the oven.

title: sour cream and mushroom pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place pork chops in bottom of glass or aluminum baking dish.
Cover pork chops with the mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Pour the cream of mushroom soup
over pork chops and mushrooms.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Serve over white rice or wide egg noodles with a dollop of sour cream on each serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: english muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in medium mixing bowl.
Beat wet ingredients together with a fork.
Add wet ingredients with dry and mix until moist and lumpy.
Don't overbeat.
Fill muffin tins 1/2 to 2/3 full and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In casserole dish, layer the asparagus, mushroom soup and cheese.
Place crumbled crackers on top of cheese.
Place egg on top of crackers.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: nachos
directions: Fry hamburger and 1/2 onion in pan; drain off grease.
Add refried beans and 1/2 cup taco sauce to meat.
In casserole dish, put layer of Doritos, then put meat mixture on top of chips, then put cheese on top of meat.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese is melted about 15 minutes.
Serve with lettuce, tomato (cut in small pieces), and sour cream.

title: mexicana chicken
directions: Sprinkle cheese with garlic salt.
Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken; cook for 5 minutes.
Turn chicken over.
Add green onions and green pepper around edge of skillet.
Cook for 5 minutes more, until chicken is tender.
Place rice on serving platter.
Remove chicken and vegetables from skillet and arrange over rice; keep warm.

title: sunday morning sausage ring
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate).
Lightly butter a 9-inch ring mold.
Mix ingredients and pack into mold.
Bake 20 minutes, take from oven and pour off excess fat.
Bake 20 minutes more.
Turn onto heated platter and fill with scrambled eggs (8 to 12 eggs) or Eggs A La King.
Makes 8 servings.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream
butter
or
shortening.
Gradually add sugar and cream until
light
and
fluffy.
Then add eggs, well beaten. Sift together
flour,
cinnamon,
allspice,
salt and cloves. Dissolve soda
in
buttermilk.
Add
the
soda and buttermilk alternately with
the flour mxiture and beat after each addition.
Lightly dredge
with
flour and add to mixture raisins and
chopped
nuts. Last add jam.
Stir to get good distribution.
Grease
and paper line two 9-inch cake pans or an angel food cake pan.
Bake at 325° or 350° in angel food pan.

title: melt in your mouth drops
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar for 2 minutes. Add flour.
Mix for 5 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon onto foil-lined cookie sheet.
Top with candied cherries.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool on cookie sheet for 2 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: sea fare
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange fish fillets in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt, onion powder and pepper. Spoon soup over fillets; top with spinach.
Beat remaining ingredients with wire whisk or hand beater, about 1 minute or until almost smooth; pour over spinach and bake, uncovered, about 40 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: sherbet - 7-up punch
directions: In large punch bowl, place crushed ice to halfway mark.
Add sherbet, which has been softened.
Add the 7-Up.

title: nacho dip
directions: Layer beans in large flat dish. Fry hamburger and drain.
Add taco mix. Spread over beans. Top with sour cream, then olives, tomatoes and cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips and chunky salsa, however you like.

title: one dish vegetable meal
directions: Cook separately in salt water.
Place cauliflower in center of large round or oblong platter.
Sprinkle with black pepper and melted butter.
Cream potatoes and make ring around cauliflower, about 2-inches wide.
Place peas that have been seasoned with butter and pepper in the trench.
Place seasoned carrots, cut lengthwise around with pointed end to the outside of the dish.

title: frozen okra or squash
directions: Line a baking pan with foil.
Wash and slice okra or squash; spread a thin layer on pan.
Put in a preheated 400° oven until vegetable gets hot all the way through.
Take out; let cool. Place in freezer bags.

title: chicken tortillas
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large bowl, mix together all ingredients except tortillas, cheese, olives and sour half and half. Line pan with 1 layer of tortillas.
Spread half of mixture on top.
Repeat.
Top with cheese and olives.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve
with sour half and half.

title: burritos
directions: Ground 1 pound of hamburger meat.
Drain.
Mix the burrito seasoning with the meat according to the package directions.

title: gaspacho
directions: In a gallon jug (glass), make layers of the vegetables listed. Pour the dressing over vegetables.
Chill overnight.
Turn jug upside-down and marinate again overnight.

title: apricot bread
directions: Cut apricots with scissors into small pieces.
Pour boiling water on and let set until slightly cool.
Add remaining ingredients and stir only until moistened.
The batter should be lumpy.
Spoon into greased pans.
Makes 3 small or 1 large loaf. Bake small loaves 35 to 40 minutes at 325°.
Bake large loaf 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: beet salad
directions: Dissolve jello using juice from pineapple for part of the liquid.
Let jello set until slightly thickened.
Add next 5 ingredients and set until firm.
Garnish with mayonnaise, green onion and diced celery.
Chill overnight in a closed container.

title: baked beans and meat sauce
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and bell pepper; add seasonings. Pour beans in a casserole dish.
Pour other ingredients over them. Bake 30 minutes, uncovered, at 350° and then 15 minutes covered.

title: best ever clam chowder - baked
directions: Brown onion in butter in Dutch oven or small roasting pan. Add soup, clam chowder and minced onion with liquid.
Add half and half and stir together.
Cover and bake 3 hours at 250°.
Makes lots, but goes fast.
Serve hot with bread and crackers.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs and beat.
Add water, vanilla and dry ingredients.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: german pancakes
directions: Whip eggs until thick and lemon-colored.
Add milk, flour and salt.
Heat and melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch dripper pan.
Pour batter into pan of melted butter.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with hot maple syrup.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: For dressing, mix the vanilla instant pudding with the reserved pineapple juice.
Pour over fruit and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: oil crust(makes two 9-inch pies or one double)
directions: Mix well together flour, oil, water and salt.
Roll between 2 sheets of wax paper one half at a time for pie pastry.
To keep flaky crust, don't handle a lot.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Whip bananas.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs well.
Combine mixtures.
Add flour and soda.
Then add nuts and flavoring.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven and let set 5 minutes before removing.

title: black russian cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12 cup fluted tube pan. In a large mixer bowl, combine cake mix, pudding mix, sugar, oil and eggs.
Blend.
Add liquid ingredients.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Do not over bake.
Cool cake in pan 10 minutes.

title: semur indonesian
directions: Cut round steak into 1/2 inch squares.
Heat oil in skillet over medium heat; saute round steak.
Then add onion, garlic powder, sugar and pepper.
Cook, stirring until onion is golden. Add water and soy sauce. Simmer, covered one hour.
Serve over noodles, rice or mashed potatoes.
Serves 4.
(Canned mushrooms can be added at end of cooking time.)

title: double strawberry sip
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container.
Cover and turn blender on high speed until smooth (about 10 seconds).
Serve immediately.
Yields 8 servings, 1/2 cup each.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix ingredients together in a food processor.
Season to taste.

title: huevos rancheros tome style
directions: Fry eggs in bacon drippings in cast-iron skillet.
Pour hot chili stew over eggs.
Serve immediately with fresh, hot tortillas and fried potatoes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: cheddar bay biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.

title: yellow muffins
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add yolks of eggs and beat well. Add milk and flour, a small amount at a time, beating well each time. Mix baking powder with flour. Fold in egg whites (beaten stiffly). Bake in muffin tins in a moderately hot (350°) oven.

title: "awesome fudge"
directions: Pour condensed milk into saucepan.
Add chocolate chips and vanilla.
On low heat, stir until all is melted and mixed.
Remove from heat; stir in nuts and pour into a buttered pan.
Allow to cool.
May be refrigerated.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan and cover bottom with about 1 1/2 cups nuts.
Follow directions on German chocolate cake mix and pour over nuts.
Melt margarine and mix with cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Pour over mix and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine pudding, milk, 8 ounces Cool Whip and sweetened condensed milk in mixing bowl.
Mix with electric mixer until thick.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding.
Cover with 16 ounces Cool Whip.

title: blueberry pancakes
directions: Beat egg well.
Beat in remaining ingredients in order given. Carefully fold in blueberries.
Bake on hot griddle.
Makes 12 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Put rice in 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Spoon drained corn on top and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour 1 can tomato sauce over this, then 1/2 can water, onion and pepper.

title: cheese 'n chutney
directions: Process in food processor or blender until mix becomes paste. Garnish with parsley. A good spread for crackers.

title: marinated salmon steaks
directions: Combine all ingredients except fish.
Marinate fish 4 hours. Turn steaks occasionally.
Bake fish in 350° oven for 15 minutes until steaks are light brown.
Baste with marinade and turn.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer until fish is flaky.
Rewarm remaining sauce.
Pour over fish and serve.

title: spinach
directions: Cook spinach for 2 minutes less than directions call for. Drain and place in casserole.
Stir in sour cream and onion soup mix.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: elegant chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts.
Chill overnight. Sprinkle nuts on top of salad, just before serving.
Makes 12 main dish servings.
Serve on lettuce garnished with melon wedges, if desired.

title: pampushky(ukrainian donuts)
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup of warm milk.
Blend butter and sugar; add beaten egg yolks.
Add milk and yeast mixture.
Add flour, lemon rind, salt and nutmeg and remaining cup of milk; mix well.
Cover with light dish towel and let rise in warm place until double in bulk.
Punch down and let rise again about 1 hour.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut out with top of wine glass or donut cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheets and cover with dish towel; let rise again about 1 hour.
Heat 4 cups Crisco oil in large skillet.
Drop a few pampushky and let them fry to a golden brown; turn.
Remove onto clean paper to absorb surplus oil.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Line
baking
dish
with dried beef.
Wrap bacon around chicken and
place on top of beef in dish.	Mix sour cream and soup
together.
Pour
over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours.

title: sunshine pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water.
In large bowl, combine pasta and remaining ingredients, except tomatoes.
Toss to coat with reserved artichoke marinade.
Remove stems from tomatoes.
Cut each tomato into 4 wedges, leaving 1/2 inch base to keep tomato intact.
Serve 1 cup pasta over each tomato.

title: frozen chocolate mousse cake
directions: Combine and melt chocolate chips and water over a double boiler.
Add egg yolks one at a time to this and beat after each one.
In a small bowl, beat egg whites and sugar until stiff, like meringue.
In a small bowl, whip the cream until stiff.
Fold it all together and pour into graham cracker crust.
Keep it frozen.

title: gramma's cheesecake
directions: Melt butter. Mix in egg, salt and sugar.
Add flour.
Press in pan and refrigerate.

title: old-fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins and water in saucepan over low heat until raisins are plump, 20 to 30 minutes.
Drain raisin liquid into measuring cup. Add water to make 1/2 cup.
Heat oven to 400°. Cream the shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in raisin liquid.
Measure flour by dip-level-pour method or by sifting. Blend flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Stir in. Add rolled oats, nuts and raisins.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add chilies and half of the cheese.
Cook slowly until cheese has melted.
Line a 5 x 7-inch casserole with tortillas.
Layer with chicken and cheese.
Top with rest of cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter; add eggs.
Mix together the vinegar, cocoa and food coloring.
Add to creamed mixture.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and beat with mixture thoroughly.
Bake in layers 30 minutes at 350°.

title: granny's old fashioned chess pie
directions: Beat egg yolks well.
Add sugar, corn meal and butter.
Mix thoroughly with electric mixer.
Add milk and vanilla.
Beat for 2 to 3 minutes on medium speed.
Pour into an unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° until set (45 to 50 minutes).

title: california corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Cook at 325° for about 45 minutes or until set.

title: walt disney oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat 5 minutes. Add flour, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon; blend. Add oats fast. Spoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10-15 minutes.

title: stromboli sandwiches
directions: Mix together (raw) the lean ground beef, grated Parmesan cheese, onions, olives, salt, pepper, oregano and sauce.
Put in refrigerator.
Cut loaf in half and make open faced.
Evenly spread sauce on bread and cook for 12 minutes under broiler. Slice tomatoes thinly and spread out on top.
Next, put the Swiss cheese or Mozzarella on top. Broil until cheese melts.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach thoroughly in lukewarm water; drain.
Chill to crisp.
Combine oil, sugar, vinegar, onion, salt and mustard. Beat or blend in blender until dressing becomes thick and syrupy and sugar is thoroughly dissolved.
Tear spinach into bite size portions; place in large salad bowl.
Add bacon.
Pour dressing over all.
Let stand 30 minutes.
(I make the dressing in the food processor.)

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix the pudding and milk according to package directions.
Mix in the remaining ingredients.
Layer using vanilla wafers and bananas.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix instant pudding with milk.
Add Cool Whip and vanilla. In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put a layer of crackers, pudding, crackers, pudding and crackers.
Top layer should always be crackers.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and put in large bowl.
Sprinkle pudding/pie mix over fruit.
Pour strawberries over fruit and mix well.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: 4 layer pudding cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix together the oleo, flour, sugar and 1 cup chopped nuts with a fork until crumbly.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Press it in (not real hard).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: morning special
directions: Spread rolls in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top of rolls.
Top with sausage.
Beat eggs with milk. Add desired seasonings.
Pour over sausage mixture and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in 3-quart glass bowl until hot and bubbly (about 160°).
Stir; remove spices and serve.

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt butter; mix eggs and sugar with melted butter.
Add buttermilk and coconut, then add the flour.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in milk. Stir in flour, soda, powder, salt, cinnamon and lemon rind.
Stir in oats, nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Add more flour for a softer cookie.

title: oatmeal apple raisin muffins #1
directions: Baking Temperature: 400°. Baking Time: 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, eggs, water and oil well.
Fold in German chocolate, chocolate chips and sour cream.
Bake in oiled and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream of crab broccoli soup
directions: Drain and slice crab.
Cook broccoli per package directions. Saute onion in butter. Blend in flour. Add milk and half and half. Stir and cook until thickened and smooth. Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot soup.
Add seasonings, crab and broccoli; heat through. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water, stirring well.
Let stand 5 minutes or until bubbly.
Combine remaining water and mix well.
Add dissolved yeast and stir well.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap and let stand in a warm place (80° to 85°) for 72 hours, stirring 2 to 3 times daily.
Use within 11 days.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and pudding.
Add nuts, pineapple and marshmallows.
Top marshmallows with cherries.
Refrigerate at once.
Keep cold.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sugar.
Put in layers in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Toss and serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Make a well and add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Can add 1/2 cup nuts, if desired. Grease and flour 2 bread pans. Bake at 350° until done, approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: quick pecan rolls
directions: Mix brown sugar, corn syrup and 1/2 cup melted butter; spread on the bottom of cake pan.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Mix together the flour, baking powder, salt and 1/3 cup sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Add eggs and milk all at once.
Stir just to blend; knead 8 to 10 times.
Roll into a 15 x 12-inch rectangle.
Brush with 2 tablespoons butter, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Roll into jelly roll.
Cut and place on brown sugar mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine the chiles, onion and margarine.
Cook together until onion is clear; set aside.
Mix broth, soup and onion-chiles mixture.
Add chicken; blend well.
Warm tortillas.
Put 1/4 cup chicken mixture on center of tortilla.
Sprinkle cheese and roll. Place, seam side down, in baking dish.
Continue for 6 to 8 minutes.
Pour remaining sauce over enchiladas and spread. Sprinkle remaining cheese over top; bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: chili soup
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add tomatoes, seasoning mix, water, macaroni and bouillon cube.
Stir to mix.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.

title: 9-inch pat-in-the-pan pie crust
directions: Heat oven to 400°. With hands, mix all ingredients together. Press firmly against bottom and sides of pan. Do not press on rim. Bake 12 to 15 minutes until light brown.
Before baking, I sometimes fill crust with pumpkin pie mixture.

title: cocoa cream roll
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and beat to a light colored creamy butter.
Add water; then beat in the cocoa.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder; gradually add to batter, beating hard.
Flavor with vanilla.
Add at the last the butter/oleo which must be hot.
Bake in a quick oven to a very light brown.
Turn on a damp cloth; trim edges.
Spread quickly with marshmallow filling or cake icing and roll up.

title: uncooked tomato relish
directions: Peel tomatoes and chop fine.
Drain using only pulp.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into sterile jars and seal.
Do not cook.
Let stand at least 5 days before using.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: grandma's rolls
directions: Cream together first four ingredients.
Add water and flour and beat thoroughly.
Place in bowl, cover and refrigerate overnight.
Shape into rolls and let rise 2 hours.
Bake in greased pan for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: hawaiian butterscotch cookies
directions: Measure flour, baking powder and salt.
Sift together.
Set aside.
Cream sugar, butter and egg.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in butterscotch morsels, pineapple, nuts and orange rind.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon on well-greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Remove from baking sheet immediately.
Cool on rack.
Store cookies with wax paper between layers.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: italian style filet mignon(filetto di bye)
directions: Fry bacon 1 minute; add onions and saute until golden brown. Remove bacon and onion from frypan.
Brown meat on all sides over high heat.
Reduce heat and cool for 5 minutes.
Add melted butter or margarine and sherry.
Cook for another 2 minutes or until meat is cooked.
Do not overcook.
Serve with bacon and onions.
Serves 6.

title: old fashioned pumpkin pie
directions: Prepare pastry and line pie tin.
Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350 for about 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cool, plain or with whipped cream.
Makes two 8-inch pies or one 9-inch pie.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine sugar and cream cheese until well-blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Blend in vanilla.
Pour mixture over previously prepared crust.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Boil potatoes, celery, carrot and onion in water. When vegetables are tender, remove celery and carrots from water. Lower temperature. Mix the melted butter, flour and some of the milk in a skillet to make a thickening. Add salt and pepper to potato mixture. Add the rest of the milk and cheese. Cook until thickened.

title: catsup recipe
directions: Add all ingredients except red pepper and turmeric.
Cook down 1/2, then add cornstarch, dissolved in vinegar and the red pepper and turmeric.
Bottle and seal.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Wash beans and put in kettle.
Cover with plenty of water.
Add ham hock or salt meat.
Boil until tender.
Add potatoes, onions, and carrots.
How many depends on family size.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Boil until tender.
Serve with cornbread.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Slice tops off of green peppers; take out seeds.
Place peppers in enough boiling water to cover them and cook 5 minutes. Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain and rinse.
Add remaining ingredients to ground beef and heat through.
Fill peppers with stuffing; cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: olive garden zuppa toscana ii
directions: Cook sausage at 300° for 1/2 hour. Drain on paper towel and cut into slices. Cook potatoes, onion, chicken broth, water and garlic in pot on medium heat until potatoes are done. Add sausage, bacon and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for another 10 minutes. Turn heat to low. Add kale and cream. Heat through (do not boil) and serve.

title: never fail chocolate frosting and cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla and oleo.
Stir until sugar dissolves over medium heat.
When mixture comes to a rapid boil, boil 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and oleo and let
set 15 minutes; beat and use.
I use Duncan Hines cake
mix, buttered
yellow cake mix.
Make two layers. Let cool
and
cut into and make four layers.	Let layers set overnight before cutting.
They will do better.

title: bible bread(ezekiel 4:9)
directions: Mix yeast, 1/4 cup water, sugar and oil.
Set in warm place until it begins to bubble (5 to 10 minutes).
Mix white flour, 1 cup scalded milk (or water) and this yeast mixture.
Let it rise double in size (45 minutes to 1 hour).
Mix remaining flour with salt, baking powder, soda, raisins and nuts.
Add remaining scalded milk (or water) and flour mixture to yeast mixture.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Bake in greased bread pans at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix ingredients except olives.
Form dough into balls.
Punch hole in center and place olive in center.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: nut roll - potica
directions: Dissolve yeast with 1/2 cup warm water and 1 tablespoon sugar. Let rise until cup is full.

title: hot meat and lettuce
directions: In a skillet, add oleo, onion and chopped peppers on medium heat and saute.
Add meat until meat is done, then add Worcestershire and soy sauce.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour over cut up lettuce and sliced cucumber just before serving. Serve while still warm.

title: potato porcupines
directions: Wash and
peel	potatoes and shred onto absorbent paper to drain.
Combine
egg and flour and blend together.	Immediately add shredded
potatoes
to	egg
mixture
and stir until evenly mixed.
Heat shortening or oil in a large skillet until hot (375°).
Place
spoonfuls
of
potatoes
in
skillet.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, glucose, water and butter until brittle in cold water (260°).
Stir in peanuts and cook for 5 minutes; stirring constantly.
Remove and stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour onto a well-greased porcelain tabletop and stretch.

title: poppy seed slaw
directions: In
a
medium bowl, combine cabbage, carrots, onion and poppy seed;
toss lightly.
In a small jar with tight fitting lid, combine
oil,
vinegar,
sugar,
salt and pepper;
shake until well combined.
Pour over cabbage.	Toss again.
Serves 4.

title: clan morrison rum cake
directions: Before you start, sample the rum to check for quality.
Good isn't it?
Now go ahead, select a large mixing bowl, measuring cup, etc.
Check the rum again, it might be just right.
To be sure rum is of the highest quality, pour one level cup of rum into a glass and drink it as fast as you can; repeat.
With an electric mixer, beat 1 cup of butter in a large fluffy bowl.
Add 1 seaspoon of sugar and beat again.
Meanwhile, make sure that the that the rum is of the finest quality.
Try another cup, open second quart if necessary.
Add 1 arge leggs, 2 cups fried druit and beat till high.
If druit gets stuck in beaters, just pry it loose with a drewscriber; sample the rum again.
Sift 1/2 pink of lemon juice, fold in chopped butter and strained nuts.
Add 1 bablespoon of brown thugar, or whatever color you can find.
W'as Mel. Grease over and turn cake pan to 350°.
Now pour the whole ness into the oven and ake.
Check the rum again and ho to ged.

title: sweet and sour cabbage soup
directions: Boil water and bouillon.
Stir in brown sugar.
Add cabbage, potatoes and tomatoes.
Boil on high for 1 minute.
Reduce to medium heat; cook 15 minutes.
Add meat and apples. Cook for 5 minutes.
Add vinegar.

title: marbled cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, cocoa,sugar and oleo. Press firmly into bottom of 9x13 baking pan.
In a large mixing bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour half the batter evenly over the crust.
Stir in melted chocolate into remaining batter.
Spoon over vanilla batter.
With table knife, swirl through batter to make marble effect.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake in a Bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jello cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions and bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Prepare Jell-O with 3/4 cup of boiling water and 1/2 cup of cold water.
Cool.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Heat milk and sugar to a rolling boil, stirring constantly. Boil one minute.
Add chocolate broken into pieces and heat until melted, then beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Remove from heat; add margarine, vanilla and salt.

title: ham rolls
directions: Wash and peel onions.
Spread small amount of cream cheese on each slice of ham.
If onions are larger than the ham, cut off the green ends.
Place an onion on the cream cheese and ham.
Roll it up and slice it into three pieces.
Put a toothpick through each one.
Place on serving dish.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: quick chicken `n' dumplings
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil in a Dutch oven over medium-high heat, stirring often. Separate each biscuit in half, forming 2 rounds. Cut each round in half. Drop biscuit pieces, 1 at a time, into boiling mixture. Stir gently. Cover. Reduce heat to low and simmer, stirring occasionally, 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Combine beef, onions,
rice,
salt and pepper.
Mix and shape into balls.
Put a layer
of cabbage and a layer of meat balls in jars until jars are filled 1 inch from the top.
Fill with tomato juice.
Process
in pressure canner for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: joe's special
directions: Brown and drain meat. Add spinach. Beat and add eggs.
Keep stirring.
Serve immediately.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken breasts and vegetables
directions: Peel potatoes.
Place carrots and potatoes in bowl.
Wash chicken; drain well.
Place 2 tablespoons oleo in skillet.

Brown chicken, a few pieces at a time. When all is browned, set aside. Take the other 2 tablespoons oleo and place in saucepan. Saute potatoes and carrots 2 minutes. Stir in chicken broth and salt. Arrange chicken on top of vegetables.
Reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes.

title: soup bean pie
directions: In mixing bowl, beat together sugar, butter, vanilla and eggs. Stir in pinto beans.
Beat with mixer and pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done with knife test. Serve warm or chilled with whipped cream or ice cream.
If you like pecan pie, you'll be amazed how much it tastes like a pecan pie.

title: honey bars
directions: Heat oven 350 degrees.
Mix all ingredients and press into a well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Ice while warm, cut, and serve.

title: oatmeal carmelitas
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Press 1/2 of the mixture in an 11 x 7-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with chips and pecans.
Blend ice cream topping with the 3 tablespoons flour and drizzle over chocolate and pecans. Sprinkle with the remaining oatmeal mixture.
Bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes or until it just starts to turn brown.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: chili for hot dogs
directions: In a saucepan, cover meat and onions with water (just enough to cover).
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add tomato paste, catsup and chili powder; add salt.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until thick.

title: "tater tot" casserole
directions: Lightly brown hamburg with onion and drain.
Place in 9x13 pan.

title: corn souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in greased bowl for 1 hour.

title: lazy chicken enchiladas
directions: Cut the chicken into small pieces, place into a frying pan with melted butter and season with cilantro.
Cook 5 minutes or until chicken is white.

title: jeff's tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate and let stand for 1 hour.
Great with fish and Hush puppies.

title: grandma cacciabondo's chop suey
directions: Parboil celery and reserve liquid.
Saute onion, pork and soy sauce until pork is no longer pink.
Take out 1 cup "celery water" and allow to cool.
Add pork mixture into celery and water.
Add cornstarch and molasses to 1 cup water and then add to pork mixture when pork is tender.
Serve over hot rice.

title: yellow squasherole
directions: In a 1-quart casserole, place 2 tablespoons of butter. Microwave at High 12 seconds to 1 minute until melted.
Add crumbs and pecans.
Microwave at High for 2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute.
Pour crumbs onto wax paper and set aside.
In same casserole, place water, salt and squash.
Cover.
Microwave at High for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes until tender. Drain.

title: boiled cake
directions: Boil lard, sugar, raisins, water, spices and salt together for a few minutes.
When cool, add 2 cups flour combined with baking soda and nut meats.
Cook not quite one hour.
(This was probably cooked on a wood stove.)

title: applesauce muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine oat bran, wheat flour, bran, baking powder and cinnamon.
Set aside.
In a smaller bowl, combine egg whites and applesauce.
Whisk in skim milk, then pour liquid into flour mixture in the larger bowl.
Mix well, then fold in blueberries.
Spray muffin tin with nonstick spray.
Spoon batter into 12 muffin cups.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: mama bonomo's meatball soup
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients thoroughly.
Make 1-inch meatballs and brown in skillet (in small amount of butter, if desired).
Drain and reserve.

title: cornmeal rolls
directions: Cook cornmeal, sugar, salt, shortening and milk in medium saucepan until thick.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast which has been dissolved in warm water.
Then add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Add flour to form soft dough.
Knead well on lightly floured surface. Place in bowl, cover and let rise until double.
Punch down.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut up squash, onions and carrots and cook until tender.
Then add chicken soup and sour cream.
Add margarine.
Add herb stuffing.
Mix well.
Place in baking dish.
Cover top with more crumbs and bake for about 15 to 20 minutes at 450°.
Makes two casseroles.
Freeze one for later, before baking.

title: honey garlic chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Cut off bony tips of wings; cut back wing in half at the joint (this is when the frozen ones are great to use; saves lots of time). Place in a single layer in a shallow 3-quart baking dish.

title: gum drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix together the dry ingredients starting with the flour, set aside.
Mix together shortening, sugars, eggs, vanilla and soda.
Blend the two mixtures together and drop by tsp. on lightly greased cookie sheet.
I like to bake a couple just to see if the mixture is o.k.
Bake for 12 min. and let cool for 2 min. before removing from the pan.
If they flatten out too much add a little flour to the mixture.

title: texas pecan pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until creamy. Add eggs, mix well. gradually add flour that baking powder has been added to, mix well. Add lemon extract, nuts and raisins. Pour into a greased and floured 10 inch tube pan. Bake in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hour to 2 hours. Cool 15 minutes. Remove from pan. Cool completely. Wrap and store for a few days before serving.

title: delicious three cheese appetizer
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients together; add Monterey Jack cheese and artichoke hearts.
Top with Ro-Tel tomatoes, chopped green onions and Cheddar cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes. Serve with chips.

title: heath bars
directions: Melt margarine and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Boil, stirring, for 5 minutes.
Add nuts.
Spread in greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Spread them out after they melt. (Covering with Saran Wrap will speed up melting.)

title: sausage baked rice
directions: Brown sausage; drain well.
Put all ingredients into large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until all liquid is gone.

title: amber jam
directions: Wash, remove peel and cut peel into thin slices.
Add 1 quart water to peel; boil 5 minutes.
Drain; add 1 quart fresh water. Boil; repeat 3 more times.
Remove seeds and strings from fruits. Slice the fruit; add to boiling peel.
Add twice as much water as fruit mix; boil 40 minutes.
Add equal amount of sugar as fruit mix; boil now until thick and amber colored, usually about 25 minutes.

title: orange chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken; place, skin side down, in a baking dish.
Combine butter, marmalade and mustard; cook over medium heat until smooth, stirring constantly.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste and turn once.
(Sauce is good served over rice.)

title: jean's quick 'n easy casserole
directions: Heat chips in 9 x 13-inch pan in oven at 400° for 5 minutes. Remove and add heated refried beans over chips.
Add cooked ground beef or chicken, spreading evenly.
Top with shredded lettuce, tomatoes and grated cheese.
Return to oven and heat until cheese melts.
Serve with salsa and sour cream.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Use pineapple juice in batter in place of water.
(If juice is not enough, add water to make 1 1/3 cups.)
Bake in
a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cake is cool, mix vanilla pudding with cup of milk and cream cheese.
Beat well until all is blended; then fold in pineapple.
Spread on top of cake.
Spread Cool Whip on top of that, then top with coconut.

title: cream cheese blintzes
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, sugar and egg yolks.
Remove crust from bread and roll bread out flat.
Place large tablespoon of cream cheese mixture in the middle of slice of bread.
Fold ends into center.
Press middle of bread to spread cheese mixture; cut into thirds.
Melt 1 1/2 sticks of butter.	Dip each square in butter.
Place on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Can freeze.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread and cube.
Arrange 1/2 of the bread in buttered 13 x 9-inch dish.
Brown sausage; drain.
Crumble sausage on top of bread.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the grated cheese on top. Arrange rest of bread on top.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Beat eggs, milk, mustard and pepper together; pour over bread mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (until set).

title: macaroni and cheese salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package; drain and run cold water to chill.
Mix rest of ingredients, chopped and about 4 tablespoons mayonnaise.

title: grilled chicken fruit salad
directions: Lightly coat the grill with cooking spray and preheat for 5 minutes.
Grill the chicken for 5-7 minutes.
Cool and cut into small cubes.
In a large salad bowl, combine the chicken, grapes, celery, onion, and walnuts.
Mix together the mayonnaise, mustard, salt, pepper and lemon juice to make dressing.
Pour over the chicken salad and toss lightly.

title: gingerbread
directions: Sift the first 6 ingredients together.
Combine oil, eggs and molasses.
Pour liquid ingredients into center of dry ingredients.
Add boiling water.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch greased pan or 9-inch round pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in preheated pan (iron skillet). Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: banana-wheat quick bread
directions: Tightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Combine all ingredients in large mixer bowl; blend at low speed.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into prepared pan.
(After baking immediately remove from pan.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked apples
directions: Wash and core apples.
Remove skin from upper half of apple. Place apples in baking dish and fill center of each apple with sugar, butter and cinnamon.
Pour water, 1/4 inch deep, into baking dish.
Bake apples in oven at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Thaw spinach and mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in square casserole pan.

title: scallops au gratin
directions: Rinse scallops, cut into cubes and set aside.
