Pour 1/4 cup liquid Butter Buds into a medium size saucepan.
Add mushrooms and saute slowly over low heat until tender.
Remove mushrooms; set aside.
In the same pan, blend together the 2 tablespoons Butter Buds, or chicken broth, cornstarch, salt, dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce and white pepper.
Gradually stir in milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Add scallops, mushrooms and sherry to the sauce.
Pour mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray.
Sprinkle crushed crackers on top and finish with Parmesan cheese over the crackers. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Leave in pan, undrained.
Add water and vinegar to dry ingredients.
Add to fried bacon pieces in pan. Cook, stirring constantly until it thickens.
Excellent on spinach salad.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Grease 2 loaf pans.
Mix all ingredients except the last 2. Pour 1/4 batter in each pan.
Sprinkle on the cinnamon and sugar. Pour over remaining batter.
Marble through with knife.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken noodle parmesan
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, combine soup, milk, cheese and pepper; add noodles and chicken.
Over low heat, heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.

title: kieske
directions: Cook pork hocks until done in enough water to cover meat. Take out meat and cool.
In water, put in pearl barley until cool. When meat is real cool, grind.
Grind onion.
When pearl barley is done, add the meat and cook 5 minutes more.
If mixture is dry, add a little water so the kieske won't be too thick.
Season with salt and pepper.
When done, you can serve or put in pan and bake until light brown.
Serve.

title: cole slaw
directions: In a small bowl, mix together the vegetable oil and vinegar. Add mustard, celery seed, mayonnaise, salt, pepper and paprika. Mix well and pour over shredded cabbage and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put ina 2-quart casserole (ungreased).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: frozen pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and cream cheese (I heat cream cheese a little to mix better).
Fold in strawberries and mashed bananas. Fold in Cool Whip and pour into graham cracker crust or 2 small pie shells.

title: milk chocolate pie
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture starts to boil.
Continue to cook until it boils about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add oleo and vanilla.
Stir until oleo melts.
Cook a few minutes, then pour into 9-inch baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: shirley's delicious buns
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Boil the 2 cups water and add lard, instant potatoes, sugar and salt. Cool until lukewarm. Add the beaten eggs.
Beat well with mixer until mixed well. Add yeast and mix again.
Add 2 cups flour.
Mix until bubbly. Stir in rest of flour until not sticky.
Knead 10 minutes.
Let rise until double in greased bowl.
Punch down.
Let rise and punch down again.
Let rise again. Shape into rolls or buns. Let rise until double.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until light brown. Butter top.
Enjoy!

title: country supper casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat, onion and bell pepper. Drain and add tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Place mashed potatoes in bottom of greased casserole. Drain green beans and carrots.
Mix and put on top of mashed potatoes.
Top with meat. Top meat with cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Serve with green salad.

title: dump cake
directions: Takes a
x
9-inch
pan
or dish (greased).
Spread pineapple well over bottom.
Spread fruit filling over pineapple. Sprinkle
nuts and coconut over top.
Sprinkle whole box of cake mix
over
top of mixture and cut margarine into pats and place over top of cake.
Bake for one hour at 350°.

title: moist cherry cake
directions: Prepare cake mix by directions on box.
Pour half of batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add cherry filling, then remaining batter.
Mix sugar, nuts and cinnamon. Sprinkle over cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: yummy caramel nut pie
directions: Mix 2 cups sugar, flour, milk, egg yolks, water, oleo and vanilla.
Cook over low to medium heat until slightly thickened, stirring constantly.
While cooking this mixture, brown 1 cup sugar in iron skillet over medium to high heat, stirring constantly.
After sugar is dissolved and browned, stir in cooked mixture; stir constantly until well blended.
Add pecans.
Beat egg whites; sweeten to taste.
Stir small amount of egg whites into cooked mixture.
Pour cooked mixture into 2 baked pie shells and top with remaining meringue; brown lightly.
Yields 2 pies.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Add together everything except peas.
Cook until thickens like gravy.
Add peas and mix well.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken divine
directions: Mix eggs, soup, mayo and mustard together.

Unroll dough into 2-inch long rectangles. Press in 13 x 9 pan and up the sides 1/2-inch. Layer cheese, chicken, cooked and drained broccoli, mixture of soup, mayo, eggs, mustard and onion. Pour over chicken. Bake 26 to 31 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Wash and boil sweet potatoes until soft.
Peel potatoes and mash.
Mix mashed sweet potatoes, melted butter, sugar, evaporated milk, eggs, allspice and salt.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until solid.

title: apricot conserve(heritage recipe)
directions: Wash apricots and run through food chopper.
Cover with water and soak a short time.
Then add sugar and pineapple, cook about half hour.
Care should be taken that it doesn't stick, at it burns easily.
Makes four quarts.

title: banana-nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400° . Grease 12 standard size muffin pan cups or use paper liners.
Beat together butter and sugar at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Beat in bananas until smooth.
Mix together flour, salt, baking powder, and baking soda.
Alternately stir flour mixture and buttermilk into egg mixture until dry ingredients are just moistened.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Do not overmix batter, it should not be completely smooth.
Spoon batter into prepared pan, filling two-thirds full.
Bake until lightly golden, 15 to 18 minutes.
Transfer muffin-pan cups to a wire rack to cool slightly.
Turn out into rack.
Serve warm.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and put into 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Mix flour and 1 cup of sugar; sprinkle over berries. Drizzle melted oleo or butter over the flour and sugar mixture, then sprinkle chopped pecans and 1/4 cup sugar over all.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: date cookies
directions: Mix and form into 2 rolls.
Place in refrigerator overnight. Slice about 1/2-inch thick and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour condensed milk over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients; press down.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until browned.
Allow bars to cool.

title: lemon squares
directions: Cream together flour, butter and confectioners sugar.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven until pale gold at edges (about 15 minutes).
Pour lemon topping over hot crust and return to oven until set, about 30 minutes.
Loosen edges; cool.
If desired, sift extra confectioners sugar over top. Cut in squares.
Makes 48 (1 1/2-inch) squares.

title: dick's onion bread
directions: Bake on medium in a bread machine.

title: ham slice with rice
directions: Place ham in 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch microwaveproof dish.
Mix sour cream and mustard in large bowl; stir in rice, raisins and onions. Spoon mixture around ham.
Cover tightly and microwave on Medium-high (70%) for 5 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn and microwave until hot, 4 to 6 minutes longer.

title: bean casserole
directions: Drain first can of beans, then add a can of soup and onions. Repeat layer.
Top with cheese.
Heat in a 350° oven until hot.

title: pumpkin dessert bread
directions: Place all dry ingredients in large mixing bowl; with spoon, make a deep well in center.
In this well, add all other ingredients.
Stir carefully just enough to dampen all dry ingredients.
Pour into loaf pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Delicious served with spiced tea.
Makes 2 loaves; 12 to 18 servings.

title: mexican taco dip
directions: Using a round pizza tray, layer the ingredients:

title: clam chowder
directions: Drain canned clams; reserve liquid.
Place bacon, onions and potatoes in 3-quart casserole.
Add clam liquid and water to make 2 cups.
Cover and cook 1 hour.
Melt butter in a 2-cup measure. Stir in flour.
Pour into potato mixture; mix well.
Add milk, salt, pepper and clams.
Cook to warm up.

title: sausage balls
directions: Roll
sausage
into
small balls (will shrink about 1/3 size). Place
on
cookie
sheet
and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375°. Combine
remaining
ingredients
to
make
sauce.
Pour sauce over balls and let set overnight in refrigerator.
(Not necessary if
in
a
hurry for a party; just as good!) Remove from heat and serve.

title: mom's broccoli casserole
directions: Steam the broccoli until halfway done.
Combine remaining ingredients; place in baking dish with broccoli.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cream of lettuce soup
directions: Remove stem ends of lettuce.
Heat 2 tablespoons margarine in large saucepan.
Add lettuce and onion; cover and cook until leaves are tender enough to puree.
Puree in blender; rinse pan. Place remaining margarine and oil in pan.
Add flour and cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add stock; bring to boil, continuing to stir.
Add puree, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat; dissolve dry milk into liquid milk and heat.
Before serving, beat eggs with milk mixture.
Stir into hot soup and serve.

title: carolina baked ham
directions: Soak a salt-cured ham overnight in water and 1 cup vinegar covered pan.
Drain.
Cover with hot water.
Add another 1 cup vinegar; simmer until parboiled.
Drain and rinse.
Again, place ham in hot water; cover and add 2 bay leaves, 3 tablespoons sugar and strip of lemon peel with chopped onions.
Gently simmer until tender (about 3 hours).
Mix 1 cup brown sugar and 1 teaspoon dry mustard.
Pat mixture on ham and stud a few cloves.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: upside-down date pudding
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream. Makes 9 servings.

title: seafood jambalaya
directions: Boil rice; set aside.
Saute onion over medium-slow heat in oil until almost brown.
Add shrimp and cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add parsley, shallots and bell pepper; saute 10 minutes, stirring.
Add smoked sausage and cook for 10 minutes. Add 3 cups water and cook for 1/2 hour over medium heat.
Add oysters and crabmeat.
Cook 15 minutes; salt and pepper to taste. Add rice, a little at a time, steadily stirring, until all rice is in.
Heat over medium heat for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together until the mixture is like meal.
Add egg, water and vinegar; mix well.
Make a ball and let set at least 15 minutes in refrigerator before rolling on floured surface.
Bake at 400° until golden.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: *May use self-rising flour; omit soda, salt and baking powder.

title: harriette's rhubarb cream pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; add sugar mixed with flour and melted butter. Stir in rhubarb and spice if desired.
Fill pie crust and/or freeze filling in container.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat for about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together first five ingredients.
Sift flour, soda and salt and add to the creamed mixture.
Add oats, nuts and chocolate chips.
Stir by hand until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoons on a very lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet to waxed paper to cool.
Very crisp cookie.

title: fudgy no-bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat milk, cocoa, butter or paste and sugar in a pot until boiling.
Stir constantly.
Add vanilla and pour mixture over oatmeal.
Mix oatmeal well.
Drop by spoon onto ungreased pan or pat into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Place in refrigerator.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: venison stew
directions: Brown onions, garlic and venison. Cover with beef broth. Add all other ingredients. Cover and simmer until meat is tender. Add carrots and potatoes to broth and cook until done.

title: carrots in sauce(colorful, good for holiday dinners)
directions: Cook carrots somewhat underdone, next to raw.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix all; add cool carrots.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Will keep weeks.

title: easy berry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in small, shallow pan.
Mix milk, sugar, flour and baking powder together and pour over melted butter which has been placed in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle sugar over the top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave lemon chicken
directions: In 10-inch square microwave dish, place chicken, skin side down.
Pour 1/4 cup lemon juice over chicken.
Heat, covered, on roast 10 minutes.
Turn chicken over; add remaining lemon juice and seasonings.
Heat, covered, on roast 9 to 11 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: double chocolate chip cookies(soft)
directions: Mix all together.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese.
Let cheeses soften at room temperature. Mix all ingredients except nuts.
After mixing, let chill for 2 hours.
Mold into ball or log, then roll in nuts.

title: blina - a "deutsch, not dutch" pancake
directions: Soak yeast in water; set aside.
Sift together flour, salt and sugar.
Add enough water to make a thin batter, then add yeast mixture and egg.
Let set overnight.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put 1/3 cup mixture in cup and add hot water.

title: jiffy beef cornbread bake
directions: Brown
ground
beef.
Put
1/2 cornbread mix in greased large casserole.	Cover
with creamed corn, then ground beef, onions, jalapenos
and
cheese.
Top with remaining cornbread mix.	Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: tuna puff sandwiches
directions: Mix all together.
Split hamburg buns and slice tomatoes. Place tuna salad on top of bun, then add sliced tomatoes and spread with cheese and mayonnaise mixture.
Broil until these get brown and puffy.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Blend shortening, flour and salt until fine.
Beat egg and vinegar together; add enough water to make one cup.
Add both mixtures together until smooth and can be rolled into a ball. Makes 6 single or 4 double crusts.
Freeze or keeps in refrigerator for days.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix together cream cheese, olives, onion and approximately 1/3 of the jar of picante sauce.
Spread mixture on tortillas.
It will take approximately 1 tablespoon of mixture to cover tortilla. Roll up.
Seal with a dab of cream cheese, if needed.
Cut into thirds.
Serve with remainder of picante sauce.

title: frosty orange
directions: In a blender, combine milk, water, orange juice concentrate, ice cubes, vanilla and sugar. Blend until smooth. Pour into 3 (12-ounce) glasses and enjoy with a straw.

title: baked haddock
directions: Arrange fish in dish and spread soup over fish to bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Melt butter, then add to butter finely chopped onion, Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt and Ritz crackers. Sprinkle ingredients over fish and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: holiday fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Slice bananas into gelatin mixture.
Add frozen strawberries and undrained pineapple.
Pour half the mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Refrigerate one hour or until firm.
In mixer bowl, beat cream cheese with sour cream and sugar; spread over chilled layer. Gently spoon remaining gelatin mixture on top.
Refrigerate until firm (about 2 hours).

title: cauliflower gratinee
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add garlic and saute 2 minutes.
Stir in the Prosciutto and saute 2 more minutes.
Add cauliflower and cook just until it begins to lose its crispness, 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in flour and then the cream; blend well.
Season with the cayenne, salt and pepper to taste.
Heat to boiling and immediately remove from heat.
Pour the cauliflower into a shallow gratin dish.
Top with the cheese and parsley.
Bake until top is lightly browned and bubbling, about 30 minutes.

title: potato rolls
directions: Cook potato in water until tender; drain, mash and measure out 1/2 cup.
In large bowl, combine 2 cups flour and yeast.
In saucepan, heat milk, sugar, shortening and salt until warm (115° to 120°).
Stir constantly until shortening melts; add to preceding along with beaten egg and potato.
Beat 1/2 minute on low; scrape bowl often.
Beat 3 minutes on high.
Then with spoon, stir in enough more flour to make soft dough.
Turn out on floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 minutes.
Shape ball; return to greased bowl.
Cover; let rise an hour.
Punch down; place on board.
Cover; let rest 10 minutes.
Make into rolls; place in greased pans.
Let rise until double.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: cowboy salad
directions: In bottom of large bowl, put one layer of grated apples with sugar to taste, then some ground walnuts.
Then spread Cool Whip over nuts.
Put one layer of crushed pineapple with sugar to taste.
Layer ground nuts, then Cool Whip.
Put one layer of raisins, ground nuts and Cool Whip.
Top with sliced bananas with sugar to taste.

title: candy apples
directions: Melt caramels in water in double boiler; stir until smooth. Stick wooden skewer into blossom end of each apple; dip apple in caramel syrup, turning until completely coated.
Add a few drops of water if syrup is too stiff.
Roll bottom half of each apple in chopped nuts at once.
Set on waxed paper covered cookie sheet. Chill until coating is firm.

title: nonnie's spicy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Add beaten eggs last and mix well. Bake in covered casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour. Remove cover and brown top for a few minutes. Spread 1 can of tomato sauce (small can) over top and cook for another 10 to 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: grandma's noodle and beef casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add onions and pepper with butter; saute until tender.
Mix rest of ingredients (I add some tomato juice to keep casserole juicy.)

title: the best brownies
directions: Blend oil, sugar and vanilla in a mixing bowl.
Add eggs; beat well with a spoon.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; gradually add to egg mixture until well blended.
Stir in nuts.

title: dulce de calabaza(also known as candied pumpkin)
directions: Soak pumpkin overnight in lime water (water should cover pumpkin).
To make lime water, dissolve 1 tablespoon quick lime to 1 quart cold water.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix hamburger, rice and onion.
Shape into balls.
Combine tomato soup and water.
Warm in pan.
Put hamburger balls in soup, salt and pepper.
Simmer about 1/2 hour.

title: batter dipped hot dogs
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add milk, egg and oil. Mix together thoroughly.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: honey butter carrots
directions: Kids love these sweet carrots!!

title: french marinated pork chops
directions: Place chops in glass baking dish. Put the remaining ingredients in a blender and process on low.
Pour marinade over chops. Refrigerate for 2 hours or more, turning chops occasionally.
Place chops on grill 4 to 6-inches over coals. Cook 12 to 15 minutes per side, turning and brushing with marinade sauce frequently.

title: beef and cheese buns
directions: Brown meat and pepper.
Drain and stir in tomato sauce, soup, oregano and basil.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Cut rolls in half and spoon meat mixture on the bottom.
Spoon cheese mixture over the meat. Wrap individually in foil.
Place on a baking sheet
and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on slightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: egg souffle
directions: Place bread in 8 x 8-inch pan; top with melted butter.
Mix salt, mustard and eggs together; beat well.
Add milk and beat again.
Top bread slices with Swiss cheese; add egg mixture. Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: speedy taco bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook ground beef and onion until browned. Add taco mix, tomato sauce and corn.
Put in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour salsa over meat. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Prepare corn bread muffin mix according to directions on box.
Spoon over the cheese.
Bake 35 minutes or until corn bread is golden brown.
Serve with sour cream, chopped tomato and shredded lettuce, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon bread (a tea bread)
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar; mix the eggs in the mixture. Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt; set aside on wax paper. Add the sifted dry ingredients alternately with the milk and mix completely; mix in the nuts and lemon peel. Blend well. Place the mixture in a buttered bread pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour. After baking, mix juice of 1 lemon mixture over the top.
Let stand a few minutes, remove from pan and cool. Slice when cool and serve.

title: lemon and orange pound cake
directions: Beat eggs and butter.
Mix in all remaining ingredients and beat for 10 minutes.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy lemon pork chops
directions: Bread pork chops, shaking off excess crumbs.
Place in frying pan in heated oil and fry until golden brown.
While preparing chops, place chicken broth, juice of lemons, parsley and pepper in measuring cup and blend together.
When chops are done, scrape the pan while adding mixture.
Slice lemons that have been squeezed and place over each chop.
Add parsley to garnish.
Cover pan and cook on low heat until sauce thickens and is brown in color.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown ground steak with salt, pepper and garlic.
Pour half into baking dish.
Cover with onion, potatoes, then cheese and remainder of ground steak.
Top with thin layer of ketchup.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
(Leftover meatloaf can be substituted for ground beef for meatloaf pie.)

title: rice pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions.
Mix pudding with rice.
May add coconut or raisins or serve plain.

title: chicken salad in a tomato boat
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Cut tomatoes almost through to make 6 to 8 petals.
Fill with chicken mixture.
Garnish with olives. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: best ever corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cabbage noodles
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water until tender; drain.
Add 2 tablespoons of butter, salt and pepper and put aside.
Cut up cabbage head by slicing.
Fry in corn oil until brown and tender. Empty into noodles and stir well.
Serve while hot.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Blend in milk, margarine, pineapple and bread crumbs.
Pour into a well-greased casserole and bake in preheated oven for 45 minutes at 350°.
Especially good served with baked ham instead of sweet potatoes.

title: cleo's custard pie
directions: Mix
well.
Pour
into baking dish or unbaked pie shell that has been buttered.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until center is set.

title: spring delight(serves 8)
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Heat soup until boiling.
(Do not add water.)
Pour over dry ingredients and stir until dissolved. Add remaining ingredients and pour into greased mold.
Chop vegetables in blender and it sure goes faster.

title: sweet and sour brisket
directions: Place brisket on onions and garlic.
Mix other ingredients and pour over brisket.
Cover and roast in 350° oven until tender, approximately 1 hour per pound.
Watch that liquid doesn't evaporate!!!

title: mom's 24 hour fruit salad
directions: In a small pan, mix together egg, sugar and lemon juice.
Cook until thickens.
Cool.

title: crock-pot roast with gravy
directions: In crock-pot, stir in vinegar, soup mix and ketchup.
Mix well.
Add roast and cover.
Cook on low five to nine hours, or until tender.

title: green chile and chicken enchiladas
directions: Cut chicken into small bite sized pieces.
In skillet brown onion and garlic lightly in oil.
Add 1/4 to 1/2 can enchilada sauce to skillet.
Add chicken, olives and green chilies.
Let mixture simmer a few minutes.
In a 13 x 9-inch greased baking dish, layer one layer of tortillas that have been dipped in remaining enchilada sauce, a layer of meat mixture and a layer of cheese.
Repeat layering process until all ingredients have been used up.
(End with a layer of cheese.)
When all layers are finished, pour remaining green sauce over enchiladas.
Bake covered in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Ole!!

title: crab enchiladas
directions: Add just enough oil to bottom of frypan to avoid sticking. Wash, peel (if necessary) and slice vegetables for stir-fry.
I like almost anything fresh from the garden.
I've never come across a bad combination. I like to mix the colors so the dish is pleasing to the eye.

title: banana punch
directions: In blender, combine bananas, lemonade and orange juice.
Blend well.
Pour into a large freezable container.
Add pineapple juice and water.
Freeze overnight.
To serve, put punch in bowl and pour in 7-Up.
Use potato masher to mash up punch until slushy. Decorate with orange or lemon slices.

title: fettucini
directions: Cook noodles.
Rinse thoroughly.
Add other ingredients. Simmer for an hour or so.

title: texas hash
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef, breaking up large pieces. Drain off all except 1 tablespoon fat. Stir in onion and green pepper. Cook and stir 5 minutes or until onion is tender. Season with chili powder, salt and pepper. Add tomatoes. Break up with spoon, then add rice and water.
Bring to a boil. Stir once. Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid absorbed. Makes 4 servings.

title: foil steak supper
directions: Place the steak in center of a piece of foil and sprinkle with soup mix.
Cover with potatoes, carrots, celery, green pepper and onion and dot with butter.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Fold foil over, leaving space for steam.
Place on a grill over low coals and cook for about 1 hour and 30 minutes or until done.

title: glorified rice
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken-cheese soup
directions: Simmer chicken until tender.
Remove chicken, cool and dice. Boil broth, uncovered, until reduced to 1 cup.
Add onion, carrots and celery.
Simmer until tender, about 10 minutes.
Gradually stir in soup and milk.
Add chicken and cheese; heat and stir until cheese melts.
Garnish with shredded cheese, if desired. Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Dissolve first 3 ingredients in large bowl and let stand until bubbles form.
Blend and add to yeast mixture the soy milk and cashew meal.
Mix in remaining ingredients except whole wheat flour.
Stir in flour.
Pour into "Pammed" 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch baking pan.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°. Bake for 45 to 60 minutes.
For Bundt pan, use 1 1/2 recipes.

title: green beans and tomatoes with mustard
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings.
Crumble bacon; set aside. Saute onion and green pepper in bacon drippings until tender. Stir in flour; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and mustard.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Stir in green beans; cook until thoroughly heated.
Transfer to serving bowl; sprinkle with crumbled bacon. Yields 6 servings.

title: 5 minute noodle dinner
directions: *Tuna can be substituted with your favorite meat.
Chicken, pork, hot dogs, beef tips.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Put flour in a bowl.
Melt butter in pan and add sugar. Blend in eggs and vanilla. Add flour mixture gradually. Spread into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and chips. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly the softened shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Blend in flour, baking powder and salt. Cover and chill 1 hour.
Roll dough 1/4-inch thick and cut.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 6 to 8 minutes at 400°.
Serves 3 dozen.

title: miss american pie
directions: Bake pie crust.
Pour blueberry pie filling in bottom of crust.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Beat cream cheese, adding powdered sugar until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread cheese mixture on top of blueberry pie filling.
Chill 30 minutes. Gently spread cherry pie filling on top.
Chill approximately 4 hours.

title: german christmas cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients and then all the flour to make a medium stiff dough.
Let stand overnight in a cold place or refrigerator.
In the morning shape into 6 or 8 balls and roll out ball in rectangular shape and cut diagonally with spatula or fork shaped cookies.
Roll cookie dough thin for crisp cookies and roll thicker for soft cookies.
Mix 1 egg in small dish with fork.
Dip fork in beaten egg and make tine marks across top of each cookie. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: marjorie kanatzar's barbecues
directions: Fry onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients, except meat, and simmer slowly for 15 minutes.
Add meat and turn on low for 1/2 hour.
I usually have to add a little water.
Makes wonderful sandwiches.
Serve on buns.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Put rolls spread out on an 11 x 17 1/2-inch sheet pan.
Bake as directed.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Hidden Valley Ranch dressing mix.
Spread over cooled rolls.
Put chopped vegetables over cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle grated cheese over vegetables. Refrigerate 12 hours or overnight.

title: creamy chicken hash
directions: Cube potatoes and chicken.
In skillet melt margarine; cook onions tender.
Stir in flour and salt.
Stir in half and half, stirring until thick.
Stir in potatoes and chicken.
Cover and cook until warm.

title: chicken breast delight
directions: Wash chicken breasts and let drain.
Cut dried beef into small pieces and layer bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Wrap each chicken breast in slice of bacon with ends tucked under bottom side . Do not salt chicken.
Place chicken on top of dried beef. Mix sour cream and soup together and pour on top of chicken breasts.
Prepare the night before and refrigerate overnight. Bake, covered, at 375° for 3 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine flour, salt, and soda in medium mixing bowl.
Set aside.
Cream together sugars and crisco.
Add eggs and beat well. Add flour mixture and all other ingredients.
Drop teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10-12 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix in order given eggs, evaporated milk, salt, pumpkin, sugar and pumpkin pie spice.
Put in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle with yellow cake mix over all.
Add chopped nutmeats and lastly drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until done.
Serve with Cool Whip, ice cream or plain.

title: banana wheat quick bread
directions: Slice bananas thinly.
Combine all ingredients in mixer bowl. Blend at low speed.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cedar creek marinated vegetables(appetizer)
directions: Cut off cauliflower buds and split to bite size.
Split carrots and celery into fourths, lengthwise, then cut pieces 2 inches long.
Add drained mushrooms, olives and garlic cloves. Sprinkle garlic powder over cut vegetables.
Add lemon juice, lemon halves and Italian dressing.
Stir and set in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Stir again and salt to taste.
Marinate for at least 2 more hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve in large bowl.
Use toothpicks to spear morsels.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening; add yeast, water and buttermilk.
Place
in covered bowl in refrigerator overnight. Bake
as needed.
On floured board roll 1/2 inch thick and cut with
a
biscuit
cutter.
Bake
at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes. Yields 3 to 5 dozen.

title: rabbit with red wine
directions: Assemble and prepare all ingredients. In 6-quart pot melt butter and brown rabbit.
Add onions and cook until translucent. Sprinkle flour over rabbit, stirring.
Add all seasonings; mix. Combine water, wine, lemon juice and rind.
Pour over rabbit. Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer covered for 1 hour.

title: shipwreck
directions: Slice raw potatoes and place in greased casserole.
Crumble hamburger over them (do not cook hamburger before).
Add half of the salt and pepper.
Slice onion and spread over hamburger meat. Spread kidney beans over onion.
Cover all with undiluted tomato soup and add remaining salt and pepper.
Bake for 1 hour and 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter and jelly cheesecake
directions: Combine oats, peanuts and margarine; press into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: sweet bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased and lightly floured pan.

title: hot brown
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan; add flour and stir well.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly until well blended.
Add all remaining ingredients; cook until slightly thickened.
Place ham on toasted bread, then add bacon, cheese sauce and top with tomato slices. Bake at 425° until bubbly.

title: aunt sue's strawberry fig surprise *
directions: Pour sugar over figs and refrigerate overnight.
Bring to boil and simmer for 20 minutes.
Slowly pour in Jell-O while stirring. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour in jars, seal.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in eggs, flour, buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until set.
Cool slightly before serving. Makes 8 servings.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat two minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 2 loaf pans or 1 tube pan, greased and floured.

title: camaron ranchera
directions: Boil onion and jalapeo in a little bit water.
Separately in cooking pan, bring shrimp, tomato juices, and seasonings to a boil.
Then mix all ingredients together.
Let come to a boil, then simmer on low heat for 20 - 25 min.

title: spicy potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes in 4 pieces lengthwise. Toss in bag of Shake 'N Bake.
Place on cookie sheet in oven at 400° for 1 hour.

title: zabaglione - italian cake(servings:  4)
directions: Mix with wire whisk in double boiler until sugar is dissolved. Cook in double boiler, stirring, until mixture thickens from sides to center.
Move to center to cook liquid.
Turn down heat to low and gently simmer.
Pour into long-stemmed glasses.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, pour water over oatmeal. Let stand for 10 minutes. Add sugars and butter, stirring until butter is melted. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt together. Add to batter; mix well. Stir in half of the chocolate chips. Pour into a greased 9 x 13 baking pan. Sprinkle walnuts and remaining chips on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.

title: poppy cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease baking pan.
Mix egg, milk, Bisquick and 1/2 cheese.
Spread in pan.
Top with rest of cheese, poppy seed and oleo.
Bake 25 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach; drain thoroughly (squeeze out water).
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Chill to blend flavors.

title: white chocolate cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese and 1/2 cup cold milk in a large bowl with a wire whisk until smooth.
Add remaining cold milk and pudding mixes.
Beat with a wire whisk for about a minute.
Stir in Cool Whip until smooth and well blended.
Spoon into crust. Refrigerate for about 4 hours or until set.
Garnish with white chocolate curls made from Baker's Chocolate, if desired.
Store leftover cheesecake in refrigerator.
Makes 8 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Put butter in casserole; briefly melt in a 350° oven to coat bottom of dish.
Mix corn, flour, sugar, salt and pepper; add beaten eggs and milk.
Mix together well and put in buttered casserole.

title: chef salad pizza
directions: Spread rolls on pizza pans. Bake as directed. Mix cream cheese, sour cream, milk and Ranch dressing. Spread on rolls. Top with ham, turkey, lettuce, peppers, olives, cheese and mushrooms.

title: easy apple or peach cobbler
directions: In a 1-quart shallow casserole, combine apples or peaches, sugar, 1 tablespoon baking mix and cinnamon.
In a medium bowl, mix remaining 2/3 cup baking mix with brown sugar.
Cut in I Can't Believe It's Not Butter until mixture is size of small peas.
Stir in milk until moistened; drop by spoonfuls onto fruit mixture. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted into crust comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage appetizers
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage; drain grease.
Add cheese and melt mixture together.
Spoon into small rye bread or white squares and place under a broiler for 1 minute.

title: crock-pot pot roast
directions: Coat pot roast with a little vegetable oil. Rub in salt, pepper and herbs. Put pot roast in bottom of crock-pot and place vegetables around it. Add the beef broth and cover the pot. Cook for 8 to 10 hours on
low.

title: crumb cake
directions: Put pie filling in bottom of cake pan.
Melt oleo and pour over dry cake mix; stir all that up good.
Then pour all that over pie filling.
Put nuts (pecans) on top if you want.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch dish or pan until light brown at 325°.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Place big bag of Tater Tots in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Spoon on top of Tater Tots. Put cheese on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham glaze dijon
directions: In small saucepan, heat pineapple, brown sugar and mustard to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Spoon 1/2 cup glaze over ham during the last 30 minutes of baking.
Heat remaining glaze mixture and serve with ham.

title: nannie's chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender and debone.
Melt butter and toss with dressing mix.
Put half the stuffing in a casserole dish. Top with chicken and mushroom soup and 2 cans of broth where chicken was cooked.
Add remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 50 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together.
Roll ball in pecans.

title: buckeyes
directions: Melt butter and pour into large bowl.
Add peanut butter.
Add sugar.
Mix well with hands.
Dough will be sticky.
(Use less peanut butter.)
Take a little dough to form about 1-inch balls. Put them on cookie sheet, covered with wax paper.
Refrigerate for about 30 minutes (until hard).
Melt chips in double boiler with just enough paraffin to make glossy.
Dip balls in chocolate half way.
Put back on wax paper.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: irish soda bread
directions: In bowl, sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar.
(If using seed, add now.)
Cut in shortening with pastry cutter or two knives.
Pour in buttermilk; add raisins.
Mix; batter will be very moist.
Turn out onto floured board and knead gently a few strokes.
Shape into round shape.
Cut loaf into quarters, about 1/4 way.
Brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with sugar; bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until light brown.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Beat softened cream cheese with sugar until fluffy.
Add peanut butter.
Beat well.
Gradually beat in milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into shell.
Freeze until firm.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain grease.
Add taco seasoning mix. Add tomatoes and sauce.
Let simmer for 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: creamy cabbage cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over medium head of shredded cabbage.
You may want to add finely shredded carrots, sliced, hard-boiled eggs and chopped tomatoes.

title: peanut butter fruit bars(for hiking, camping, picnics)
directions: Stir together brown sugar and honey in a large saucepan.
Bring mixture to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter until smooth.
Measure 1/3 cup of dried fruit bits.
Set aside.
Stir remaining fruit bits into honey mixture until well coated.
Spread mixture into a greased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking pan.
Press reserved fruit into top and cool.
Cut bars into individual bars and wrap each in plastic wrap.
Makes 24 bars.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Boil together the margarine, water and cocoa.
In a bowl, mix flour, sugar, eggs, salt and buttermilk mixture.
Add cocoa mixture and blend well.
Bake in an 18 x 12 x 1-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all together. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cream cheese loaf cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in flavorings; blend well.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan; bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Enjoy warm or cold.
Freezes well.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Fill churn with milk.
Pour in rest of ingredients.
Freeze according to ice cream churn directions.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Mix the above ingredients together except the coconut. Mix them well and then add the coconut.
Grease and flour a 10 inch pie pan. Pour mixture into pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. The crust forms as the pie bakes.

title: harvest hamburger casserole
directions: In a bowl, combine beef, onion, tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce and salt. Spoon into a greased 3-quart or larger casserole. Layer the potatoes, flour, corn, lima beans and pepper on top. Bake, covered, at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and continue baking, uncovered, for 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and add onions and salt.
Let stand about 1 hour. Drain thoroughly. Combine remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling and add to cucumber mixture.
Mix and heat gently to boiling, stirring often.
Place in sterilized jars and seal. Makes 7 pints.

title: hobo's lunch
directions: Brown ground chuck. Add onion and garlic powder.
Let simmer for a few minutes. Add potatoes and water. Cook until potatoes are tender. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: crock-pot french onion soup
directions: Peel onions and slice or chop; brown lightly in butter.
Pour onions in crock-pot.
Add water and bouillon cubes.
Mix and cover.
Cook on low 7 to 8 hours or on high 3 to 4 hours.
Put in serving bowls.
Add slice of toasted French bread.
Top with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Put in oven or microwave until cheese is melted.
Serve piping hot.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Mix
ingredients all together.	Drop cookies on greased sheet. Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: ham and scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine soup, milk and pepper in casserole dish.
Arrange a layer of potatoes, ham and soup sauce.
Dot top with butter. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°. Uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: pineapple carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; set aside.
Mix eggs, oil and sugar.
Stir in carrots, pineapple, vanilla and nuts.
Add dry ingredients slowly to carrot mixture, blending thoroughly.
Turn into a 10-inch tube pan (Bundt or angel food).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: sausage crescent rolls
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, sprayed generously with vegetable cooking spray, spread crescent rolls to cover the bottom of the pan. Keep the rolls touching. Sprinkle sausage and cheese evenly over the rolls. Combine eggs and milk, beating well. Pour mixture over sausage and cheese. Cover with aluminum foil so that rolls will cook thoroughly in the middle. Bake for 25 to 35 minutes or until set. Remove from oven and allow to stand for 5 minutes. Cut into squares and serve immediately. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine onions and squash.
Cover with water; cook 5 minutes and drain.
Combine soup, sour cream, carrots and fold in squash and onions.

title: slow cooker barbecue pot roast
directions: Brown meat in hot oil in skillet, then transfer to slow cooker.
Add sauce, green pepper and onion.
Cover and cook at high heat 4 to 5 hours or until tender.
Slice and serve with sauce.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: grandma's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, baking soda and salt.
In a large bowl, combine butter, sugars and vanilla.
Beat until creamy. Beat in eggs; gradually add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well; stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 8 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all together.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer at least 2 hours, but the longer, the better.

title: fried venison steaks
directions: Soak steaks in milk overnight.
Drain.
Mix flour and seasonings. Dredge steaks in flour mixture.
Heat oil in large pan and fry steaks until done.
Drain well.

title: spice pound cake
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Generously grease, then flour pan. Blend all ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350°.
Cake is done when toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: carefree casserole
directions: Measure cooked rice in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In a small frying pan, saute onion in butter.
Blend in soup and water.
Stir in chicken or tuna, peas, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Stir into rice in casserole.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cashew chicken casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine 5 minutes.
Add broth, soy sauce and soup.
Simmer for 2 minutes.
Add chicken and rice. Turn into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole; bake 15 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and sprinkle first with noodles, then cashews and bake an additional 2 minutes.

title: mom's fruit leather
directions: Place peeled and pitted peaches in blender and add honey to taste.
Blend until smooth.
Cover jelly roll pan with aluminum foil and then Saran Wrap (do not let hang over sides or it will burn).
Spread peach mixture 1/4-inch thick on tray.
Bake at lowest heat 24 hours.
Roll in Saran Wrap and store in jar with cover.
Will keep in cool room indefinitely.
Can be done with apples-cinnamon, apricots, etc.
Tear off piece and eat!

title: taco chicken
directions: Dip chicken in butter.
Then roll in corn chip crumbs.
Put on rack in pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti in 3 to 4-inch pieces. Cook as directed and rinse. Add other ingredients. Mix well and let set at least a day before serving.

title: crabbies
directions: Combine and mix thoroughly.
Spread on muffin halves.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze for at least 8 minutes.
Cut into eighths.
May freeze before baking.
Broil 5 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve immediately.

title: squash pie
directions: Beat eggs well. Mix everything and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until done. (Stick knife in center and if it comes out clean, remove from oven.)

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Place beans in 3 cups water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cook 2 minutes.
Do not drain; set aside for 1 hour.
Return beans to heat, adding water to cover if necessary.
Simmer for 1 hour or until beans are tender.
Drain and set aside.

title: apple candy
directions: Bring applesauce and sugar to boil. Boil for 15 minutes.
Stir to keep from scorching.
Add the jello.
Stir until dissolved. Add walnuts or almonds.
Pour in small 8 x 5 x 2-inch pan. Refrigerate overnight.
Cut and roll in powdered sugar and form. Let stand at room temperature for 12 hours.
Roll again in powdered sugar.
Store in airtight container.

title: heart healthy chili(from wes' heart diet)
directions: In large
saucepan,
brown ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Cook over low heat about 1 hour.	Stir occasionally.
Yields 6 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook corn according to package directions.
Add salt and milk. Make a thickening with flour and water and add to corn so it is consistency of medium gravy.
Saute onions, celery and pepper and stir them into corn with the beaten eggs.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until set.
When top is just set, sprinkle generously with buttered dry bread crumbs.
Return to oven 1 to 2 minutes.

title: southwestern style bean dip
directions: Heat all ingredients together in saucepan on medium-low heat, until cheese has melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: white sauce
directions: Melt fat over moderate heat.
Stir in flour and cook without browning until it is pale yellow.
Gradually stir in the liquid. To avoid lumps, use a whisk and cold liquid.
Boil after each addition of liquid.
When all liquid is added, cook sauce 10 minutes over low heat before adding seasoning.

title: sweet muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms of 6 muffin cups or line with cupcake liners.
Beat egg with fork in small bowl; stir in milk and oil.
Mix in dry ingredients until flour is moistened. Batter should be lumpy.
Fill the cups 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 muffins.

title: nina's corn casserole
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar with corn.
Add eggs, milk and butter.
Beat.
Pour into greased dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Doubles easily.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown meats; drain. Add onion and cook until tender. Add sugars, catsup, barbecue sauce, mustard, molasses and seasonings; mix well. Add beans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or can be cooked on low in crock-pot for approximately 3 hours. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: crustless apple pie
directions: Mix egg, sugar, nuts and apples.
Sift remaining ingredients together. Add to apple mixture.
Pour into a 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: butter dip rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Melt butter in 9 x 9-inch pan in oven; remove.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add milk and stir with a fork.

title: custard pie
directions: To sugar, add all ingredients together at high speed for 5 minutes.
Pour into two 9-inch pie shells.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except potato chips and 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Bake at 350°.
Top with remaining cheese and potato chips.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: gingerbread(over 150 years old)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add molasses and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately to cream mixture with buttermilk.
Beat well.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crunchy graham treats
directions: Combine cereal, raisins and nuts.
Melt chocolate morsels, peanut butter and margarine, in a medium saucepan, over low heat, stirring frequently.
Turn off heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour melted mixture over cereal mixture.
Stir until well coated.

title: boiled oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first four items in medium saucepan on medium-high.
Stir constantly.
When mixture comes to a rolling boil, cook for 2 1/2 minutes.
Then add all other ingredients (vanilla last).

title: chicken casserole with stuffing
directions: Do not salt chicken.
Cook chicken in boiler, using enough water to have 2 or more cups chicken broth.
Mix all ingredients, except chicken, together.
Put in greased and floured pan; place chicken in center.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana spice loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease with spray 9 1/4 x 5 1/4 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan.
In large bowl combine flour, whole wheat flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Melt margarine in a small saucepan.
Pour into bowl and whisk together with bananas, buttermilk, egg and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture and stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into pan.
Bake for 50 minutes.
Place pan on a rack and cool for 10 minutes.
Remove loaf from pan.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add alternately with oil and zucchini.
Add vanilla, nuts and pineapple.
Bake in greased bread pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix bread crumbs, ground chuck, eggs, tomato juice, onion, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Roll into balls.
Brown in oil and place on cookie sheet.
Freeze.
Then wrap in foil and keep frozen until ready to use.

title: cool whip dessert
directions: Stir Cool Whip and instant pudding (as it comes from the package), drained pineapple, cottage cheese and nuts. Cool. Serve.
Delicious.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 greased loaf pans and bake at 325° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool for 10 minutes.

title: tuna fish salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add tuna, lemon juice, a little salt, hard-boiled eggs, celery, mayonnaise and as many stuffed olives as you like.
Put in 8-inch square pan or fish mold.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Add milk, cream and melted butter. Pour into pastry-lined pie plate.
Bake in hot oven for 45 minutes.
Cool and serve with whipped cream.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: creme brulee
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Scald the cream and milk with the vanilla bean; infuse for 10 minutes. Beat egg yolks with 2 teaspoons sugar until slightly thickened. Stir in hot cream and milk mixture. (If you do not use a vanilla bean, add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract.) Strain mixture into 6 (4-ounce) ramekins. Set ramekins in a cold water bath and bake until skin forms (approximately 15 to 18 minutes). The custard underneath will remain liquid. Chill for 4 hours.

title: chili bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a skillet, mix chili and corn.
Cook to boiling.
Mix cornbread with egg and milk (make thinner than regular cornbread).
Spoon over chili and corn.
Bake until brown; don't overcook.
If 1 can of chili is used, only use 1/2 package of cornbread mix.

title: caramels
directions: Cook slowly to 248° or a hard ball forms in cold water when a drop is added.
Pour caramel mixture into well-greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Let cool until set. Remove from pan and cut into squares. Wrap pieces in wax paper.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Combine sugar, milk, cocoa and oleo.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Add rest of ingredients and mix.
Drop by spoon onto greased wax paper.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix the German chocolate cake mix with the evaporated milk and butter.
Pour 1/2 of this batter into a 13 x 9-inch lightly greased cake pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 5 to 6 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs until light; add milk.
Mix flour with sugar; add to	milk
and
egg mixture.
Stir in coconut and vanilla. Pour into 2 unbaked 9-inch crusts.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan fritters
directions: Melt caramels in cream; stir in pecans.
Drop in small patties on wax paper.
Let set until firm.
Melt candy bar with paraffin wax.
Dip patties in melted chocolate.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer in pan or dump. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water, then feed with 1 cup warm water, sugar and potato flakes.
Let mixture stand all day, loosely covered, then refrigerate 2 to 5 days.
Take it out, feed it again with 1 cup warm water, 3/4 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons potato flakes.
Again, let it set out all day or overnight, 8 to 12 hours, loosely covered.
Now you are ready to pour off 1 cup Starter to make bread.
Store the rest in the refrigerator, feeding every 3 to 5 days.

title: crunchy apple pie
directions: Put chopped apples in a large bowl.
Add sugar, flour, egg yolk, vanilla, lemon juice and pecans.
Mix until well until blended.
Add egg white stir, pour mixture into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until apples are tender and brown.
Take from oven and let cool before serving.

title: blackberry salad
directions: Mix jello with water (reserve 1/4 cup aside); do not add sugar.
Add other ingredients and chill.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt, shortening and 2 cups flour.
Blend well.
Add flour to make a soft dough. Knead well.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Make into rolls. Place in greased pans and let rise until doubled again.
Bake at 400° for 20-25 minutes.
Makes 24 to 30 rolls.

title: mint syrup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a sauce pan and stir well.
Bring to a boil and cook 10 minutes or until mixture is reduced to 2 1/4 cups.
Remove from heat, stir and strain.
Refrigerate.
May be served over fresh fruit or in tea.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust. Chill several hours.
(You can serve it with fruit on top if you want.)

title: pistachio marble cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water, oil and extract in large mixer bowl.
Blend, then beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Measure 1 1/2 cups batter; stir in chocolate syrup.
Spoon batters alternately into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Zigzag spatula through batter to marbleize. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pan and finish cooling on rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar if desired.

title: pecan crunch pie
directions: Beat eggs and baking powder.
Add sugar very slowly.
Beat until very stiff.
Crush graham crackers.
Add them (by folding) to egg mixture.
Add vanilla; spread in heavily buttered pie pan.

title: crab mold
directions: Lightly toast baguette slices in the oven.
Lay a wide strip of roasted red bell pepper on each slice and place a square of sliced provolone cheese on the pepper.
Fold the pepper over the cheese and drizzle with Tomato-Basil sauce.
Place under the broiler until cheese is bubbly (but watch them carefully and don't let them burn).

title: pumpkin cheese torte
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Put pecans and sugar into processor and process until finely chopped.
Add cookies or crumbs and melted butter; blend well to create mixture for crust.
Press into bottom and up approximately 1-inch of 10-inch spring mold pan to form crust.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: golden chicken
directions: In skillet brown chicken in oil, pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover, cook over low heat for 45 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into a ball.
Roll ball in chopped nuts.

title: next best thing to robert redford
directions: Combine flour, butter and nuts.
Press into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: sally rand muffins
directions: Beat together butter, sugar and egg.
Sift together the flour and baking powder.
Add the flour mixture alternately with milk to the butter mixture.
Bake in greased muffin pans at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: yogurt covered nuts
directions: Use a 2-quart pan.
Boil sugar, cream and butter.
Cook to 238° (soft ball). Remove from heat and add vanilla and cinnamon. Stir until mixture begins to thicken.
Add nuts and stir until well coated.
Turn onto wax paper or foil or greased cookie sheet.
Separate and cool.

title: sweet potato roll
directions: Mix potatoes, eggs, sugar and flour.
Pour on prepared cookie sheet (floured and greased).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: janet's apple dip
directions: Stir cream cheese and brown sugar until smooth. Add chopped nuts and mix until blended. Serve with sliced apples (or pears).

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in a large heavy sauce pan. Heat to boiling.
Stir constantly about 5 minutes over medium heat until mixture reaches softball stage - 238°.
Remove from heat. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir vigorously until well blended. Pour into greased 13x9x2-inch pan.
Cool.
Makes about 3 pounds fudge.

title: jolene's popcorn cake
directions: Grease pan with unmelted margarine.
Mix popcorn, candy and nuts.
In saucepan, mix oil, melted margarine and marshmallows. Cook over low heat until marshmallows are melted.
Pour over popcorn mixture; mix well.
Press into pan.
Cover and chill.
Cut into squares when ready to serve.

title: monkey bread
directions: Shake biscuits in a sack with 3/4 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Drop loosely in a greased Bundt pan.
Melt 1 stick oleo; mix in 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Mix flours, cornmeal, raisins, baking soda and salt.
Stir in buttermilk, molasses and oil until smooth.
Spoon into 3 greased 1-pound coffee cans.
Cover with greased lid or foil with string. Place on rack in large kettle.
Add boiling water to come halfway up sides of molds, cover and simmer for 3 hours.
Remove from kettle and cool on rack for 10 minutes.
Invert and serve warm. Each loaf makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: boneless buffalo wings
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 3 ingredients, set aside.
In another bowl whisk together egg and milk.
Slice chicken into 12 strips.
Dip chicken pieces into the egg mixture, then into the flour mixture.
Repeat dipping process, so that chicken pieces are well coated.
Place chicken pieces on a plate and chill for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a deep fryer or deep frying pan, heat oil. Add chicken strips and cook until browned on all sides.
Drain chicken on paper towels.
Combine hot sauce and margarine. Combine the chicken pieces and the hot sauce mixture in a large container with a lid.
Shake gently to coat each piece of chicken with sauce.
Serve chicken wings with celery and dressing.

title: spiced crackers
directions: Mix corn oil and spices.
Pour mixture over crackers and mix well.
Seal for 4 to 5 hours or overnight.
Great for party snack.

title: doughnuts
directions: Mix warm water, yeast and sugar; let set 15 minutes.
Add butter or Crisco, eggs, salt and flours.
Let rise.
Roll and cut. Let rise again and fry.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Heat tomatoes and butter in saucepan over moderate heat until butter melts.
Mix in crumbs, sugar, salt and pepper.
Spoon into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle allspice over top; bake, uncovered, at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes, until mixture is "set" in middle and lightly browned.

title: apple cinnamon dumplings
directions: Roll biscuits out flat. Lay apple wedge on biscuit. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Fold over apple wedge and place in baking dish. Heat margarine, Sprite and sugar. Pour liquid mixture over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: tonya's cheesy potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into very small pieces.
Cook in boiling water for 4 minutes or until tender.
Drain and let cool.
Combine 1/4 cup butter, onion, salt, pepper, sour cream, soup and cheese in a large bowl.
Gently stir in potatoes.
Spoon into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cakes
directions: Grease cookie sheets.
In a small pan bring raisins and water to boil.
Drain, reserving 1/4 cup liquid; set aside.
In a large bowl beat brown sugar, 1/2 cup shortening and margarine until fluffy.
Add eggs and egg yolk; beat well.
In another bowl combine flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves; blend well.
Add this flour mixture and reserved liquid to sugar mixture; mix well. Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls 3 inches apart onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 2 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Place in a buttered baking dish (9 x 13-inches).
If apples are dry, add 1/4 cup water.
Cut together the sugar, Bisquick, margarine and cinnamon, using a pastry blender or a fork, until mixture is crumbly.
Then spread evenly over the apples and press mixture down, to pack closely over apples.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm, topped with whipped cream or lemon sauce.

title: salmon ring
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Prepare biscuit dough and roll in oblong shape about 1/4-inch thick and spread on salmon and seal edges.
Place on greased angel cake tin; join ends of salmon roll to make circle.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Heat remaining tin of soup, mixed with 1/4 cup milk, and serve over ring.

title: cheesecake tart
directions: Lightly oil a 9-inch tart pan.
In a blender, process cookies and butter until the mixture is crumbly.
Press mixture onto bottom and sides of a tart pan, then refrigerate.
Preheat oven to 325°.

title: sorrells' chili
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix together with rest of ingredients in an 8-quart boiler.
Cook on medium until done.
Add water to thin, if needed.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown onion, garlic and ground beef in oil.
Stir in salt, pepper, herbs, celery, m.s.g. and gravy.
Cook over low heat about 15 to 30 minutes.
Thicken with 2 tablespoons cornstarch or flour in small amount of water.
Cook lasagna according to package directions.
Spread small amount of gravy on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place layer of 1/2 cooked noodles, 1/2 grated Mozzarella cheese, all of cottage cheese and 1/2 of Parmesan cheese.
Cover with 1/2 remaining gravy, rest of lasagna noodles and Mozzarella cheese.
Top with rest of gravy and grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: In mixing bowl, cream shortening and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Combine 2 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with the milk.
Spread into greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Toss blueberries with lemon juice. Sprinkle over batter.
In small bowl combine cinnamon, remaining sugar and flour and cut in butter until mixture is size of peas. Sprinkle over blueberries.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: zucchini "spiced apple" pickles
directions: Soak zucchini in cold water and lime overnight.
The next morning, drain and rinse thoroughly in clear, cold water.
In large kettle, bring vinegar and sugar to a boil.
Add the zucchini, cinnamon, cloves and food coloring.
Boil until the zucchini is clear (about 50 minutes).
Pack in sterilized jars. Seal and keep jars in hot water for 30 minutes.

title: meal in a pan
directions: Cut and fry bacon; when halfway cooked, add potatoes.
Cover, stirring often, until potatoes are done.
Put bread in eggs to soak while potatoes cook.
Then add to pan until eggs are done. Bacon, potatoes, eggs and bread in a pan.

title: beef stroganoff casserole
directions: Separate rolls while cold; let warm to room temperature, then press them into the bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown beef; add onion and simmer until tender.
Add paprika, salt and pepper.
Let sour cream warm to room temperature.
Add sour cream and mushrooms to beef mixture; mix well.
Spread into pan.
Place slices of cheese on top of mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cherry pecan jello
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Pour this over cherry jello.
Mix remaining ingredients together, then add to jello mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken pie
directions: Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well. Sift dry ingredients and alternate with bananas to shortening mixture.
Add nuts.

title: hearty hamburg soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt margarine.
Add onion, carrot and green pepper.
Cook until onion is tender (not brown).
Add beef; cook until meat is crumbly.
Stir in tomato juice.
Add potatoes and seasonings.
Cook over low heat until vegetables are tender (25 to 30 minutes).
Combine flour with 1 cup milk (add milk to flour a little at a time and stir until free of lumps).
Stir into soup mixture.
Add rest of milk and heat; stir frequently.
Do not let boil.

title: grandma's famous gingerbread
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine buttermilk and soda; add to sugar mixture, mixing well.
Sift flour and ginger together.
Add flour mixture to sugar mixture, mixing well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
If desired, serve
gingerbread dusted with powdered sugar or topped with a dollop of whipped cream.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples into 9 x 11-inch baking dish which has been greased.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top of apples to taste.
Melt butter into small saucepan.
Add sugar.
Remove from heat.
Cut slices of bread into 4 long rectangles.
Cover the apples with bread pieces.
Pour on sugar/butter mixture.
Bake in 350° oven until brown on top (20 to 25 minutes).

title: thirty minute lasagna(yields 8 servings.)
directions: Brown ground beef and drain excess fat; boil noodles rinse and drain; in a bowl combine ground beef, noodles, and spaghetti sauce. Spray 13x9 pan with non-stick product.
Put a layer of noodle mixture in pan and top with 1/2 of mozzarella cheese, repeat noodle layer and top with other 1/2 of cheese.
Bake at 375° for approx 30 minutes or until cheese on top is golden brown. LET STAND FOR 10 MINS AND SERVE.

title: sweet and sour cabbage(keeps well for days)
directions: Grate or shred and mix together the first 4 ingredients.
In a medium saucepan, bring to a boil the remaining ingredients.
Mix sauce over shredded mixture and refrigerate for at least 4 hours before serving.
Will keep for several days in the refrigerator.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice.
Melt butter in skillet.
Saute onion in butter.
Add Cheez Whiz and soup.
Cook until creamy.
Add rice and broccoli.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake in oven on 350° until bubbly, about 15 minutes.

title: caramel custard pie
directions: Add enough water to evaporated milk to make 2 cups. Beat in eggs. Combine brown sugar and flour. Cut in margarine until mixture is like coarse crumbs. Add milk mixture to brown sugar mixture. Beat until well blended.
Pour into pastry shell. Bake at 400° until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: tom's chicken
directions: Mix mushrooms, peppers and sauce over medium-low heat.
Place chicken in deep dish and pour warm sauce over chicken.
Cook at 325° for one hour or until fully cooked.

title: the best chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Sift together flour, cornstarch and salt.
In bowl pour boiling water over sugar.
Add chocolate mix and buttermilk which has had soda added to it.
Add flour, eggs and vanilla. Stir just until blended and pour quickly (the batter will look soupy).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: green bean bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the onion rings.
Spread in casserole dish.
Lay onion rings on top and bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine eggs, oil and sugars.
Add vanilla, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and salt.
Mix well.
Add lemon juice.
Mix.
Add flour and mix.
Add zucchini, nuts and raisins.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Grease and sugar two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Pour batter evenly into both pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: doughnut balls
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add vanilla and milk.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons into deep fat and fry.

title: bean and bacon roast
directions: Coat roast with
flour	and
seasonings.
Brown in oil. Combine soup, water and gravy base and pour over roast.
Cover and simmer 1 hour and
45 minutes, stirring soup mix occasionally. Add carrots, onion	and
pepper.
Bake
another 45 minutes.

title: frozen fudge popsicles
directions: Mix well and freeze like popsicles.

title: dearborn inn fruitcake
directions: Lightly grease a 10-inch tube pan.
Line bottom and sides with heavy brown paper.
In a large bowl, combine raisins, currants, dates, candied peel, nuts, candied cherries, apples and orange. Sift 1/4 cup flour over mixture.
Mix well.
Sift remaining flour with baking powder and spices.
Preheat oven to 275°.
Beat butter with brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, then molasses.
With wooden spoon, stir fruit-nut mix into egg mix.
Add flour mixture, combining well.
Turn into prepared pan. Press batter with spatula to spread evenly.
Bake 2 1/2 hours or until cakes tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Remove from pan.
Peel off paper.
Wrap in foil; store in refrigerator or airtight tin at least 2 weeks. Makes one 6 pound cake.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In a large Dutch oven, brown ground beef, stirring slightly to break up large pieces. Drain off excess fat.

Add water, undrained tomatoes, onions, carrots, celery, barley, catsup, bouillon, salt, basil and bay leaf. Bring to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Remove bay leaf.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: oyster stuffing
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add onion and celery.
Cook some; then add oysters and rest of ingredients, except bread cubes or crumbs. Cook about 15 minutes.
Add to bread.
Mix well.
Use as stuffing for turkey.
Makes about 10 cups.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Saute ground beef and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until onion is soft and mix is thickened.
Put in a prebaked pie shell.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until heated through and potatoes are lightly brown.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cook until thick and pour over fruit and refrigerate.

title: quaker's best oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugar until creamy. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda, salt and spices. Mix well.
Stir in oats.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add flour, gradually beating well after each addition.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Shape into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm from oven.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook squash; drain.
Cook onion and celery until celery is tender.
Mix zucchini, onion, celery, tomatoes, cheese and salt. Add cream of chicken soup.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Put four slices of cheese on top. Return to oven long enough for cheese to melt.

title: applesauce raisin muffins
directions: Beat together egg, oil and applesauce.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder and spices; beat well.
Stir in raisins. Spoon batter into oiled and floured muffin wells.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until firm to touch and browned. Delicious topped with cream cheese.

title: *rich lemon filling
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in the top of a double boiler. Add lemon juice, water and egg.
Place over rapidly boiling water and cook for 10 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly. Add butter and lemon rind; cool.
Use as a filling between cake layers or in a jelly roll.
Sprinkle top with confectioners sugar.

title: best ever spaghetti
directions: Brown meat. Add garlic, onion, tomato paste, tomato sauce and water.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Cook spaghetti separately. Combine and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook and drain meat; add onion and brown.
Add tomato sauce, soup, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Layer peas, cooked spaghetti and cheese slices. Add crumbled crackers to melted oleo and spread on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: rhubarb custard pie(9-inch pie)
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk.
Mix sugar, flour and rhubarb. Pour into pie crust and dot with butter.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 400°.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix well and pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 300°.

title: upside-down date pudding
directions: Mix.
Cool slightly and pour over batter in pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: impossible custard pie
directions: Put in blender and blend for 3 minutes.
Let sit for 5 minutes.
Pour into greased pie plate.
Bake 40 minutes at 400°.

title: fresh broccoli and bacon salad
directions: Cut broccoli into small flowerets and wash thoroughly.
Combine broccoli, onion, and next 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine mayonnaise and remaining ingredients.
Add to the broccoli mixture, stirring until well coated.
Cover and chill.
Yields 5 cups.

title: butternut squash pie
directions: Cook squash until tender and water evaporates.
Measure out 2 cups.
Mix all ingredients and pour into two unbaked pie shells. Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes.

title: spring ham bake
directions: Combine in 1 1/2-quart or 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, except corn flakes.
Mix corn flakes with butter and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine first three ingredients and boil ten minutes.
Cool and add vinegar.
Mix remaining ingredients and cover with vinegar mixture.
Cover tightly and refrigerate.

title: citrus salad
directions: Save juice from fruit.

title: chippewa bannock
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients, then mix in the bacon drippings and water.
Heat the oil in a large, heavy skillet until a drop of water sizzles.
Drop the batter from teaspoon, flatten into cakes and cook 3 to 5 minutes on a side or until well browned.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mom's lemon custard cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Reserve 1 cup of prepared batter.
Bake 2 layers in prepared pans.
With reserved batter, add sugar, milk and rind and juice.
