Cook over very low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add milk if custard is too thick.
Spread between layers.

title: for two pain perdu
directions: Beat egg.
Add salt, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Pour into shallow dish and dip bread into mixture letting the bread absorb as much egg mixture as possible.
Arrange slices in greased pan and place in hot oven (400°) until dry and brown.
Serve with butter and honey.

title: mini meatballs
directions: Mix and brown meatballs in 1 tablespoon vegetable oil; simmer 10 minutes and drain fat.

title: chocolate cake with sprinkles
directions: You get all the dough from the box and pour it into a bowl. You get 2 eggs.
You get some milk that goes to the top of one glass.
Then you mix it and pour it into a round kind of pan. Then you put in the oven at 30°.
Two hours are good.
When it comes out, you put on sprinkles and 2 scoops of whipped cream (like a sand castle).
Then you put in about 5 candles.
Then you eat!

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit. Save 1 cup pineapple juice. Mix pineapple juice with the instant pudding. Pour over fruit. Chill.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Whip eggs until thoroughly blended; cut bread into cubes (can also cut off crust).
Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, bread and pineapple.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: veal parmigiana
directions: Heat 1 teaspoon oil in small nonstick skillet over medium heat. Add onion and garlic and saute for 3 to 4 minutes, or until crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes, salt, sugar, nutmeg and pepper.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, or until saucy and thickened, stirring frequently.
Stir in basil and 1 1/2 teaspoons Parmesan cheese.
Cover and remove from heat; reserve.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix all except chicken and pour into an 8 x 10-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange raw chicken pieces on rice mixture.
Sprinkle package of onion soup mix over chicken.
Cover with aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix the flour, butter and 1 cup of nuts with a fork and press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Let cool.

title: onion casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Parboil onions 10 minutes; drain.
Put half the onions into an 8 x 8-inch shallow baking dish coated with non-stick vegetable cooking spray.
Layer with half the bread and half Cheddar cheese.
Repeat with the remaining onions, bread and Cheddar cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper in a bowl. Pour mixture over the top layer.
Sprinkle with cayenne pepper and dot with butter or margarine.
Place casserole baking dish into a larger baking dish; add hot water to the outer dish halfway up the side of the casserole dish (like making a custard).
Bake for 40 minutes.
Serves 4. Great dish to make ahead.
Rewarm in oven or microwave.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Mix all ingredients and form into a loaf.
Place in ungreased 9 x 13 pan.
Add desired amount of catsup on top. Bake uncovered for 1 hour.

title: chili
directions: Cover beans with water and soak overnight.
Drain water and cover with fresh water to an inch or so over beans.
Add tomatoes, onion and garlic.
Bring to boil, turn to medium-low heat.
Cook until beans are almost done (adding water if needed).
Add rest of spices.
Brown meat, drain and add to beans.
Add tomato sauce and simmer for 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: low-fat biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Pour in oil and milk and mix together.
These can be either rolled out and cut or they may be dropped by spoonfuls onto a cookie sheet and baked at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bubbly and brown.

title: bacon roll ups
directions: Cut bacon strips in half.
Spread soup on bread (like spreading mayonnaise).
Roll up corner to corner.
Wrap with a piece of bacon.
Secure with a toothpick.
Bake on cookie sheet at 325° for 1 hour.

title: drunken pork roast
directions: Place roast in preheated oven at 350°.
Pour about half the 7 and 7 drink over all.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Roast 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Pat brown sugar over the entire roast.
Place orange slices over roast and secure with toothpick. Pour remainder of 7 and 7 over roast.
Return to oven and continue to bake until desired doneness, basting every 15 to 20 minutes. Makes absolutely wonderful gravy.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cinnamon toast
directions: Cut crusts from bread.
Toast until golden, spread with cinnamon and granulated sugar.
Kids Love it.

title: holiday dessert cake
directions: Beat together powdered sugar, milk and cream cheese.
Beat Dream Whip, milk and vanilla, then fold into first mixture.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, alternate layers of cake and mixture.
Top with can of pie filling.
Refrigerate until serving.
Best made day before use.

title: cherry swizzle
directions: Beat ice cream into cherry drink in a medium bowl; divide evenly into 8 tall glasses.
Pour 1/4 cup cola into each.

title: cheese straws
directions: Bring cheese and oleo to room temperature.
Grate cheese and mix with Parkay in a mixer bowl, using medium speed of mixer. Cream well.

title: strawberry icebox pie
directions: Mix jello, cornstarch, sugar and boiling water together until thick and clear.
Fill bottom of baked pie shell with sliced strawberries and pour mixture over them; chill.
Top with whipped cream.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Have chicken cooked, deboned and chopped.
Dice potatoes; cover with water.
Boil 3 to 4 minutes (potatoes should be firm).
Drain.
Add other ingredients and simmer until warm.
Pour into pie crust.
Place second crust on top.
Press edges together.
With fork, place holes in top crust to let steam escape.
Cook 30 minutes or until golden brown.
If edges brown too soon, cover (just edges) with foil.
For best results, place on cookie sheet.

title: white fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Pare and dice apple.
Peel and slice bananas.
Mix fruit in bowl with marshmallows, coconut and walnut pieces.

title: honey chicken
directions: Place
chicken, skin side up, in a large shallow baking pan in	a
single layer.
Sprinkle Accent, salt and pepper on chicken. Let
stand 10 minutes. Stir together corn oil, honey and
soy sauce. Drizzle on chicken. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven about 1
hour
or
until fork can be inserted with ease. Baste frequently.
Makes 4 servings. Serve with cooked rice.

title: broccoli casserole(six servings)
directions: Boil broccoli 5 minutes and drain.
Mix other ingredients and combine with broccoli.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour into buttered dish and dot with butter.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and golden brown.
Can be made the day before serving.

title: pacific pot roast(crock-pot recipe)
directions: Rub roast with 1 tablespoon oil and minced garlic.
Put in glass bowl, add sherry, ginger, pepper and onions.
Chill overnight.
Remove meat, brown in 2 tablespoons oil in frying pan. Put in crock-pot with 1/2 cup marinade, cook on low 7 to 8 hours. Add 1/2 cup more marinade to saucepan and cook juice.
Serve with meat.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: biscuit stuffin' atop chops
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-9inch baking pan.
Brown chops; drain.
Place chops in prepared pan.
Set aside.
In medium mixing bowl, combine soup, celery, onion, seasonings and egg.
Mix well.
Separate biscuit dough into 10 biscuits.
Cut each biscuit into 8 to 10 pieces.
Stir into soup mixture.
Spoon over chops.
Bake in 350° oven 55 to 65 minutes until topping is golden brown.

title: white christmas drinks
directions: Grate rind and juice of lemons.
Mix with sugar and cream. Add 3 tablespoons of mixture to glass.
Add ice cubes and 1 shot of gin or rum.
Fill with Bubble-Up or 7-Up.
Makes 10 drinks.

title: reception salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: dot's pound cake
directions: *Use large eggs; one egg equals 1/4 cup.

title: tuna dip
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Add drained tuna and sauces to taste.
Enjoy.

title: godfather meat loaf
directions: In 2-quart batter bowl, combine ground beef, eggs, Ro-Tel chillies and tomatoes, bread crumbs, garlic, salt and pepper.
On large piece of wax paper, flatten meat mixture into rectangle. Arrange ham on top of meat, leaving 1-inch margin around edge. Place slices of cheese over ham slices.
Carefully roll up meat, using wax paper to lift.
Seal edges.
Place roll, seam side down, in microwave ring mold or on microwave roasting rack.
Microwave on 70% power for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Place meat loaf on microwave-safe serving platter.
Pour Ragu sauce over top. Microwave on 80% power for 1 to 2 minutes or until hot.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add sugar and pineapple. Chill until beginning to set.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a glass dish and refrigerate.
Will keep good for several days.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli.
Arrange in greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over all. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: jim's olive meat loaf
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine eggs, bread crumbs and spaghetti sauce.
Add ground beef; mix well.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut cheese into desired size (4 pieces). Wrap ham around each piece of cheese.
Stuff chicken breasts with ham and cheese.
Fasten together with a toothpick.
Mix together egg and milk in small bowl.
Dip chicken breasts in egg and milk and then in bread crumbs (seasoned with salt and pepper).
Place chicken breasts in a pan and bake for 30 minutes (or until lightly browned).
Remove.
Place in casserole dish.
Saute sliced mushrooms in margarine.
Add soup with water and green beans to mushrooms.
Heat.
Pour over chicken.
Place casserole in oven 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with rice, mashed potatoes or noodles. Serves 4.

title: butter shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill in refrigerator.
Serve decorated with parsley.

title: hamburger potato dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Place potatoes in a casserole dish and add hamburger with onions, mushroom soup, water and salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.
Stir occasionally.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, Milnot and margarine 5 minutes on medium heat (or until soft ball).
Add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Beat until soft and creamy.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Crumble yeast cake in bowl; add salt, sugar and water, also well beaten egg.
Add 1/2 cup flour and beat well.
Add melted margarine, then stir in rest of flour.
Roll and put in pan.
Let rise only once.
Put in refrigerator in airtight container.
Will need to roll this out at least 2 hours before baking.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fumi salad
directions: Brown almonds and sesame seed.
Mix cabbage and onions in bowl.
At last minute, add almonds, sesame seed and crushed uncooked Ramen (do not use seasoning packet!).
Mix dressing and pour over salad just before serving.

title: peachy double cooked chicken
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
In bag, combine flour, salt and pepper. Shake chicken in mixture.
Brown chicken and place in casserole dish.
Combine orange juice, vinegar, peach juice and honey.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour 15 minutes. Baste often.
Place 2 to 3 cloves per peach halve.
Place around or on chicken.
Bake uncovered 15 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Rinse sauerkraut with cold water; drain well.
Combine sauerkraut with green pepper, onion and celery in a medium bowl. Combine oil, water, vinegar and sugar in a small bowl.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over sauerkraut mixture.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with apple, popcorn or your favorite snack.

title: zucchini-raisin cookies
directions: In mixing bowl cream margarine and sugar until light.
Add egg and beat well.
Add zucchini and blend in.
Set aside.

title: best chocolate fudge
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan over medium heat, melt sugar, milk, chocolate, corn syrup and salt to boiling.
Stir frequently. Add marshmallows.

Carefully sit candy thermometer in place and cook without stirring until temperature reaches 238° or soft ball stage (when a small amount of mixture dropped into a bowl of very cold water forms a ball that flattens on removal from water), about 10 minutes.
Remove saucepan from heat.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake in 450°
oven	for
10 minutes.
Lower heat to 350°.
Bake 35 minutes or until done when tested.	Good!

title: pork barbecue
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients.
Heat to boil over high heat; reduce to low.
Cover; simmer 3 hours or until pork is very tender.
Stir often.
Skim off fat.
Using whisk, stir until meat is shredded.
Serve on rolls or buns.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix and let stand before serving with vegetables (raw cauliflower, celery, peppers, carrots, broccoli, etc.).

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and margarine about 10 minutes.
Drain, mash, then add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: cheese grits
directions: Add finely chopped onion and egg to mash potatoes.
If they are a little too runny, add a bit of flour to them.
Also, add salt and pepper.
Make round patties.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: barley and wild rice pilaf
directions: Heat 2 teaspoons olive oil; add onion and saute until done. Add barley, rice and 2 garlic cloves and stir 1 minute.
Add 4 cups water and salt; bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook until grain is tender and liquid absorbed, about 1 hour.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and vanilla together. Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix first six ingredients; add corn bread mix last.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 20 to 25 minutes in 400° oven.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar in large mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder and cocoa together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool in pan for several minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Spread frosting over cake.
May omit frosting if preferred. Yield:
16 servings.

title: 5 layer dessert
directions: Mix and press into greased dish.
Bake at 325° until brown; cool.
Mix cream cheese (room temperature), powdered sugar and Cool Whip and spread on crust.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer in casserole dish.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs and grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: coke salad
directions: Heat cherry juice to boiling point.
Pour over Jell-O.
Stir. Crumble cream cheese and add to mixture.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cool.

title: roasted pepper and sourdough brunch casserole(makes 8 servings; carb count: 12 grams)
directions: Spray 11 x 7-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Place bread cubes in dish. Arrange roasted peppers evenly over bread cubes. Sprinkle Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheeses over peppers.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread apples in ungreased 8-inch pan. Mix other ingredients with a fork, then sprinkle over apples. Bake about 30 minutes or until topping is brown and apples are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spicy ketchup
directions: May be used as chip dip, meatball sauce, steak sauce, etc.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate 12 hours before serving.

title: confetti candy
directions: Melt almond bark and pour over mixture.
Spread out on wax paper.
Leave 2 to 3 hours.
Break up and store in airtight cans or bags.

title: spaghetti with raw sauce
directions: Place tomatoes one by one into boiling water for 1 minute. Plunge immediately in cold water and peel.
Cut in half horizontally and remove seeds.
Chop remaining tomatoes coarsely and combine in bowl with other ingredients, except spaghetti.
Let stand for 1 hour.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Oil bottom of casserole dish lightly.
Put a thin layer of spaghetti sauce, 1/2 of zucchini mixture and sprinkle with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat.
End with layer of spaghetti sauce, then Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: golden french dressing
directions: Measure all ingredients into bottle or jar.
Cover lightly and shake well.
Chill. Shake well before serving.
Makes 2 cups.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Cut butter into small pieces, mix with corn bread and bread crumbs.
Melt fat, add celery and onions.
Cook 5 minutes; add to crumb mixture.
Add green pepper and seasonings, mix thoroughly. Add well beaten eggs; sprinkle water over surface, stirring lightly until dressing is of desired moistness.
Stuff lightly into neck region and body cavity of the bird.
This recipe will yield enough stuffing for a 12 pound turkey.
Cover breast with foil until 1 hour before roasting ends.

title: sunday skillet supper
directions: Cook beef and onion in a large skillet until lightly browned. Add salt, water and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: baked chicken with white wine
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Salt and pepper inside and outside and sprinkle with fine herbs.
Cut potatoes (scrubbed and unpeeled) into large pieces.
Coarsely chop onion.
Place chicken, back side down, into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Arrange potato and onion around bird and sprinkle with salt, pepper and fines herbes. Drizzle lightly with olive oil.
Bake for 40 minutes at 400°.
Turn bird over (use large wooden spoon in cavity and flip).
Pour white wine over all (about 2 cups) and bake 40 to 45 minutes, basting now and then.

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric blender and process until smooth.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Yields 1 1/4 cups or about the same as a 14 ounce can.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix and pour into a cake pan.
Freeze or eat without freezing.

title: ridiculously easy dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9-inch round cake pan with Pam or Baker's Joy.
In a blender or food processor, puree beans, 1/3 cup sugar and rum and vanilla until smooth.
Add apple fiber and puree.
If the mixture seems dry, add 2 to 3 tablespoons water to make a thick batter.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then gradually beat in the remaining 1/3 cup sugar.
Fold gently into the bean-and-fiber mixture.
Spoon into prepared cake pan; bake for 50 minutes or until a toothpick, when inserted into center of cake, comes out dry.

title: blue ribbon split pea soup
directions: Heat the butter and oil together in a large soup kettle.

Add the carrots, celery, onion, garlic and cabbage. Saute, stirring frequently, for several minutes. Add the water, split peas, seasonings and bouillon. Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer over medium heat for 1 hour and 30 minutes, stirring frequently. Stir in the parsley and adjust the seasonings.
This soup freezes beautifully.

title: crab spread
directions: Blend first 6 ingredients.
Spread on serving plate, shaping into a circle.
Top with chili sauce.
Drain crabmeat and sprinkle on sauce.
Garnish with parsley if desired.
Serve with crackers.

title: microwave cocktail meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, egg, bread crumbs, onion, salt and pepper in a large mixing bowl.
Shape into small meatballs and place in a pie plate.
Microwave for 7 to 8 minutes.
Give 1/2 turn and rearrange meatballs once during cooking.
Meatballs may not be completely cooked at this time, but this is alright.
Drain meatballs thoroughly.

title: payday bars
directions: Mix cake mix with 1 stick of melted margarine and beaten egg. Press in bottom of a buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: peach moonshine
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and hot peach juice.
Add lemon juice and allow to cool. When mixture begins to thicken, fold in peaches.

title: fudge brownies
directions: In microwave or stove top, melt butter and chocolate until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir in eggs, one at a time. Then stir in flour and vanilla.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan for 20 minutes at 350°.
Add nuts if desired.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs.
Blend well. Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Drop 1-inch balls of dough onto cookie sheet using 2 teaspoons.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.

title: stuffed jumbo shells
directions: Put enough sauce in bottom of baking dish to cover.
Cook shells as instructed on box.
Mix all ingredients.
Stuff shells and put in rows in baking dish or dishes.
You will have 32 shells.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: angel food fruit cake rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line two
15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pans with aluminum foil.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Divide between the two pans and spread evenly.
Cut through the batter with a spatula or knife to remove big air bubbles.
Bake 15 minutes.
Turn cake onto a lint-free towel, that has been sprinkled with powdered sugar, right from the oven.
Carefully remove foil.
Beginning at the short end, roll cake and towel jelly roll fashion.
Cool completely.
Unroll cakes and spread about 1 cup of pie filling to within 1-inch of the edge on each cake.
Re-roll and place seam side down on serving plate. Dust with more powdered sugar.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Mix all in greased casserole.
Top with mashed potatoes (instant works well).
Cut up parsley and mix with potatoes.
Bake about 30 minutes at 400°. Leftover pork is equally as fine.
Just use a little chicken broth instead of beef.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Put graham cracker crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour melted margarine over crumbs.
Add rest of ingredients as listed in layers EXCEPT milk over crumbs.
Pour milk over top and bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fresh green cabbage
directions: Cook meat until done.
To it, add washed, cut cabbage and green peppers.
Cook to desired tenderness.
Season to taste.

title: fudge topped brownies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder, eggs, milk and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 40 minutes or until set.
Just before brownies are done, in a saucepan, over low heat, melt chips with sweetened condensed milk and remaining vanilla.
Immediately spread over hot brownies.
Cool.
Chill.
Makes 36 to 40 bars.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream margarine with sugar.
Add milk and beat well.
Add beaten eggs.
Combine dry ingredients and mix into batter.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Reserve
1 1/2 cups batter for filling. Bake in 3 (9-inch) greased and floured cake pans for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: old fashioned potato pie
directions: Bake shell at 450°
for 10 minutes.
Set aside.
Combine eggs, sugar and half and half and beat well.
Stir in potatoes and vanilla.
Pour mixture in pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes or until set.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Mix all ingredients together; pour into baking dish and put in refrigerator to get cold.
Yields 12 servings.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: In skillet, melt butter and add heavy whipping cream, Parmesan cheese and Romano cheese over medium heat, stirring constantly. Bring to boil.
Add parsley and pepper.
Pour mixture over pasta of your choice.

title: whipped jello
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add sugar.
Chill until slightly set.
Then whip jello.
Set aside.
Whip chilled milk until stiff. Fold into Jello and add pineapple.
Keep well chilled. (Other fruit may be used in place of pineapple)

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Brown and saute meat and onions.
Slice and butter eggplant and fry.
Layer hamburger meat and eggplant.
Top with tomato sauce and grated cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 325°.

title: spinach balls
directions: Preheat oven to Bake and 100°.
On a cutting board, peel and chop onion with a sharp knife.
Unwrap stick of margarine and melt over a medium-low heat in a small saucepan.
Break and beat eggs in a large mixing bowl.
To the eggs, add the chopped onion.
To the egg and onion mixture, add the melted margarine.
Measure and add stuffing, Parmesan, pepper and garlic salt and stir into the egg mixture.
Lastly, add spinach to the egg mixture.
Stir until the mixture is evenly mixed.

Two or three students in the unit will take enough of the mixture to roll the mixture into a 1-inch ball (the size of a quarter) and place them onto a jelly roll pan. Place the pan of appetizers on the middle rack of the oven and bake them for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove the appetizers from the pan, place them on a plate and place them on the serving table.

title: rice casserole
directions: Brown rice in butter.
Put all ingredients together in casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 400°.

title: peach pickles
directions: Drain peaches, saving juice.
To the juice, add sugar, vinegar, cinnamon and cloves.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Put peaches in jars and cover with juice mixture.
Cool, then refrigerate. Ready to eat after standing overnight.

title: lemon-chocolate bundt cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except the chocolate syrup and mix 5 to 7 minutes with an electric mixer.
Generously butter Bundt cake pan.
Pour 3/4 of the batter into the cake pan.
Mix the 1/2 cup chocolate syrup into the remaining 1/4 of the batter.
Pour on top of the batter already in the cake pan and do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let cool completely before removing. If desired, top with sifted powdered sugar to give a frosty appearance.

title: wonton wrap appetizers
directions: Cook sausage; chop fine while cooking.
Drain grease.

title: chicken chili stew
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Cook onion, green pepper, garlic and chicken until chicken is not pink.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Mix melted margarine, oil and sugar.
Beat eggs and combine with water, vanilla and nutmeg.
Add to sugar mixture, presifted flour, salt and baking soda and add to mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour in buttered jelly roll pan, 16 x 11-inch.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix and beat together until smooth the last eight ingredients listed.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan. Pour 1/2 of the batter into pan, then half of the sliced apples (lay by hand evenly).
Pour remaining batter over apples.
Then place remaining sliced apples evenly on top (pinwheel style). Pour cinnamon and sugar over top.
Bake 1 3/4 hours.
Do not test until after 1 hour.
Depending on oven, may take only 1 1/2 hours.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes; slice thin.
Dip in beaten eggs.
Roll in corn meal which has been seasoned to taste.
Place in hot cooking oil until golden brown.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to the creamed mixture.
Add bananas and nuts.
Blend together. Bake in a greased loaf pan in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: spray and wash
directions: Mix.
Spray on spot, and throw into washer with other detergent.

title: blackened catfish fillets
directions: Preheat large heavy skillet until very hot.
Combine first nine ingredients in a small bowl.
Dip fillets in melted butter, then in seasoning mixture.
Place in hot skillet.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes per side until blackened.
Serve with squeeze of fresh lemon.
Serves 4.

title: canning recipe for dill beans
directions: Place unbroken beans lengthwise in pint jars; leave 1/4-inch at top.
Add 1/4 teaspoon of cayenne pepper to each jar.
Also add 1 clove garlic and 1 head of dill to each jar.
Combine remaining ingredients in a pan and bring to a boil.
Pour approximately 1/2 cup of boiling ingredients over beans in jars (needs to cover beans).
Put on lids and put in hot water bath for 10 minutes. Store on shelf for a few weeks to enjoy full flavor.
Serve chilled.

title: chocolate turtle cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels in milk, stirring frequently until smooth.
Pour over crust.
Top with pecans.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt oleo and add to the first mixture.
Roll into balls. Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Melt large bag of chocolate chips and 1/2 bar paraffin wax.
Use toothpicks to pick up balls and dip in chocolate.

title: mocha marbled coffee
directions: Whip 1 cup whipping cream until stiff and blend with 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Fold in 2 ounces chopped or coarsely grated semi-sweet chocolate.
Fill regular sized cups with hot coffee and top each with 2 or 3 tablespoons of the flavored whipped cream.
Sprinkle each with a little more chopped semi-sweet chocolate, if you like.
This is enough topping for 8 to 10 servings of coffee.

title: hungry jack beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain. Add pork and beans, brown sugar and barbecue sauce. Bring to a full boil. Put mixture into casserole dish. Cut biscuits in half and arrange on top. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 400° until biscuits are golden brown.

title: pistachio pudding dessert
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Pat lightly in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar together.
Cream well and spread on top of cooled crust.
Mix pudding with milk.
Mix with beaters for 2 minutes.
Spread on top of cream cheese mixture. Spread other half of the Cool Whip on top.
Chill, cut and serve.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt margarine in the microwave.
Pour margarine over brown sugar and mix with eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Mix.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Grease a 15 x 10-inch pan and spread mixture out.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: tacos
directions: Brown the beef and add season mix. Put in shells.
Add sauce, cheese and sour cream.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind whole peppers and onions.
Add rest of ingredients; boil 30 minutes.
Pack in jar and seal.

title: lint modeling
directions: Combine lint and water in a saucepan.
Add flour and stir to prevent lumps.
Add oil.
Cook over low heat until mixture forms peaks.
Pour out and cool on old newspapers.
Shape over balloons, boxes or use molds.
Use like papier-mache.

title: sausage and cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Melt cheese with milk in microwave. Add sausage to cheese and keep warm in crock-pot or fondue pot. Add more milk if needed to make a soft consistency.

title: hummingbird muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and 1/2 teaspoon salt (optional).

title: warm fruit
directions: In a
1/2 quart baking dish combine all the ingredients except the pecan pieces.
Sprinkle
the pecans on top and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Combine peppers, vinegar and sugar; bring to a boil.
Add Certo.
Bring back to boiling for 4 to 5 minutes.
Add a few drops of food coloring.
Take off stove and continue to stir for several minutes.
Seal in jars.
Serve on softened cream cheese as a dip for Ritz crackers.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Cream shortening, fruit and flour.
Then add beaten eggs and oleo.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
These are 50 calories each.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix first five ingredients. Add flour and mix well.
Dough will be very soft when made.
Store in refrigerator.
Use as needed.
Grease or spray muffin pans and fill about 1/2 full. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: pork chops and browned rice
directions: Brown chops in fat in cooker.
Remove.
Place rice in hot fat. Stir constantly until browned.
Add tomatoes (with liquid) and remaining ingredients.
Stir well, breaking up tomatoes.
Add chops.
Cover; set control at 10 and bring pressure up over moderate heat.
Cook 13 minutes after control jiggles (or cook at 15 for 9 minutes).
Cool cooker normally for 5 minutes, then place under faucet.
Makes 4 servings.

title: stir-fry
directions: Use as many vegetables as you need for the amount of people you need to serve.
Marinate beef overnight.
(Chicken only needs to be marinated 20 to 30 minutes.) Cook marinated meat until brown.
Place in baking dish and cook in slow 300° oven until tender.
Stir-fry vegetables in wok or large skillet, until tender.
Cook 2 cups rice in 4 cups of water.
Serve veggies and meat over rice.
Add soy sauce.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli according to package directions; drain. While broccoli is still warm, stir in the cubed Velveeta cheese. Place the ingredients in a small, lightly greased casserole dish. Smash the Ritz crackers with a rolling pin until all are crushed. Mix with melted margarine.
Put mixture on top of broccoli.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: hearty beef and potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes on bottom and up side of an 8 x 12-inch casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 10 minutes.
Brown beef in large chunks; drain.
Place beef, broccoli, 1/2 can fried onions and tomato in potato shell.
Combine soup and milk.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 2 to 3 minutes longer.

title: mexican appetizer
directions: Blend cheeses and spread on platter.
Sprinkle on half of taco mix.
Add layer of pepper, onions and tomato.
Sprinkle remaining taco mix.
Put Cheddar cheese on top.
Chill.
Serve with taco chips.

title: creamy red pepper dip
directions: Mix together. Let stand for about 2 hours and serve with assorted cut up vegetables.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix flour with sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in corn meal.
Add eggs, milk and butter.
Beat with mixer until smooth, 1 minute.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cool cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Cool until slightly set.
Add remaining ingredients and congeal.

title: lemony bouillon
directions: Combine chicken broth, lemon rind, lemon juice and bay leaf in a saucepan over medium heat.
Bring mixture just to boiling point, then simmer over low heat for 5 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream with oreos
directions: In large bowl, beat egg yolks, milk, water and vanilla.
Fold in cookies and whipped cream.
Pour into an aluminum foil-lined 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cover; freeze 6 hours until firm.
Scoop ice cream from pan or peel off foil and slice.
Return leftovers to freezer.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll rolls and press out in an ungreased jelly roll pan. Bake for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix together softened cream cheese, Miracle Whip, dill weed and onion.
(Better if mixed, refrigerated overnight, then left to stand at room temperature until spreadable.)
Spread on baked crust.
Cut vegetables into bite sized pieces and sprinkle on top.
Top with shredded cheese and bacon bits (if desired).

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburg and onion; drain grease.
Add taco seasoning to meat.
Layer in casserole or pie plate the meat, taco sauce and French onion dip; top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and chop broccoli into bite size pieces.
(I use only the flowers.)
Fry bacon until crisp; drain on paper towels and crumble.
Cut onion fine.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar together.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill several hours. Sprinkle with grated cheese before serving.

title: chili sauce(yields 6 pints)
directions: Put tomatoes, onion and mango through food chopper.
Add other ingredients and boil 2 hours or until thick.
Stir frequently. Ladle into jars and seal at once.

title: roll dumplings
directions: Mix flour and salt in a bowl.
Make a well in mixture. Add egg and hot broth.
Roll out thin on floured board. Cut in wide strips.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 320° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: vegetable burritos
directions: Coat a large Dutch oven with vegetable cooking spray; place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add onion, mushrooms and garlic. Saute until vegetables are tender and all liquid is absorbed.
Add zucchini, carrots, green pepper, tomato, olives and jalapeno pepper; saute, stirring constantly, about 10 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Drain vegetables; add green chiles and next 6 ingredients; stir mixture well.
Spoon 1/3 cup vegetable mixture onto each tortilla and fold edges over.
Serve immediately. Yield:
15 servings.

title: biscuit breakfast ring
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and water.
Heat to melt margarine. Stir in nuts.
Toss biscuit pieces in butter and nuts.
Place in tube cake pan or use a round pan and place an inverted
custard cup in the center to make a ring with the biscuits.
Bake at 375 degrees 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mrs. field's nutty white chunk cookies
directions: Mix together softened butter and sugars.
Beat in eggs.
Add remaining dry ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Add vanilla, pecans and white chocolate bar.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 22 minutes.

title: two-corn casserole
directions: Melt stick of butter.
Saute onion; set aside to cool.
In large bowl, combine both corns, corn muffin mix and 3 eggs.
Add cooled onion mixture; mix well.
Place in a casserole that has been sprayed with nonstick spray.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot sausage appetizers
directions: Mix well.
Form bite-size balls.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.
Can be made ahead of time and frozen.
Makes about 70.

title: herb-roasted potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 500°.
Cut potatoes lengthwise (spear them). Combine oil, garlic, rosemary, pepper and salt (optional).
Toss potatoes in mixture.
Line baking sheet with foil.
Place potatoes on sheet.
Roast 25 minutes or until potatoes are golden brown.

title: spinach dip in bread bowl
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together. Scoop out center of loaf of rye bread. Put dip mixture in center of loaf with pieces of bread from the center part around the plate beside loaf.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Place all ingredients in blender a little at a time until blended into a fine powder.
Store in jar and use as needed.
Use 2 teaspoons per serving.
Serve hot or cold.

title: soft hamburgers
directions: Combine first column ingredients and
shape into 6 to 8 patties.
Fry to desired doneness.	Combine remaining ingredients. Spoon over each patty.
Cook another few minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in a large Dutch oven. Don't drain.
Add baking soda and parboil 1/2 hour.
Drain.
Add other ingredients, except catsup.
Prepare in crock-pot on high for 4 to 6 hours or bake in 275° oven for 3 to 4 hours.
Add catsup last half hour.

title: breakfast baked eggs
directions: Butter and dice bread slices.
Put meat and cheese in a 9 x 12-inch glass baking dish.
Alternate the three.

title: chicken salad
directions: Dice chicken into small pieces when warm.
Add Miracle Whip, pecans, salt, pepper, curry powder and eggs.

title: artichoke nibblers
directions: Saute onion, garlic and 1 jar of artichokes (use oil of this jar to saute).
Drain other jar and add to pan; take off stove. Beat eggs and add all remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan and bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Store in jars.
Put 4 to 5 teaspoons in a cup and add hot water.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar; add egg and beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Chill dough before rolling out.
Roll out 1/8 inch thick on lightly floured surface.
Cut with floured cookie cutters; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon, if desired.
Bake on greased cookie sheets at 375° about 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli in small amount of water just long enough to separate. Saute onion in butter. Combine broccoli, onion and remaining ingredients in large casserole. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: kent's ranch bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
In a large bowl, blend 2 cups water, milk, honey and oats.
Add yeast mixture. Stir well and cover.
Let stand for 30 minutes.

Stir down and add the salt, oil, cornmeal and whole wheat flour. Beat until smooth. Add enough white flour to make a soft dough. Turn out on floured surface and knead 8 to 10 minutes. Turn into greased bowl. Cover and let rise until doubled (approximately 1 hour).
Punch down, knead lightly and let rest 10 minutes.
Place in two 9 x 5 x 3-inch greased loaf pans. Cover and let rise until double, about 30 minutes. Bake in preheated 375° oven about 35 minutes.
Turn out on wire racks to cool.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Pack in 1 gallon jar.
Place in refrigerator.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in oil.
Add soups and rice.
Mix and pour over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caesar salad
directions: Wash and cut lettuce in bite size pieces.
Mix oil, lemon juice, garlic, Worcestershire sauce and shake of m.s.g.
Pour on lettuce.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: open-face apple muffins
directions: Place muffin halves, split side up, on cookie sheet.
On each muffin half, put 5 or 6 apple slices.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 425° until apples are tender, approximately 15 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken in water; cool.
Drain water; debone all.
Place in bottom of large foil pan.
Mix soup and sour cream together; place on top of chicken.
Melt oleo; mix with crumbled crackers and poppy seed.
Spread over.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until good and hot and lightly brown crackers.
Cook for crowd 30 to 40.

title: warm blue cheese, bacon and garlic dip
directions: (May be made one day in advance and refrigerated.)

title: honey mint carrots
directions: Cook carrots in a small amount of boiling water 6 to 8 minutes or until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Combine butter and honey in a large skillet.
Cook over medium low heat until butter melts. Stir in chopped mint; cook 1 minute.
Add cooked carrots and toss gently until carrots are glazed.
Cook just until carrots are thoroughly heated.
Transfer to a serving platter and garnish with fresh mint sprigs.

title: irish potato soup
directions: Melt butter or margarine
in
heavy
pan over low heat. Add onions, stirring
until
tender.
Add potatoes, water, and salt. Cover pan and
cook
until potatoes are tender.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Press
potatoes
through
sieve
and add to liquid.
Add hot milk and
stir
well.
Combine
cold milk and beaten egg yolk. Add
slowly to warm soup, stirring constantly.
Add cayenne pepper.
Reheat soup slowly, but do not boil. Add parsley just before serving.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Pour sauce into airtight container.
Store in refrigerator.
Serve sauce over cream cheese with cheese dough, or with pork or beef.

title: indonesian gado gado dip
directions: Mix all together in bowl until smooth.
Great to dip Belgian endive, cucumber, raw asparagus, cauliflower and jicama in. Makes 1/2 cup.

title: vegetarian burritos
directions: Crush Tater Tots; put in a large skillet and add oil.
Cook over medium heat until brown.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in beans and mix well.
Add the scrambled eggs (broken into small pieces) and mix well.
Cover with the salsa and mix.

title: brunch pie
directions: Coat 9-inch pie plate with oleo.
Mix hash with egg; press into plate to form crust.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Saute onion in 3 tablespoons oleo.
Layer cheese, onion and Veg-All in crust. Beat together remaining eggs, milk, flour, mustard, garlic and pepper.
Pour over mixture in crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes (until filling is set).
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: fudge balls
directions: Cook until butter melts.
Add other ingredients.
Roll into little balls.

title: quick french bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in the warm water and set aside.
Combine the hot water, sugar, salt, oil and 3 cups flour; mix well with large spoon.
Add yeast and mix well.
Add remaining 3 cups flour; mix well.
Let dough rise 10 minutes; stir down and let rise 10 minutes again.
Do this 5 times (50 minutes total).
Turn dough onto floured board.
Knead only until can be handled.
Divide in half and roll each to 9 x 12-inch rectangle.
Roll up as if for cinnamon rolls.
Place seam down on cookie sheet; sprinkle lightly with corn meal.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: french style quiche
directions: Whisk eggs, sour cream, half and half and seasonings together.
Sprinkle cheese (I prefer Swiss, but any shredded cheese is fine) on bottom of unbaked pie crust.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 300° and continue to bake for 40 minutes.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Place uncooked rice in casserole.
Add water and sherry.
Place uncooked chicken parts on top.
Place stick of butter over chicken. Cover with aluminum foil. qPreheat oven to 450°, bake for 50 minutes.
Take off foil and bake 10 minutes more and check to see if rice is done.
Remove from oven and bon appetit!

title: b t l pasta salad
directions: Prepare salad as directed on package.
Fold tomato and bacon into finished salad.
Serve on lettuce.
Garnish with additional bacon, if desired.
Refrigerate any remaining salad.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, egg and milk.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Blend in bananas, vanilla extract and nuts. Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: cinnamon candy
directions: Cook sugar, water and syrup to hard crack stage (300°).
Add cinnamon oil and food coloring.
Pour on a well-greased cookie sheet.
Let cool, then break into pieces.

title: chicken delight
directions: Combine flour and butter.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook over hot water until thick.
Add cheese, beaten egg yolks and chicken.
Blend well.
Season with salt, pepper and cayenne.
Slowly, just a little at a time, fold in stiffly beaten egg whites gently.
Pour into a well-oiled casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Place in a pan of warm water.
Bake in a 375° oven until knife comes out clean, at least 2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Soften butter and cream with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla.
Sift together flour, cocoa and salt.
Stir soda in sour cream.
Add sour cream and flour mixture alternately to sugar mixture.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick comes clean.
Invert on cake plate.

title: three layer coconut pie
directions: Layer 1:
Cream oleo, flour and 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Add nuts and put into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes or until very light brown.
Cool.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Add the chopped onion and potato to melted butter with the water.
Season with garlic, salt and pepper. Cover and cook slowly until potatoes are very soft.
Add the milk.
Continue cooking until soup comes to a boil.
Then put through a sieve or blender. Return to the pan.
Add the chopped parsley; adjust seasonings and heat thoroughly before serving.
Yield: About 1 quart.

title: breakfast casserolewestboro, missouri
directions: Oil a 9 X 13 pan and cover the bottom with cubed bread.
Fry the sausage, drain and sprinkle it over the bread.
Add the grated cheese and cut up mushrooms.
Combine the seasonings and milk with the slightly beaten eggs.
Pour over the bread and cheese mixture and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: joe's sauerkraut confetti
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a clear casserole dish and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine in large casserole dish.
Add stuffing mix to coat.
Remove half of stuffing and set aside for topping.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Arrange fruit in mixed layers in buttered casserole.
Over each layer sprinkle brown sugar and spices in the amount you like. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot.

title: lebanese-italian dressing
directions: Use over salads.
The mint adds a unique flavor.

title: rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. In a 1-quart casserole, beat the egg white and egg slightly with a fork. Add the skim milk, dry milk, sugar and vanilla, mixing well. Stir in the cooked rice and raisins. Sprinkle the mixture with nutmeg and cinnamon. Set casserole in a larger baking pan; fill the pan halfway up the side of the casserole with boiling water. Place on oven rack. Bake for 15 minutes. Stir pudding and bake for 35 minutes or longer until the milk is absorbed. Serve pudding warm or chilled. Makes four 1/2 cup servings.

title: apple syrup-apple pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients for syrup except butter.
Cook until it boils and thickens slightly.
Then set off burner and add butter. Serve over hot pancakes.

title: diabetic carrot-raisin salad
directions: Combine carrots, pineapple and raisins; mix well.
Chill for 2 or 3 hours.
Stir in yogurt.
Serve on lettuce leaf, if desired. Yields 7 servings (each serving is 1/2 cup).

title: chinese rice
directions: Cool rice.
Mix with other ingredients and put into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: beans supreme with tomatoes
directions: Brown meat
in oil in heavy skillet. Add onions, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook
until vegetables are slightly brown. Add tomatoes, soup, beans,
salt
and
sauce.
Put in a 2 1/2 or 3 quart casserole or
x
x
2-inch
pan.
Top with grated cheese and bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Serves 10 to 12.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix and bake in crusts.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash potatoes and rub skins with oil. Bake for 1 hour, or until potatoes are done.
Reduce oven heat to 350°.

Cut a slice from top of each potato and scoop out pulp. Mash pulp; add sour cream, milk, salt, pepper and green onions. Fill potato shells with mixture and sprinkle with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: inflation beater stroganoff
directions: Roll ground chuck or hamburg into bite-size meatballs.
Brown over medium heat until almost cooked throughout.
Drain excess grease.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt butter, add brown sugar then cooked potatoes to flour mixture. Add sweet potato mixture alternately with buttermilk-soda mixture. Refrigerate 30 minutes. Roll on floured board.
Cut out and bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: lamb loin chops with peppered pears
directions: Combine all herbs, oil and water in a small bowl; mix well. Brush chops lightly with mixture and broil approximately 5 minutes.
Turn and brush lightly again.
Continue cooking for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: pumpkin nut cheesecake
directions: Combine ingredients and press into bottom and partially up the sides of a lightly greased and floured 9-inch spring-form pan. (Put foil in bottom of oven before baking in case butter leaks out.)

title: oatmeal whoopie pies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Add cinnamon and oatmeal. Mix well.
Put baking soda into hot water and add to batter.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 325°. Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: quick chicken noodles
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan combine soup, milk, cheese and pepper. Add noodles and chicken.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of chicken soup

title: microwave vegetable medley
directions: In a 15-inch round glass or ceramic dish, place head of cauliflower in center.
Arrange broccoli and carrots around outside.
Pour butter or margarine over vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with plastic wrap, turning back 1 edge to vent.
Microwave on High power for 17 to 19 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Vegetables should be crisp, but tender.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: In pan, mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add 1 cup milk and mix smooth.
Bring to boil, stirring continually, until smooth. Remove from heat.
With fork, beat eggs with remaining cup of milk.
Gradually stir into hot mixture.
Put back on heat and bring to boil until thickened a bit more.
Remove from heat; stir in butter, chocolate pieces and vanilla.
Stir until chocolate melts.
Pour in shell and chill.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until done. Drain.
Dice eggs, chop onion and celery and add to potatoes. Add dill relish, celery salt, salt and pepper to taste.
Add lemon juice. Put enough mayonnaise to make desired consistency. Sprinkle paprika to decorate.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: n. b.'s famous spoon bread
directions: Add salt, sugar and butter to the water; bring to a full boil. Stir in cold milk. In another bowl, add baking powder to eggs and beat well. Add to corn meal and stir well. Pour into a greased baking dish and bake about 30 minutes at 400°.

title: teri chicken
directions: Stir all ingredients (except chicken) together.
Soak chicken for several hours or overnight.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Turn once.
May be cooked outside on grill.

title: floyd's brunswick stew
directions: Chop chicken in blender or food processor along with some broth.
Also, chop tomatoes and whole kernel corn in blender before mixing.
Combine all ingredients in a large pot.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for approximately 2 hours.
If mixture seems too thick, add water until the desired consistency.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs.
Then add flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves, allspice and water.
Mix. Stir in nuts, raisins and applesauce.
Bake at 350°.

title: boboli italian bread shell recipes
directions: Trim Boboli shell as described in preceding paragraph.
Spread bottom of shell with mustard, Place shell in pizza pan.
Set aside.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and egg.
Stir in milk.
Sift dry ingredients and stir in.
Blend in berries.
Spread batter in greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream the butter in a large mixing bowl, gradually adding sugar.
Beat well.
Add honey.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine 3 cups of flour, baking powder, salt and spices.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with water, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Beat well after each addition.
Dredge raisins, figs and almonds in remaining 1/2 cup of flour, coating well.
Gently stir into batter.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove cake to wire rack and cool completely.
Yields one 9-inch loaf.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Slice and mix veggies and top with dressing.
Best if marinated a few hours.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain all excess fat.
Arrange chopped cabbage in casserole.
Add browned hamburger and onions on top.
Pour soup and cooked tomatoes over it all.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: taco casserole
directions: Microwave meat with seasoning 6 to 7 minutes on High.
Stir once during cooking.
Spread chips in bottom of baking dish. Spread meat over chips; top with cheese.
Micro-cook 6 to 8 minutes on Medium or until heated through and cheese melts.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes and onion.

title: microwave mozzarella sandwich
directions: Onto 1 side of each slice of bread, drizzle 1/2 teaspoon oil; top each slice of bread with half of the tomato slices and 1 ounce of cheese.
Sprinkle each sandwich with 1 1/2 teaspoons basil and pepper.
Set sandwiches on microwavable plate or large paper plate; cover with wax paper and microwave on Medium-high (70%) for 2 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: faye's grandma amber's molasses cookies
directions: Roll out on breadboard and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: fudge
directions: Boil milk, sugar, and butter for 7 minutes, stirring constantly, until it forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat and add nuts, chips, marshmallow cream, and vanilla.
Beat until thick.

title: tomato chutney
directions: Peel
tomatoes
and
chop.
Combine
with
sugar, salt, sliced orange
and
sliced
lemon.
Stir over heat until sugar dissolves. Add
cinnamon
and
ginger.
Bring to a boil; cook over low
heat until thick, about 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Remove cinnamon and ginger.
Add raisins and lemon juice and bring again to boil.
Stir in Tabasco; pour into hot pint or half-pint jars and seal at once.
Makes 3 1/2 pints.

title: ice cream snowballs
directions: If using an electric pizzelle iron containing round 5-inch grids, preheat according to manufacturer's directions.
In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar; continue to beat until smooth.
Beat in butter or margarine and anise extract or vanilla. Beat in flour and baking powder until thoroughly blended.
Batter will be sticky enough to be dropped by spoon.
Drop a generous tablespoonful of batter in center of each heated grid. Immediately close iron, squeezing handles together.
Scrape off any batter that flows out around edges.
Bake in electric iron 30 seconds or until light golden brown.
If using hand held iron, follow manufacturer's directions for baking.
When golden, loosen Pizzelle with fork or point of knife and carefully remove to a rack to cool.
Store Pizzelles in a tightly covered container. Use within 2 to 3 weeks.
Makes 48 to 50 (5-inch) Pizzelles. Enjoy!

title: shelley's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together except tomato sauce. Shape the meat in a loaf pan. Pour the tomato sauce on top of the meat. Bake at 375 degrees until done.

title: fiery mediterranean roast pork
directions: *Or use other crushed hot red pepper.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Mix rice, water and salt; cook until soft and add raisins. Take off stove.
Beat eggs well; add gradually, stirring into mixture.
Return to heat and cook until mixture coats metal spoon. Remove from stove.
Stir in vanilla and cinnamon or nutmeg. Serve hot or cold.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 300° for 45 or 50 minutes.

title: impossible cauliflower quiche
directions: Place drained
cauliflower
in greased 9-inch pie plate or quiche
dish.
Sprinkle
with
the	onion, green pepper and cheese.
Place remaining ingredients in blender, then whirl 15 seconds.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake in preheated 375° oven 20 to 25 minutes	or
until
knife
inserted
in center comes out clean and top is golden.	Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Sprinkle buttered crackers on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken in water until tender.
Bone and remove skin. Cut into bite size pieces.

title: ambrosia
directions: Note: Use a large, cold bowl.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain all beans until dry.
Add vegetables, vinegar and sugar; let set for 10 minutes.
Add dressing and store in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Makes a good summer meal.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheeses.
Mix all ingredients with beater and chill. Remove from refrigerator and mold into a ball.
Roll in nuts. Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, remove and let come to a room temperature.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini until almost tender.
Drain well.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Stir in oil and other ingredients.
Add zucchini and turn into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven or until done.

title: cheddary scalloped potatoes
directions: In skillet over medium heat, cook onion in margarine until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes or until hot and bubbling.
Makes 4 servings, but can be doubled.

title: fannie's banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine Eagle Brand and milk.
Add pudding mix and beat until well blended.
Chill for 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: chilaquilles
directions: Saute onions and garlic in 2 tablespoons fat until clear.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Simmer until tomatoes are cooked.
Add peppers.
Cut tortillas in fourths and dip in hot fat.
Remove immediately and drain on paper towels.
Put a layer of tortillas in baking dish, layer of sauce, then layer of grated cheese.
Continue until dish is filled.
Heat in 375° oven until cheese melts (30 to 45 minutes).
Just before serving, top with sour cream.
Serves 8 to 10.
Use large Pyrex baking dish or two small ones.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: In
a large bowl, dice potatoes.
Brown bacon in large skillet.
Crumble bacon into potatoes; save drippings in skillet. Use wire whip and add flour.
Stir until smooth.
Add sugar, vinegar, water, salt, pepper and celery seed.
Stir until well blended.
Continue blending until mixture bubbles and thickens. Add onion and mixture to potatoes and bacon and stir until thoroughly mixed.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, milk, vanilla and melted oleo. Make up like biscuits.
Roll out and cut.
Bake in 350° oven until light brown.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix water, sugar and vinegar in saucepan.
Heat until sugar dissolves.
Add oil; mix and pour over sauerkraut mixture.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Place cream cheese in a glass dish.
Microwave 30 seconds on High to soften.
Blend in the remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: rocky road pie
directions: Pour half and half into large bowl.
Add pie filling.
Whisk until blended well.
Fold in whipped topping until well mixed. Add remaining ingredients.
Freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer and let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Store leftovers in freezer.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Place chicken in buttered dish. Combine dressing mix, broth, pepper and butter.
Put on top of chicken. Top dressing with mushroom soup mixed with milk. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: holiday dip
directions: Blend sour cream, mayonnaise, sugar, salt, Tabasco sauce and pepper.
Stir in minced vegetables.
Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.
Serve with potato chips or snack items.
Great on a plate with whole radishes, green pepper strips, celery, carrot curls, cauliflower or use as a salad dressing on crisp green salad.

title: fried okra
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs, milk and salt.
Add okra; toss to coat well, then add flour.
Toss until flour is all taken up. Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil; flatten with spoon.
Turn heat down; cook until done and golden brown.
Serve warm or hot.

title: kiddy peanut butter candy wheels
directions: Whip egg white until stiff, adding sugar slowly, until smooth and consistency of dough.
Divide in 2 squares 1/4-inch thick. Cover evenly with peanut butter.
Roll into loaves.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate overnight.
Cut into 1/2-inch wheels.

title: crumb cake
directions: Combine flour, salt and sugar.
Cut butter into this mixture with pastry blender or fork.
Reserve 2/3 cup crumbs for topping.

title: violet's pizza dough
directions: Mix yeast with warm water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Knead for 5 minutes.
Let rise for 1 to 2 hours.
Pat onto pizza pans. Allow to rise for another hour.
Add favorite toppings and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind pears through coarse food chopper and let drip until excess juice is removed.
Grind peppers and onions.
Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil and boil 20 minutes. Fill sterilized jars and seal.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken into medium-size casserole dish.
Mix soup, sour cream and cream.
Pour on top of chicken.
Crumble crackers on top and pour oleo to top.
Bake at 300° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: rainbow cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, baking in well-greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan.
Cool cake in pan for 15 minutes; prick with utility fork at 1/2 inch intervals. Meanwhile, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and carefully pour over warm cake.
Chill 3-4 hours.
Top with whipped topping.
Cut into squares and garnish with strawberries.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain 1 large package broccoli.
Mix together the cheese, soup and mayonnaise and mix with broccoli.
Then top with cracker crumbs and bake until bubbly.

title: recipe for a happy family
directions: First, you put in several cups of friendliness, be generous with it, because this is the foundation of your recipe.
Put in 2 full cups of kindness, 1/2 cup of consideration, a dash of thoughtfulness, 2 tablespoons fun, a dash of neatness, and 1 cup of "nice conversation" powder.
Stir until evenly mixed, then pour into a soft heart.
Bake at loving degree.
Check often to see that none of the ingredients evaporate.
Bake until it is guaranteed not to fall apart.
Keep it warm and always use.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix cake and cook like
box
says making 2 layers.
Cool and cut each layer in half making 4 layers.
Mix sour cream and sugar; spread on each layer cut side up so that it will soak up juice. Put blueberries on top of sour cream mixture and spread on each layer.
Put Cool Whip over the whole cake.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper; drain.
Cook noodles until tender.
Combine all ingredients with 1/2 cup cheese.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve with garlic bread.
Mmm!

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add sour cream, egg yolks and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to cream mixture, blending well.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape into balls, working with small portions at a time.
Keep remaining dough chilled.
Cut dough with cutter and sprinkle cutouts with sugar and cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes on greased cookie sheet.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Open packages of rolls and lay flat on cookie sheet; bake following directions on package.

title: savory spareribs
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients.
Spread on ribs.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla. Add dry ingredients. Mix well. Stir in nuts and zucchini. Pour into two well greased loaf pans. Bake 325° for one hour.

title: roy's peach pie
directions: Mix pudding, flour, egg and milk together well. Spread in well-greased pan or casserole dish. Put 1 can sliced peaches on top. Mix together 3 tablespoons peach juice, 1 (8 ounce) cream cheese and 1/3 cup sugar. Spread on peaches. Sprinkle 3 tablespoons brown sugar and cinnamon on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: calico meringues
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until foamy in a small deep bowl.
Gradually beat in sugar to make a stiff meringue. Fold in M&M's.
Grease and flour a large cookie sheet.
Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls on sheet.
Garnish with an M&M.
Bake in 250° oven for 30 minutes or until cookies are firm, but still white.
Cool on wire rack.
Store in container with tight lid.

title: strawberry angel delight
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients like pie crust and line pie plate. Bake for 12 minutes at 325°.
In mixer, combine the next 3 ingredients.
Fold in whipped cream.
Put in cooled pie shell and freeze.

title: spinach salad(10 servings)
directions: Tear clean, crisp, thoroughly dried spinach into large salad bowl.
Rinse and drain sprouts.
Toss all salad ingredients together.
Set aside.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine Eagle Brand and water.
Fold in whipped mix; beat until well blended.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into 2 1/2-quart round glass serving bowl.
Top with 1/3 each of the vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding.
Repeat layering twice.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Begin by dusting the chicken cubes lightly with salt, pepper and flour.
Heat a large heavy saucepan to medium-high and brown the chicken quickly, about 5 minutes.
Add the chicken broth, sweet basil, vegetables and the cooking sherry and bring to a simmer.

title: sausage chowder
directions: Brown sausage in skillet and drain fat well.
Can use mild or spicy sausage.
Chop onion and add chopped potato.
Heat together and add tomatoes and navy beans with the juice as well.
Simmer over low heat until potatoes are tender.
Serve with cornbread. An easy meal for a busy day.

title: mom's pineapple angel food pie
directions: In saucepan, combine pineapple, water and salt; bring to boil. In bowl combine sugar and cornstarch; add to pineapple mixture. Cook until thickened; let cool.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill before serving.

title: apple pie with no crust
directions: Peel apples; cut them into slices, then put them in a pie plate.
Sprinkle the cinnamon and the sugar over the apples.
In a bowl, mix all other ingredients together, then spread over apples. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: freyda's sour cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and add 2 cups of sugar gradually, beating until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Fold in cream and vanilla.
Fold in the flour, sifted with baking powder and salt.
Combine remaining sugar, nuts and cinnamon. Place about 1/3 of the batter in a well-greased and floured tube pan.
Sprinkle with 3/4 nut mixture.
Pour remaining batter. Sprinkle nut mixture on top.
Bake 60 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix ingredients and layer on bottom of dish.
Top with grated cheese, lettuce, tomato, etc.
Dip with taco chips.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper.
Add tomato paste.
Mix milk, eggs, salt, oregano and garlic powder.
Put half of bread in greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Top with half of meat and vegetable mixture.
Top with half of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Pour milk and egg mixture over all.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Refrigerate for 4 or more hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Allow to stand for 5 minutes before cutting.

title: italian spinach
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil until lightly browned.
Add spinach, salt and pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Toss and serve immediately. Serves 4 people.

title: barbecue pork on buns
directions: Boil ham or pork loin in water until done.
Chop up in pieces. Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Pour over meat.
Serve hot on buns.

title: ten-cup salad
directions: Combine pineapple, oranges, coconut and marshmallows. Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and sugar; fold into the fruit mixture. Store in a bowl overnight. Serve chilled. This makes a BIG salad for a crowd.

title: beef stroganoff salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix well and refrigerate until chilled.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together and pour in greased casserole or baking dish.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Top with more cheese if desired.
Very good cold the next day.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook meat and onion until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off any excess fat.
Stir in the prepared mustard, chili powder and salt.
Cook and stir for 1 minute.
Add tomato sauce, tomato juice, shredded carrot and bulgur wheat.
Bring mixture to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer meat mixture, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring.
Serve.
Spoon the meat mixture onto buns.
Sprinkle each bun with shredded cheese. Makes 6 servings.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring oleo
or butter, brown sugar, salt and white Karo to a boil
while
stirring.
Boil 5 more minutes without stirring, then add
vanilla
and baking soda.
Pour over unsalted popped corn. Stir
well, then pour into large flat pan.	Bake for 50 minutes at	250°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Store in dry containers and cover.

title: pesto
directions: Combine everything in a blender on low, then medium speed. (Arrange things so the blender blade will turn.) Thoroughly work everything into a smooth paste.
Toss with hot, drained pasta. This makes enough for about 6 servings of pasta.

title: beer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon, allspice and cloves into a bowl.
Set aside.
Cream shortening.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until light.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of the flour mixture.
Gradually add remaining flour to sugar mixture.
Mix well, then add beer and beat until blended.
Add reserved flour to nuts.
Mix well.
Fold into batter.
Spoon into a greased tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and put in casserole dish. Sprinkle stuffing mix on top and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate coffee cake
directions: In a large bowl, cream together the butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour, vanilla, baking powder, baking soda and salt; mix well. Stir in milk, chocolate chips and walnuts.
Mixture will be thick. Pour into greased 9 x 3-inch spring-form cake pan.
Sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: beef stew deluxe
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Serve with rice or potatoes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Scramble eggs, fry bacon or sausage and mix with eggs. Combine with sour cream and cheese.
Bake until hot.
If already hot, bake 15 to 20 minutes and if cold, bake 25 to 30 minutes. This is good to fix for company or for a quick and easy breakfast for school.
Can be made ahead of time and kept in the refrigerator for 2 -3 days.

title: yogurt fresh fruit pie
directions: Prepare gelatin, using only 1 1/2 cups of liquid.
Chill until syrupy.
Reserve 1/4 cup.
Mix remainder with yogurt.
Spread in baked pie shell.
Arrange fruit over yogurt.
Brush with remaining Jell-O.
Chill, covered, overnight.

title: vegetarian tortilla pie
directions: Preheat oven to 500°. Spray 15 x 10 jelly roll pan with nonstick cooking spray.
tags: shredded reduced fat Monterey Jack cheese

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Wash and drain peppers, devein and remove seeds.
Grate cheese; stuff peppers and add rest of cheese to sausage and Bisquick mix.
Beat eggs well; set aside.
Pat 1 tablespoon sausage mixture in palm of hand.
Lay stuffed pepper on sausage. Pat mixture around pepper.
Seal dough real well so cheese won't run out.
Dip in beaten eggs and roll in Shake 'n Bake.
Bake for 30 or 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: seven layer taco dip(serves a party of 12 to 14)
directions: Layer ingredients in a casserole dish or flat pan with edges as follows:

title: finn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients into warm water to which yeast and sugar have been dissolved.
Knead for at least 5 minutes.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours or longer until about double in bulk.
Shape into round, low (about 2-inch thick) loaves.
Place on sprayed or greased cookie sheet.

title: butter cream bonbons
directions: Beat cream cheese and butter in a large mixer bowl until smooth.
Gradually blend in sugar and vanilla.
If necessary, chill about 1 hour until mixture can be formed into 1-inch balls. Place balls on cookie sheet.
Chill overnight.
Dip in chocolate.

title: mound bars
directions: Melt oleo.
Add Milnot and powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Add coconut.
Blend thoroughly.
Press into 8 x 9-inch buttered pan. Freeze until firm.
Cut into 1 x 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Press almond into each piece.
Melt chocolate blocks in microwave.
Use fork to dip coconut mixture into melted chocolate.

title: apple cake with butterscotch chips
directions: Mix sugar, oil, water and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add nuts and apples; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle butterscotch morsels over top. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Stir together.
Put in large flat baking dish.
Lay chicken parts on top.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 2 hours at 350°. Uncover and bake 1/2 hour longer to brown chicken.
I happen to add 1 can of water, because it gets too dry.
This is a good meal and easy.

title: marinade
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Stick meat (London Broil or beef cubes for shish kabobs) with a fork on both sides.
Sprinkle with Accent or another meat tenderizer.
Pour marinade over meat and let marinate.
Broil or grill meat; moisten with marinade while cooking.

title: slovenian mushroom pastries
directions: Combine flour, butter, 6 tablespoons sour cream and 1 egg to make soft dough.
Cover with plastic.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash all vegetables and pinch into small pieces.
Chop onion. Mix all together and lightly coat with poppy seed dressing.
Lay sliced eggs on top.

title: amaretto cake
directions: Sift together the first 6 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spray Pam in pan.
Place in a 400° preheated oven.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve the black cherry Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water, then add 1 cup of cold water.
To this, add the blueberry pie filling and pineapple.
Mix and refrigerate until firm.

title: dilly dip
directions: Mix well.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator overnight. Serve with chips and vegetables.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Toss first 5 ingredients lightly.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Chill about 3 hours.
Goo-o-od!

title: m.n.'s favorite soup
directions: In large kettle, saute bacon until browned; drain fat.
Add sausage, onion, carrot and celery.
Saute until onion is tender. Add water, tomatoes and beans.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 45 minutes until beans are almost tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered until done.
Discard bay leaf.

title: stove top parmesan
