directions: Use as many portions of meat or fowl of choice as you like. Cook until done in sprayed pan.
Top with 2 tablespoons spaghetti sauce and cover with slice of cheese.
Cover and remove from heat.
Cheese will melt.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine the mayo, vinegar and sugar. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, combine the remaining ingredients.
Pour the dressing over the salad and mix well. Serve chilled.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: french toast
directions: Mix egg, sugar and milk.
Dip bread into mixture and cook in a frying pan with oil about 15 minutes on medium heat.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Serve with maple syrup.

title: quick crab chowder
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter melted in large saucepan, using medium heat and sauteing until softened, about 15 minutes. Add all remaining ingredients except sherry and parsley and continue cooking until heated through, stirring frequently. Stir in sherry and heat about two minutes more.
Discard bay leaf and garnish with parsley.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Blend cream cheese with diced green chiles and hot pepper sauce.
Blend in Cheddar or Monterey Jack cheese. Spread each ham slice with 3 to 4 tablespoons cheese mixture and roll, jelly roll fashion, beginning at long side.
Press lightly to seal. Wrap in plastic film and chill well.

title: husband's delight
directions: Brown beef and drain fat.
Add garlic, salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add onions; simmer 5 more minutes.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream.
Fill casserole dish with alternating layers of meat and noodle mixture and cream cheese and sour cream mixture.
Spread Cheddar cheese on top. Bake at 350° until hot (approximately 20 to 25 minutes).

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine biscuit mix, water and cheese.
Stir well with a fork to blend. Divide dough in half.
On a lightly floured smooth surface, form each half into balls. With a rolling pin, roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut out rounds with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Bake on an ungreased baking sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: easy creamy rice pudding
directions: Boil rice and milk (when it comes to a boil, cover and simmer).
Cook until rice is tender.
It will be very milky. Remove from stove and add remaining ingredients, except raisins. Put back on heat, just until it returns to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add raisins, if desired.
Cool, covered.

title: cheri's creamy bean soup
directions: Wash beans and place in large bowl.
Cover with water.
Add 1 tablespoon salt.
Soak overnight.
Drain, rinse.
Add 2 quarts water and ham hock.
Boil, simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Add onion, celery, carrots, tomato juice, lemon juice, and tomatoes.
Simmer 1/2 to 1 hour.
Add milk.
Serve.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Layer pudding mixture with bananas and vanilla wafers.
Crush additional wafers and sprinkle on top.

title: ham cheese roll-up
directions: Mix ham and cream cheese; stir in pineapple, onion and honey. Spread on tortillas and roll up jelly roll style.
Store overnight in cold cut keeper, slice thin and serve with sauce.
Mix mayonnaise, mustard and honey to your taste.

title: spiders
directions: Melt morsels in double boiler.
Pour over peanuts and noodles. Stir well.
Spoon onto wax paper or nonstick cookie sheet and let harden.

title: noodle ring
directions: Brown steak and onions, add salt and pepper.
Cook noodles in salt water.
Arrange casserole alternately.
Bake 1 hour.

title: quick and easy coated chicken(microwave)
directions: Mix
baking
mix,
paprika,
salt and pepper in plastic bag. Shake
chicken in bag, 2 pieces at a time, until coated. Arrange chicken
pieces,
skin sides up and thickest parts to outside, in square
microwavable dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.	Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn and microwave until done, 6 to 8 minutes longer. Makes 4 servings.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix powdered sugar and cheese together with mixer until creamy.
Pour this over pie crust.
Beat the whipping cream until stiff like egg whites.
Spoon over cheese mixture.
Spoon cherry pie filling over whipped cream.
Chill overnight.

title: amish yum-a-setta
directions: Brown hamburger with salt and pepper, brown sugar and onion. Drain.
Add tomato soup.
Cook egg noodles and drain.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Layer hamburger mixture with noodle mixture in a casserole dish with cheese between layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot throughout.

title: chicken breast
directions: Salt and pepper boned chicken.
Mix crabmeat, celery, onions and lemon pepper.
Stuff chicken breasts.
After securing breasts with skewers, actually, they're probably not going anywhere, combine remaining ingredients to make marinade.
Place chicken on grill and broil over hot coals, basting "right regular".

title: aunt blanche's breakfast casserole
directions: Butter 8 slices of bread on one side and place buttered side down in casserole.
Sprinkle ham, onions, cheese and mushrooms over bread.
Sprinkle garlic powder and Cajun spice over this and top with remaining bread.
Mix eggs with milk, salt and dry mustard and pour over bread; cover with foil.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Remove foil and cover with crushed cornflakes.
Sprinkle melted butter over top and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve hot.
Very good.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fold in grapes.

title: snow drops
directions: Beat butter, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Work in dry ingredients gradually until mixture is smooth.
Pinch off pieces and roll into 1 inch balls.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes until light brown at 350°.
Do not overbake or brown.
Cool cookies slightly and roll in confectioners sugar.
Let cool some more and sprinkle generously again with confectioners sugar.

title: steak and lima chili
directions: Heat oil; add onion.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add meat; cook until brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: chicken 'n dumplings
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix as you would biscuits.
Spoon out and drop over chicken and gravy (dipping spoon in broth or gravy each time will make dough slide off each time).
Cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Then put lid on tight and cook slowly 10 minutes. You will have light fluffy dumplings. Season to taste with salt, pepper and butter, if needed.

title: meat loaf with mashed potatoes
directions: Combine ground beef, stuffing mix, tomato sauce, egg, salt and pepper.
Shape into 4 to 6 loaves.
Arrange in a shallow baking dish so that they do not touch.
Cover tightly.
Bake covered in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove and turn oven to 450°.

title: onions parmesan
directions: Saute onion slices in 2 tablespoons of margarine.
Spoon into an 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 cup Parmesan.
Combine soup and milk.
Pour over cheese. Spread one side of each bread slice with rest of margarine and sprinkle with rest of Parmesan.
Place bread slices, overlapping along each long side of dish leaving center open.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
To serve, place bread slice on plate; cover with onion mixture.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix well.
Pour in cake pan.
Freeze 24 hours.
Remove from freezer about 1 hour before serving.
Refrigerate after serving.

title: golden pumpkin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Reserve 1/2 cup of dry cake mix.
In large bowl, combine remaining cake mix, oil and 1 egg.
Beat until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Press firmly on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
In same bowl, combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour over prepared crust.
Bake 50 minutes or until set. Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: cherry apple salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Serve as a salad or dessert.

title: unfried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray baking sheet with 3 coats of vegetable oil.
Combine chicken and ice water in large bowl.
Put yogurt in a medium bowl.
Set both bowls aside.
To make breading, combine remaining ingredients in a large, tightly sealed plastic bag.
Seal.
Shake well to mix.
Remove 2 pieces of chicken from ice water.
Roll each piece in yogurt.
Put chicken in plastic bag. Reseal bag.
Shake to coat.
Transfer the breaded chicken to the prepared baking sheet.
Repeat the process until all 12 pieces are breaded.
Spray chicken lightly with vegetable oil.
Bake on bottom shelf of oven.
Bake for 1 hour, turning pieces every 20 minutes to allow even browning.
Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook elbow macaroni according to package directions and drain well.
Place macaroni into a greased baking dish (I use my roasting pan).
Next, in large saucepan, place canned milk.
Fill each can with cold water and add this to pan.
Add butter, salt, pepper, garlic powder and dry mustard.
Cook over medium heat until hot and add cheese.
Stir until all the cheese is melted. Mix cornstarch into 1/2 cup cold water until dissolved.
Slowly pour this into cheese sauce and stir until slightly thickened. Remove from heat and pour over macaroni.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until thick and golden brown on top.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large bowl, combine the eggs, pumpkin, sugar, salt, spices and evaporated milk with a wire whisk just until mixed.
Pour the filling into the crust.
Bake in the lower third of the oven for 15 minutes, then lower the temperature to 350°.
Continue baking for 40 to 50 minutes, or until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean.
Remove from oven and cool completely on wire rack before cutting.

title: chicken cara-mia
directions: Drain oil off artichoke hearts; save.
Add to olive oil and heat in large frypan.
Skin chicken and cut into large pieces; cook in olive oil mixture.
Remove when done.
Quarter onion and chop peppers into medium pieces.
Add to olive oil and saute.
Add sliced mushrooms; saute until just tender.
Add crushed garlic cloves; stir.
Add tomato puree, crushed tomatoes, olives and chicken.
Add remaining ingredients; cook about another 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar together in a bowl to roll cookies in. Heat oven to 400°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together just before serving.

title: chocolate bit cookies
directions: Cream butter, vanilla, cocoa and brown sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour and soda; add alternately with milk.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: microwave caramelized popcorn
directions: Cook brown sugar, Karo syrup, butter and salt slowly to boiling.
Stir, then cook 2 minutes on high heat.
Add soda; stir until thick.
Put popcorn in a brown paper bag.
Remove Karo mixture from stove; add to popcorn in bag.
You may also add 1 cup peanuts.
Microwave 1 minute on High; shake.
Microwave 1 minute on High; shake.
Microwave 1 minute on High.
Enjoy!

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and soda to creamed mixture.
Then add cereal and mix well.
Drop by teaspoons and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: apple crisp(makes about 6 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spread in ungreased 8-inch square pan the sliced apples.
Mix the remaining ingredients with fork; sprinkle over apples.
Bake for about 30 minutes, or until topping is golden brown and apples are tender.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift
the
flour
and
measure;
resift with soda.
Set aside. Cream
the
butter
and add sugar slowly, beating constantly
to cream well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after
each addition.
Stir in sour cream.
Add flour mixture 1/2 cup at a time, beating well and constantly.	Stir in lemon extract
or vanilla
and
turn	batter	into well-greased and floured
10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours or
until
done. Place pan on rack to cool 5 minutes.
Loosen cake around edge with dull side of knife.

title: green pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Cream 2 sticks margarine margarine, sugar and 1/3 cup cocoa. Add eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla; mix.
Add flour, 1 cup nuts and salt; beat two minutes.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Spread marshmallow cream on hot cake and cool.

title: high protein pancake and cookie mix
directions: Combine ingredients in a 4 or 5-quart storage container or in a heavy-duty plastic bag.
Shake vigorously and store in refrigerator.

title: grandma polly's tamale pie
directions: Brown meat. Drain excess grease.
Add chopped onion and saute. Add tomato sauce, garlic powder, creamed corn and olives.
Mix together and simmer for 5 minutes.
Next, coarsely crumble 1/2 bag Fritos chips.
Mix well and serve.

title: texas chili
directions: Pour cooking oil in skillet.
Add ground beef and simmer over medium heat until browned.
Drain; stir in tomatoes, beans, peppers, paprika, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: leslie's cookies
directions: Spray jelly roll pan with Pam.
Line with graham crackers. Boil butter, margarine and sugar for 2 minutes and pour over graham crackers.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and when cool enough to handle, place on wax paper to cool.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix eggs with sugar and butter.
Mix flour and cocoa on waxed paper; add to egg mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: diffy corn
directions: Mix; bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry chocolate cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add melted chocolate and mix well.
Pour into crust and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is set. Cool and refrigerate 3 hours.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake at 400° for 10 minutes on 1 large cookie sheet.

title: melissa's favorite birthday cake
directions: Toast almonds until lightly browned, set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients, except chocolate chips, until well blended.
Add chips.
Grease and flour 2 (8 to 9-inch) cake pans, dividing almonds between the 2 pans.
Spread batter over almonds.
(It will be thick.)
Bake at 350° for at least 35 minutes.
I have had it take 45 to 50 minutes to fully bake.
Spread fudge frosting between the 2 layers and top with whipped cream.
It is so good!! If you need a chocolate "fix" this will do it.

title: melissa's special
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box.
In large skillet, brown ground beef.
Drain and return to skillet.
Add juice from tomatoes, chili powder, salt, pepper and cheese.
Cook until smooth while stirring.
Add macaroni and mix well.
Serve with tomatoes sliced on top.

title: breakfast in a loaf
directions: Cut 2-inch slice from top of loaf; set aside for lid.
Remove soft interior of loaf, leaving a 1-inch thick wall and bottom. Place sliced ham in bottom.
Top with bell pepper rings; sprinkle with half of the cheeses.
Scramble eggs with salt until soft with no liquid remaining. Add to loaf.
Add olives and tomato slices. Top with remaining cheese and mushrooms.
Place lid on loaf.
Wrap in foil.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cut into 8 wedges.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic.
Drain grease and add rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased sheet cake pan and bake 30 minutes or until set.

title: veggie squares
directions: Press crescent rolls flat in a 9 x 11-inch pan; cook as directed on package.
Let cool completely and refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, Ranch dressing and dill weed in bowl. Spread on baked crescent rolls and press chopped vegetables on cream cheese mixture.
Top with sunflower seeds.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon.
Leave 3 tablespoons of bacon grease in skillet.
Cook onion in the bacon grease until tender.
Stir in pork and beans, brown sugar, ketchup and mustard. Put in a casserole dish and bake in the oven, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir and top with crumbled bacon.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well. Add salt and flavoring.
Add flour with baking powder.
Beat 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: beer batter
directions: Mix
dry
ingredients
together.
Beat	the egg; add to beer. Mix
egg-beer mixture to dry ingredients and stir until smooth. Great
for	onion rings, cauliflower or other vegetables.
While vegetables	are
frying,
sit back and enjoy the remaining can of beer.

title: coffee liqueur
directions: Mix sugar and water in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in the coffee; cool.
Put vodka and vanilla bean, sliced lengthwise and cut into shorter pieces, into the cooled syrup.
Pour into sterilized half gallon bottles and let stand for 30 days.
Up end the bottle occasionally.
Strain into sterilized bottles and can or cork.

title: cherry cookies
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt. In large mixer bowl, beat margarine or butter and sugar until light. Add egg yolks, dry ingredients and vanilla. Mix well. Chill dough 30 minutes.

title: baked apples
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small saucepan, combine apple juice and 1/4 cup sugar.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Heat to boiling over high heat.
Boil 6 minutes to reduce liquid.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix together ingredients and freeze.
Thaw until slushy, about 3 to 4 hours.
Serve.

title: chocolate chip pumpkin bread
directions: Grease bottoms only of 2 regular or 3 small loaf pans. Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix shortening and sugar. Add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour equally into pans.
Bake until toothpick comes out clean, about 70 minutes.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes, then loosen sides and remove from pans.
Cool completely before slicing.
Wrap and refrigerate.
Can be frozen and warmed in microwave.

title: crab spaghetti
directions: To skillet, add tomatoes, oregano, basil and thyme.
Simmer on low for 20 minutes.
Add crab and parsley.
Simmer 5 more minutes. Add garlic.
Heat through.
Serve over cooked pasta and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Serves 4 with 3 grams of fat per serving.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain
liquid
from beans.
Place beans in big bowl and mix in
green
pepper and onions.
Combine remaining ingredients, pour over beans and mix well.
Refrigerate for 12 to 24 hours before serving.

title: microwave rocky road candy
directions: Combine chocolate chips and half and half in medium bowl. Microwave on Medium-high (70%) until chips are melted, 1 to 3 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in vanilla and remaining ingredients until coated.
Press into a greased 8 x 8-inch square dish. Chill.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: In a saucepan, combine soups, enchilada sauce and Ro-Tel.
Do not add water.
Add hamburger meat.
In casserole dish, lay the tortillas in bottom.
Pour half of the mix over tortillas, then spread cheese.
Make another layer of tortillas, then the rest of the mix and cheese.
Bake in oven for 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: baked honey tomatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice off stem end of tomato and scoop out seeds.
Place, open side up, in buttered baking dish.
Mix bread crumbs, salt, pepper and tarragon.
Drizzle honey over tomatoes. Rub into cavity, sprinkle with bread crumb mixture.
Dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes.
Broil for an additional 5 minutes.

title: chimney corner dressing
directions: Beat 1/2 to 3/4 hour on low speed of mixer.

title: chunky peanut chicken
directions: In a large bowl, combine 4 teaspoons of the Worcestershire sauce and 1 tablespoon of the oil.
Add chicken; toss to coat.
In a 1-cup measure, combine the chicken stock with the tarragon.
Let chicken and broth stand 30 minutes at room temperature.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add other ingredients and let set.
Serve on lettuce.

title: autumn loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients. Place in greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes. Makes 1 loaf.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain off grease.
Add taco seasoning and 1 cup water.
Add refried beans and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
While the meat mixture is simmering, mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour meat mixture on top and mix together. Serve with nacho chips or Fritos.

title: heavenly strawberry pie
directions: Place sliced strawberries over bottom of pie crust. In medium pan, add jello, pudding and 1 1/2 cups water.
Cook over medium heat until thick and starts to boil.
Spoon hot mixture over strawberries. Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Add Cool Whip before serving.

title: hawaii fruit cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions, using pineapple juice instead of water.
Use sheath cake pan.
Allow cake to cool. Mix cream cheese and pudding (this is first layer).
Spread pineapple and Cool Whip mixture.
Coconut is next layer.
Last, top with cherries.

title: beer batter (fish)(the easy way)
directions: Mix to the thickness you desire (test fry).
Dip fish and deep fry at 350° until golden brown.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Serve while hot.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients (except tortillas) into a bowl. Spread filling on each shell.
Roll up the shells.
Chill for 6 hours or overnight.
Slice and serve.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Chop onion, cucumbers and tomatoes in large bowl.
Mix salad dressing and Salad Supreme and add to vegetables.
Add cold spaghetti and mix all ingredients well.
Chill overnight or at least 6 hours before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine soup, mayonnaise, egg, onion and broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Put margarine and stuffing mixture on top and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Blend together with pastry blender and store in refrigerator. When need for a pie, measure 2 c. mix and 1/4 c. cold water or enough to make dough to handle for a 2-crust pie.

title: veal marsala
directions: Brown the garlic in oil.
Dredge meat with salt, flour and pepper and brown in garlic oil.
Meanwhile, combine wine, parsley, 1/8 teaspoon pepper, water, 1/8 teaspoon salt and mushrooms. Slowly add wine mixture to browned veal.
Cover skillet and simmer very slowly for approximately 20 minutes or until tender.
If mixture thickens, add a small amount of water.

title: caruso crab dip(the hit of the party)
directions: Mix all ingredients (except Cheddar cheese) in casserole dish. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients; mix well.
(Can use a blender or food processor.)
Coat chicken with marinade.
Cover and put in refrigerator for 4 or more hours, stirring occasionally.
Drain chicken; grill on grill 8 to 10 minutes per side or until cooked through.
(In winter broil under broiler.)
Slice in thin slices. Wrap tortilla in foil and warm through.
Place chicken and some garnishes on tortillas.
Roll up and enjoy.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook first four ingredients for 20 minutes with lid on.
Add potatoes, carrots and mixed vegetables.
Cook until tender.
Add cream of chicken soup and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts. Freezes well.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add water to cranberries and simmer for 10 minutes.
Drain off water.
Add sugar and stir, then add dry Jell-O.
Add pineapple, chopped apple and nuts.
Stir well, then refrigerate.

title: chocolate, oatmeal and peanut butter cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, butter and milk to full boil and boil one minute.
Then take off heat and add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Spoon out and put on sheet.

title: lemon squares
directions: Cream together flour, butter, sugar; press in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° until pale gold, about 15 minutes.
Pour lemon topping over hot crust.
Let set about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine milk, margarine, cocoa and sugar in pan.
Stir to boil. Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter, vanilla and oats. Spoon on wax paper or buttered pan.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: Mix pie filling mix, gelatin and water together in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cook until clear.
Add food coloring, if desired. Cool.
Place strawberries (whole, halves or sliced) in pie crust.
Cover with cooled mixture.
Chill.

title: corn relish
directions: Husk and silk corn.
Cook in boiling water for 5 minutes; plunge into cold water.
Drain.
Cut from cobs.
Measure 8 cups cut corn.
In an 8 to 10-quart kettle, combine celery, red pepper, green pepper and onion.
Add sugar, vinegar, celery seed, 2 cups water and 2 tablespoons salt.
Bring vegetables to boiling.
Boil, uncovered, for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: surfer squares
directions: Melt butterscotch, sugar and butter in saucepan on medium, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add egg; beat well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Spread in a greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: water chestnuts wrapped with bacon
directions: Cut bacon in thirds.
Wrap a strip of bacon around a water chestnut and poke a flat toothpick through the bacon and water chestnut.
Continue wrapping water chestnuts with bacon until finished.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add condensed milk, lemon juice, vanilla and sour cream.
Mix well and pour into pie crust. Refrigerate.
Add cherries before serving.

title: skillet scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes with onion, salt and milk in a skillet. Cook, covered, at a simmer for 30 to 40 minutes, until tender. Sprinkle cheese, pepper and crumbs over top.
Continue cooking, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: amazing corn cake
directions: Combine corn and sugars.
Add eggs and oil.
Beat until well blended.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to batter and mix well. Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or foil pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: grandmother's oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine eggs, raisins and vanilla; let stand for 1 hour. Thoroughly cream shortening and sugars.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon into sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Blend in egg mixture and nuts.
Push dough by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: grandma's drop biscuits
directions: Mix together and drop by teaspoon.
Sprinkle top of cookie with whatever you desire.
Bake at 350°.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Wash and slice pickles.
Pack in jars.
On top of each jar, place 1 bay leaf and 1 clove garlic.
Heat sugar, vinegar, water, salt and dill seed together; pour over pickles.
Seal jars and pack in canner.
Bring to boil and time for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry cream salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; chill until slightly thickened. Break up cranberry sauce with fork.
Stir into gelatin with celery and nuts.
Fold in sour cream.
Pour into 4-cup mold. Chill until firm.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fruit-topped cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until creamy and smooth.
Fold in thawed whipped topping.
Spoon into graham cracker crust.
Add pie mix around edge of pie.
Chill 3 hours or longer.
Garnish with additional topping if desired.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix ingredients in a gallon container, adding water to finish filling container.
Chill and serve.

title: chewy noels(bar cookie)
directions: In a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan melt butter.
Stir together brown sugar, nuts, flour, soda and salt.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Carefully pour over butter in pan; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sift powdered sugar over top.
Place wax paper under wire rack; immediately invert pan onto rack. Cool.
Dust again with powdered sugar.
Cut into bars.
Write Noel on each bar with green decorator icing, if desired.
Makes 24.

title: rosemary chicken with cream sauce
directions: Sprinkle chicken tenderloins with salt and black pepper. Combine butter and olive oil in heavy skillet.
I like to use my electric skillet for this.
When moderately hot, add chicken, one at a time.
Add rosemary, celery seed, and thyme. Cook until all pieces of chicken are slightly golden.
Add additional butter, if needed.
Cover and simmer for about 10 minutes. Shake pan from time to time.
Uncover and pour in wine and broth.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to 350 degrees and cover skillet.
Cook about 20 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Taste and adjust seasoning, if needed.
Remove chicken and reserve all cooking liquid.
Wrap the chicken in foil to keep warm.
Strain cooking liquid and remove fat, then reduce to about half by cooking over medium heat.
Just before serving, combine cornstarch and heavy cream. Blend well and stir into warm cooking liquid, stirring until slightly thickened.
Return chicken to sauce.
Serve over rice or noodles and sprinkle with toasted almonds, if desired.

title: venison to die for
directions: Large piece of heavy-duty foil to completely wrap venison inside.
Place foil on cooking pan.
Lay venison inside.
Add oil, onions, garlic and water.
Sprinkle salt over meat and add lemon pepper to meat liberally.
Cover.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 4 to 5 hours without opening foil.
When done, slice in small slices.

title: pound cake(serves 20)
directions: Cream together sugar and butter; add eggs one at a time, beating thoroughly with each egg.
Add milk and flour alternately. Put baking powder in last.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Start in a cool oven.

title: cheese ball
directions: Set cream cheese out ahead of
time to soften.
Crush bacon into small bacon bits and chop onions real fine.
I use a blender to chop bacon and onions.
Stir bacon bits, onions and pecans into cream cheese.
Form into ball.
Chill.
Serve on snack crackers.

title: chili
directions: Cook at least 2 hours.

title: christmas relish
directions: Combine all ingredients; put in a jar and let stand.
Turn so flavors mix.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar, Karo and water in iron skillet; stir over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Increase heat until mixture boils. Boil until fine thread draining from upheld spoon can be blown away.
Add peanuts; stir so it will not scorch until syrup becomes a light amber color.
Stir in butter and add soda.
Stir and empty at once into a buttered pan.
Spread out thin.
Let it get completely cold, then give pan a twist and it will come out of pan in one piece.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Combine all together and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes, reduce heat to 325° and bake until pie sets, about 40 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Add apples.
Combine flour with salt and cinnamon.
Mix all ingredients well. Add 1 cup nuts.
Bake in moderate oven about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: blueberry and jello dessert
directions: Using pineapple juice, measure 2 cups of juice and water. Dissolve Jell-O.
Add pineapple and blueberry pie filling.
Let set in refrigerator.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and sugar.
Let set overnight.
Spread on top of Jell-O.

title: papa's con queso
directions: Cook potatoes until done.
Mash well with butter, cream, salt and eggs; beat well.
Shape potatoes into balls.
With handle of teaspoon, make a hollow place in the ball and fill with cube of cheese.
Grease each potato ball with a bit of lard, place in a hot oven (450°) and brown.
Serve balls sprinkled with chopped parsley and garnish with slices of tomato.

title: grandma's strawberry shortcake(makes 8 servings)
directions: Sprinkle strawberries with 1 cup sugar; let stand 1 hour. Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease round layer pan, 8 x 1 1/2-inches. Stir together flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, baking powder and salt. Cut in shortening.
Stir in milk, just until blended.
Spread dough in pan.
Bake until golden brown, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: irish fruit bread
directions: Combine margarine, egg, sugar and salt.
Mix well with spoon. Add orange juice.
Add seed, fruits, dry ingredients and buttermilk.
Stir well.
Mixture will be fairly thick.
Spread in square baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: easy key lime pie
directions: Mix limeade, milk, Cool Whip and food coloring; pour into pie crust and chill.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease pan.
Place apple chunks in 8 x 10-inch pan.
Melt stick of butter.
Mix sugar and Bisquick, then pour it on top of apples.
Pour butter on top of sugar and Bisquick mixture.
Spread butter evenly.
Add cinnamon to your desired taste.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
Eat it up.

title: mistletoe  dip
directions: Blend soup with sour cream.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill at least 1 hour. Yields 1 1/2 cups.
Serve with chips or bread sticks.

title: napoleon cremes
directions: Bottom Layer:
Combine 1/2 cup margarine, sugar, cocoa and vanilla in 3-quart pan.
Cook until margarine melts.
Stir in egg. Blend in graham cracker crumbs and coconut.
Press in 9 x 13-inch square pan.

title: encore cherry salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water and stir in pie filling.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish and chill until set.
Dissolve lemon Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Beat together cream cheese and mayonnaise and gradually add lemon Jell-O to mixture.
Stir in pineapple and fold in Cool Whip.
Pour lemon Jell-O mixture over raspberry Jell-O mixture and sprinkle pecans over top.
Chill.
Cut into squares to serve.
Serves 12.

title: apple pie
directions: Slice apples and de-core and take skin off.
Place in plastic bag with cinnamon, sugar and nutmeg and shake.
(Optional:
best if you leave in bag overnight to get flavor and juice.)
Place in bottom of pie shell.
Place top shell over apple filling.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Place pan under pie to catch drippings.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating between each.
Fold in flour after sifting 5 times, alternating with whipping cream.
Bake in well-greased and floured tube pan. Start in cold oven; set temperature at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
This is particularly good served with fresh strawberries.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecan halves, in a saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Boil until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water.
Stir in pecans quickly.
Continue to stir until pecans separate.
Spread on wax paper.
Break apart while cooling.
Store in a tight container.

title: beef and cheese casserole
directions: Boil
macaroni	until
tender,	drain.	Brown
meat
in skillet, pour off
fat,
add
onions,
green pepper and sauce. Simmer about 5
minutes.
Add
1/3 macaroni in casserole dish. Add 1/3 sauce,	1/3 of both cheeses, continue in layers ending with cheese on top.
Bake
in
oven at 350° until cheese melts and mixture bubbles.

title: cappuccino caramels
directions: Line an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan with foil, extending the foil over edges of pan.
Butter the foil; set the pan aside.

title: mandel brats
directions: Mix ingredients (except for extra sugar) together, adding chocolate chips last because dough will be stiff.
Spread onto a greased cookie sheet (12 x 24-inch).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cut into bars.
Turn bars onto side and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon; bake at 350° for an additional 10 minutes.
Turn bars on other side and repeat process.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon and bake another 10 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen cookies. Goes great with a cup of coffee.

title: swiss cheese and mushroom quiche
directions: Spread Swiss cheese over bottom of pie dish.
Beat together eggs, milk, flour, salt and mustard.
Set aside.
Saute in pan the onion and 1/4 pound mushrooms with 1/4 cup margarine, salt and pepper.
Pour over cheese layer.
Pour custard mixture, eggs, flour, etc. over mushrooms.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake.

title: chicken divan
directions: Combine soup, mayonnaise, juice and curry powder.
Arrange broccoli in small bunches in bottom of a baking dish.
Place a chicken breast on each bunch.
Pour the soup mixture over the broccoli and chicken.
Sprinkle the Parmesan cheese, American cheese and stuffing over mixture in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until bubbling.

title: patchwork chili
directions: Crumble beef and cook until no longer pink.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Can season with garlic powder, oregano, basil, etc. Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: multiple choice ham casserole
directions: Chop cauliflower and/or broccoli into flowerets or bite size pieces.
Steam cauliflower and/or broccoli until tender.
Place cauliflower and/or broccoli in a lightly greased 2-quart casserole; sprinkle with ham.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in a heavy saucepan.
Blend in flour and cook until bubbly.
Add cheese, stirring, until melted.
Spoon sauce over ham.
Combine bread crumbs and remaining butter; spoon over sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry winks
directions: Mix
together
shortening,
sugar
and eggs.
Add milk, vanilla, flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Then add nuts, dates and cherries with juice.

title: prairie apple crunch
directions: Place apples in a greased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch dish.
Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Combine brown sugar, flour and butter.
Sprinkle brown sugar mixture over apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Can be served with cream or ice cream. Serves 10 to 12.

title: region three treats
directions: Mix the marshmallow cream with the peanut butter. Add Rice Krispies and mix thoroughly. Shape into balls. Refrigerate for awhile. Dip into melted chocolate. Lay on wax paper to dry. Can freeze them or store them in the refrigerator.

title: blueberry yum yum
directions: Soften margarine enough to mix with cracker crumbs. Mix sugar, margarine and crumbs to mealy; set aside.

title: shake 'n bake
directions: Mix all ingredients and use to coat anything you oven-fry. It's economical and keeps well in airtight containers.
You have the option to vary interests in tastes.

title: heart healthy cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Add slightly beaten egg whites, canola oil and buttermilk.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into hot canola oil-coated cast iron skillet.
Bake in a 450° oven for 20 minutes to a golden brown.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, oil, water, 1 package vanilla pudding and the eggs.
Add the second box of vanilla pudding mix and poppy seed.
Bake in greased Bundt pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hot wings
directions: Mix. Set in fridge overnight. Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown ground beef, green pepper and onion.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cucumber and dill salad
directions: Peel the cucumbers and split them in half.
Scoop out the seeds with a mellon ball cutter.
Slice the cucumbers crosswise. There should be about 4 cups.
Put the slices in a mixing bowl. Add the remaining ingredients and toss to blend.
Add more seasonings, such as vinegar, sugar and so on to taste, if desired. Yield:
4 servings.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: In baking dish, put sweet potatoes with juice from can.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle brown sugar over sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until juice is thickened.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Blend shortening with flour. Slowly stir in juice, stirring until well blended. Add raisins and let simmer 10 to 12 minutes.

title: crunch cabbage slaw
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: great sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar with mixer.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together, then add a cupful at a time to the creamed mixture, stirring until smooth.
Chill overnight, if possible.
Roll out and cut with your favorite shapes.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate with frosting or colored sugar.

title: super chocolate cake
directions: Have margarine and eggs at room temperature.
Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add melted chocolate.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add cold water and vanilla; mix well again.
The batter may curdle slightly at this point, but it does no harm.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with the boiling water.
Batter will be very thin.
Pour into a greased 8 x 11-inch pan.
Bake for about 35 minutes at 350°.

title: summer okra casserole(yields 4 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Fry seitan in oil until browned, about 5 minutes.
Add onion, soup, pickles, catsup and okra.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish and top with biscuits.
Bake until biscuits are golden brown, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: macaroni and cheese deluxe
directions: Cook macaroni. Combine next 6 ingredients and add to macaroni. Stir well. Spoon into lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread with crumb topping
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat 1/2 cup butter until creamy.
Add 3/4 cup brown sugar, white sugar and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Blend in pumpkin.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Mix together 2 1/2 cups flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir into pumpkin mixture.
Fold in 1 cup nuts and raisins.
Spoon into 2 greased loaf pans.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Place rice in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle onion soup mix on top of rice.
Place chicken on top of soup-rice mixture.
Brush the cream of chicken soup on top of chicken pieces.
Pour water around chicken.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for one hour or until chicken is done.
Watch it carefully and add a little water if the rice seems to get dry.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat; add other ingredients and cook slowly for 2 hours.

title: caramel bars
directions: Melt caramels with cream or milk.

title: amaretto fruit dip
directions: Mix first three ingredients (can be done ahead).
When ready to serve, fold into Cool Whip.
Delicious served with fresh fruit. If not all used, can be frozen.

title: sea lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add softened cream cheese.
Blend until only small specks of cheese are still showing. Refrigerate until cool, but not set.
Fold in pineapple and nuts. Fold in Cool Whip.
Place in jello mold.

title: lemon cheesecake mousse pie
directions: Stir milk into softened cream cheese; stir in lemon pudding mix.
Fold pudding and cream cheese into whipped cream.
Add lemon extract and 2 tablespoons lemon zest.
Pile high into crust. Garnish with remaining zest.
Chill well.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place a slice of ham and cheese on each chicken breast.
Roll up carefully, beginning at narrow end.
Secure rolls with wooden toothpicks.
